title: cheesecake roll-ups
directions: Mix together cream cheese, egg yolk and sugar.
Spread over bread.
Roll up jelly roll style.
Dip in melted butter, then into cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Freeze overnight.
Cut each roll in half and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 32 rolls.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Bring kettle of water to a boil; add some oil.
Add 1 pound spaghetti; cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 15 minutes; drain.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar (white) until fluffy.
Add flour and pecans.
Roll into balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Roll into powdered sugar when cool enough. Store into tight can.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add liquids, beaten eggs, melted margarine and buttermilk.
Mix well; put in covered container and let set in refrigerator 24 hours before use.
Bake as desired in 375° or 400° oven for 20 minutes.
This batter will keep in refrigerator 2 or 3 weeks.

title: chocolate velvet walnut cake
directions: Preheat your oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, pudding, eggs, sour cream, vanilla, water and oil with a mixer.
Then fold in your chocolate chips and nuts (pecans and almonds work well also). Grease a tube pan well.
(If this is not cooked in a tube pan it will not turn out right.
I know I've tried.)
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: string beans and potatoes
directions: Place desired amount of string beans in a pot.
Add potatoes. Add water to nearly cover beans and salt.
Bring to boiling.
Cook for a half hour over medium heat, covered.

title: swiss bliss
directions: Spread 20-inch sheet of heavy-duty Reynolds Wrap with margarine.
Cut steak into serving pieces and arrange on foil, overlapping.
Sprinkle with onion soup, mushrooms, pepper and chopped tomatoes.
Season.
Mix tomato juice and cornstarch.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Seal and bake for 2 hours at 375°. (Beef cubes can be used instead of chuck steak.)

title: potato salmon hash
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil in a
bowl until blended.
Let mixture stand 10 minutes.
Heat oil in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat.
Add potato mixture, spreading with a spatula to cover bottom of pan.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes, pressing down occasionally until bottom is browned and crisp.
Turn hash in clumps and press back into a round.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes longer until bottom is brown and crisp.
Loosen with spatula. Invert onto serving plate and cut in wedges.
Makes 2 servings.

title: bow tie pasta
directions: *You may use regular sausage and add red pepper flakes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in covered dish.
Season chicken.
Add the green pepper, onions and garlic.
No water.
Let stand 2 hours. Cook at 300° until tender.

title: hoe cake cornbread
directions: Mix
meal, salt and water together.
This will be about pouring
consistency.
Heat
iron skillet (or Teflon) and pour in bacon drippings, just enough to cover bottom of pan.
Pour mix
in center
of
pan until it almost touches sides of pan. Turn
with spatula
when edges brown.
Cook a little more and drain
on paper towels.
This could be served with vegetables but
we usually eat it with country butter or break it up in a glass and pour milk over it.
This makes 3 to 4 Hoe Cakes.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: After thawing bread dough, roll on lightly floured surface. Roll into rectangle shape.
Cover each rolled loaf with thin pepperoni slices and roll dough from the short end.

title: spiced grapes
directions: Remove and set aside skins.
Cook pulp in vinegar with spices tied in cheese cloth until soft.
Mash through sieve to keep out seeds.
Add skins.
Bring to boil.
Add sugar and bag of spices. Cook until thick.
Put into jars and seal.
Good with chicken or pork!

title: jewish cookies
directions: Cream well the margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, cocoa and salt.
Mix well; fold in nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and thinly slice apples.
Place in a bowl and toss with cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar.
Let stand while preparing batter.

title: twin mountain muffins
directions: Cream butter. Add sugar and egg. Blend well. Sift together flour, baking powder. Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to butter mixture. Preheat oven to 450°. Line muffin pan with paper baking cups. Spoon in batter. Bake 10 min or until browned slightly. These are delicious with soups or breakfast.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Heat water to boiling and add vegetables.
Cook 5 to 6 minutes until tender.
In another saucepan, melt margarine over low heat. Blend in flour.
While stirring, slowly add milk. Cook over low heat until it thickens.
Add crushed bouillon cubes. Stir to dissolve.
Add cooked vegetables in water. Stir and heat until bubbly. Serve.

title: texas hash
directions: Prepare rice according to directions on package.
Brown meat, green pepper, onion and rice in skillet.
Add salt, black pepper and catsup.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Brown in 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in shortening.
Add seasonings and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer.
Add beans.
Pour meat mixture in greased casserole dish.
Top with corn bread batter.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate banana pudding
directions: Blend milks together; add pudding and chill for 5 minutes. Gradually add sour cream.
Add Cool Whip.
In clear bowl, layer wafers, bananas, pudding and nuts.
Swirl with syrup after each layer of pudding.
End with pudding layer, covered with nuts and syrup.

title: fruit cocktail delight
directions: In bowl, combine fruit cocktail and pudding mix. Mix well. Fold in marshmallows just before serving. Garnish with nuts if desired. Refrigerate. Yields 6 servings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all together.
Heat at 300° until warm.
Serve with toasted pita triangle.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender and mash.
Add onions, salt and pepper. Soak sliced bread in milk and add squash. Stir in eggs and cheese.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: white buttercream
directions: Melt Premier white baking bars and heavy cream over hot (not boiling) water until smooth.
Transfer to a large mixer bowl; cool to room temperature.
Gradually beat in cold butter and confectioners sugar; continue beating until light and fluffy.

title: pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers.
Dissolve lime in water.
Put cucumbers in this and soak 24 hours.
Pour water off and soak in clear water 4 hours, changing water each hour.

title: old fashioned cream pie
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
Add cream, milk, vanilla and salt.
Blend with mixer and pour into pastry shells.
Melt butter and dribble over top.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce to 350° and bake 50 minutes.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Brown meat.
(If leftover meat is used, do not cook more in liquid.)
Add 2 cups liquid, chicken broth, gravy, 2 tablespoons soy sauce, 2 teaspoons brown sugar and Accent.
Cook all this 20 minutes (if raw meat was used).
Add onion and celery; simmer 5 minutes (or until transparent, but still crisp).
Add bean sprouts and mushrooms.
Stir gently.
Thicken with 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Serve with rice and chow mein noodles.

title: sweet potato pie #2
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheets to 375°.
Boil sweet potatoes in water until tender (may use canned).
Cool slightly.
Place in large mixing bowl. Beat with electric mixer until smooth. Stir in butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix in spices and salt.
Pour in Pet milk and mix.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake on preheated cookie sheets near center of oven for 70 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: christmas cake
directions: Prepare raisins and peel.
Mix baking powder, salt and cinnamon with the flour and sift.
Beat butter and sugar to soft cream.
Beat eggs for 5 minutes.
Add them to the butter mixture by degrees, beating all the time.
When mixture is quite smooth, continue beating while you add the flour gradually, then the fruit and almonds.
Stir in the brandy or rum and turn into a cake pan that has been lined with two thicknesses of waxed paper.
Bake in slow oven 5 hours at 325°.
Cover with waxed paper as soon as it is brown.
This cake will keep for 6 months or more in airtight tin and should be made several weeks or a month before Christmas. Cut the top level for frosting.

title: salmon stew
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and sugar together in a large mixing bowl.
Make deep well in center of dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, oil and thawed strawberries.
Pour into well.
Stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Add pecans.
Pour into 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pans and cool on wire racks.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Layer these ingredients on a large platter in order given. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate several hours. Overnight is really better for flavors to blend. Garnish platter as desired.

title: chuck wagon dip
directions: Heat oil in deep skillet. Saute onions and peppers until translucent. Remove with slotted spoon. Crumble ground beef. Brown with garlic in skillet. Return onion and pepper to skillet. Add remaining ingredients and bring to gentle simmer. Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes, stirring frequently. Add water, if needed, to prevent sticking.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Top with cheese.

title: green bean soup
directions: Add water to bone or cubed turkey ham and vegetables.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes or until tender. Add milk or cream.

title: rice ring
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Press lightly into a greased mold. Unmold at once onto a hot platter.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and add sugar gradually; beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add pumpkin, mixing to combine.
Sift together the flour, salt, soda, baking powder and spices.
Blend with pumpkin mixture.
Add nuts and raisins.
Place batter in 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake approximately 60 to 65 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool.
Wrap and store overnight before slicing.
Makes 2 loaves. Dates can be used instead of raisins.

title: carry along casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix in tomato sauce and mushrooms.
Simmer.

title: quincy jones punch
directions: Take a bit of thoughtfulness.
Blend it with a smile. Stir in lots of kindness as you tread life's weary mile.
Mix encouragement with some sunshine to dry up someones tears; stirring in a few words of sympathy that are certainly most sincere.
Then your reward will be great in heaven.
Your life will be free from strife if you follow this recipe for a good and useful life.

title: hungarian potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jacket until almost done.
Cool, peel and slice.
Melt oleo in saucepan.
Add soup and sour cream.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Alternate layers of potatoes and mixture.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cook in oven at 350° until hot throughout and cheese is melted.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pull chicken off bones and place in bottom of casserole.
Mix flour, baking powder and milk well.
Pour over chicken.
Then mix soup and broth and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until brown around edge.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and stir in stuffing mix.
Grease casserole dish and put a layer of buttered crumbs on bottom of dish.
(Keep enough back to sprinkle over the top.)
Place chicken over crumbs. Mix soup, sour cream, and water chestnuts and pour over the chicken.
Top with remaining stuffing crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: dinner party chicken
directions: Saute chicken in butter until white.
Cut in halves or break in pieces.
Saute onion and celery.
Add soup and mayonnaise until heated.
Pour over chicken which is in a baking dish.
Mix stufffing, eggs and butter (melted).
Put stuffing over sauce and chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Put foil over baking dish when stuffing is brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix; roll into walnut size balls.
Place on cookie sheet; pat out flat.
Bake for 8 minutes at 350°.
Cool before removing from cookie sheet.

title: orange brussels sprouts
directions: *If using fresh Brussels sprouts, trim stems and remove wilted or discolored leaves.
Wash Brussels sprouts and cut large ones in half lengthwise.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in a buttered Pyrex dish.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Saute shallots and onion.
Add tarragon, allspice, dill, bay leaf, garlic, tomatoes and chicken broth.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 30 minutes.
Strain and puree vegetables.
Return mixture to pot and add whipping cream, sugar, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil and serve.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: In a bowl, blend cream cheese, vanilla and butter to a smooth texture; set aside.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Stew chicken with salt, pepper and bay leaf.
In a large saucepan cook green pepper and onion in margarine until tender. Stir in soups and Rotel tomatoes.
In a 13x9x2 inch dish, alternate layers of tortillas, chicken, soup mixture and cheese using 1/3 of all ingredients.
Repeat layers 2 more times.
Bake at 325 degrees for 40 minutes.
Serves 10-12.

title: texas brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream
together sugar and shortening with milk, vanilla and egg.
Sift together flour, salt and cream of tartar.
Add to sugar
mixture.
Blend
well.
Roll
into
small balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheet one inch apart.
Flatten with fork that's been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 4 dozen cookies.
Should be very crisp.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Mix grape jelly and mustard.
Melt in crock-pot.
Add sliced smoked sausage.
Cook on low 1 to 2 hours.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese log
directions: Blend well and roll into log and roll in chili powder.
Wrap in plastic (not foil).

title: fool proof pie crust
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together with mixer, then add next 3 ingredients.
Mix well and mold into ball.
Chill well before using (dough will be moist).
Dough can be stored in refrigerator for 2 weeks or can be frozen.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and refrigerate.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except frozen vegetables in crock-pot. Cook on low for 10 to 11 hours. Add frozen vegetables and heat through, about 1 more hour.
Yields 8 servings.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix margarine, flour and sugar together.
Pat into pizza pan and bake at 350° for 12 minutes; let cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and confectioners sugar together; spread over cool crust. Cook strawberries (sweeten if not already) and cornstarch until thick.
Then spread over cream cheese mixture.

title: chicken rolled in crescent
directions: Unfold rolls. Mix chicken with 3 Tbsp. cheese. Place chicken mixture on rolls and roll up, folding in the ends. Mix soup and milk. Add half of this mixture in a flat, greased casserole dish. Place rolls in mixture and pour remaining soup over them.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix by hand sugar and oil.
Add eggs one at a time.
Whip carrots into this.
Then add dry ingredients.
Bake in an 8 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
In some ovens it may take one hour.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Beat together sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs.
Add flour and baking powder.
Add apples and pecans.
Bake in greased and floured pan (Bundt pan) at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: lentil salad
directions: Rinse and sort lentils.
Place lentils in large pot with carrots, onions, cloves, chicken stock, bay leaf and thyme. Bring to boil; reduce to simmer.
Cook 25 minutes.
When lentils are done, drain and discard carrot, onion, cloves and bay leaf.

title: rich frosted brownies
directions: Combine sugar, flour, eggs, butter, cocoa and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until center is firm. Allow to cool.
Frost with Chocolate Frosting.
Yield:
about 48 (1 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch) squares.

title: jello magic milk shakes
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender or shake vigorously until well blended.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet-sour sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Good for wings, spareribs or ham.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Melt the margarine in the water.
Mix all ingredients (except last 3) together well.
Pour into large cake pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch). Top with nuts and chocolate chips; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Generously grease bottoms only of two 9 x 5 x 3-inch baking pans.
Beat all ingredients on low speed for 1 minute, then beat on medium speed for 1 minute.
Pour in pans.
Bake until toothpick inserted in bread comes out clean, about 1 hour, in a preheated 325° oven.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: coconut pie
directions: Put ingredients in blender, except coconut, and blend on low for 3 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand five minutes.
Sprinkle on coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Combine beef, rice, salt and pepper. Form into small balls. Place in baking dish. In a skillet, brown onions in butter. Add cream of mushroom, water, salt and pepper to taste. Pour over meat balls. Cover baking dish and bake in 350° oven about 1 hour or until rice is tender.

title: molasses krinkles
directions: Mix together brown sugar, shortening, egg and molasses.
Sift together flour, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon and cloves.
Combine mixtures.
Chill until firm enough to form small balls.
Dip one side in sugar and flatten in a greased cookie sheet.
Place a couple of drops water on each cookie.
Bake at 350° to 375°, approximately 8 to 10 minutes.
Underbake for a softer cookie. Otherwise, will be ginger snap.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Soak cucumbers in salted water 20 to 30 minutes.
Squeeze carefully to remove excess water.
Do not mash.
Put into a bowl; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix with enough sour cream to cover cucumbers.

title: minestrone
directions: In a large Dutch oven, heat oil over medium heat.
Add carrots, onion, celery and garlic.
Cook, stirring often, 3-5 minutes or until onion is softened.
Stir in the tomatoes and cook for 2 minutes.
Pour in broth and increase heat to high; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring often, or until reduced.
In a separate saucepan, cook cauliflower, zucchini and green beans in boiling salted water.
As soon as the water returns to a boil, drain vegetables.
Add vegetables and cannellini beans to the soup; season with salt and pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes, or until vegetables are just tender.
Stir in the basil and ladle into bowls.
Serve with a dish of freshly grated Parmesan to sprinkle on top.

title: marinated bean bonanza
directions: Mix vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper in a 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Mix in beans, green pepper and onion.
Cover; refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Before serving, remove to salad bowl with slotted spoon.

title: cheddar cheese log
directions: Grate cheese in a mixing bowl.
Add onion, Worcestershire sauce and paprika; beat well with electric mixer until well blended.
Shape into a long roll, 2 inches in diameter.
Roll log in pecans until it's well coated.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill overnight or until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: punch
directions: Combine juices and water until melted.
Add ice cubes; add sherbet.
Pour ginger ale down sides of bowl.
Serves 40 cups.

title: quick salad dessert
directions: Combine pineapple and cottage cheese in colander.
When drained, pour into mixing bowl.
Add dry jello and mix.
Then fold in whipped cream.
Chill and serve.

title: spaghetti and cheese
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Cook vermicelli; drain.
Mix beef, onion, pepper, cheese, tomatoes and spaghetti.
Cook over very low heat until cheese is melted and mixed in.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add water or red wine if dry.

title: cranberry velvet
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Fold in whipped cream. Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
Add mayonnaise and then add coffee.
Stir until well blended.

title: german slaw
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, oil, celery seed, salt and mustard.
Boil for 1 minute.

title: squash souffle
directions: Mix
all ingredients.
Pour into well greased casserole. Top with
extra
crumbs;
sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 1 hour.

title: whipping cream cake
directions: Cream 2 sticks butter and 3 cups sugar until light and fluffy. Add 6 eggs, 1 at a time.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Add flour; put in the whipping cream last.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: hot cabbage creole
directions: Fry bacon in Dutch oven.
Add onion and green pepper; saute until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: banana salad
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients together until thick; stir constantly.
Cool until ready to serve.
Pour over bananas (sliced or split); sprinkle with salted peanuts.
Dressing keeps well in refrigerator for several days.
A quick dessert or salad.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together.
Make a soft dough.
Put in greased pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 500°.

title: yeast cornbread
directions: Combine
first
3 ingredients.
Combine dry ingredients in another bowl.
Add oil to yeast mixture.
Add yeast mixture to dry ingredients all at once.
Stir only until mixed.
Pour into sprayed
x 13-inch baking pan.
Smooth top with knife. Rise 20 to 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: butter pecan dessert
directions: Mix ice cream and Cool Whip.
In a separate bowl, mix pudding and milk.
Combine mixtures together.
Mix well.
Mix crackers and butter together.
Layer a 9 x 13-inch pan with 2/3 of cracker mixture.
Pour ice cream mixture on top of crackers.
Top with remaining crackers.
Keep in freezer until 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: cream gravy
directions: After frying meat, remove all grease except about 1/3 cup leaving it and the drippings in skillet.
Add flour, stirring to prevent lumping.
Cook on medium-low heat until light brown.
Add milk, depending on the thickness desired.
Stir continually to avoid lumping.
Season to taste.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar and Karo.
Heat enough to melt together and mix well.
Prepare wafers, fruit and nuts.
Pour melted mixture over dry ingredients and mix well.
Pack firm into a tube pan or individual pans and let stand overnight or several hours before cutting.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cut chicken breasts up into pieces.
Sprinkle with spices and cook in 1 tablespoon oil until done.
Layer in order the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° until cheese is bubbly and casserole is warm through.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt in a bowl. In another bowl, beat butter on medium speed until smooth and creamy, about 1 minute. Gradually beat in sugars and continue beating for about 2 minutes. Beat in eggs one at a time and add the vanilla. Stir in flour mixture until just combined. Add chocolate chips, oats, coconut and pecans.

title: harvard beets
directions: In medium saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch, 1/2 cup water and the vinegar until blended.
Bring to boiling, stirring constantly; simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in beets; cover and let stand 30 minutes. Just before serving, bring beet mixture to boiling.
Stir in margarine, salt and pepper.

title: quick and easy rolls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Spoon batter into muffin pans, coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 1 dozen rolls.
Each serving amount:
1 roll.
Calories per serving: 90.
Exchanges:
1 starch

title: snow whirl frosting
directions: Put egg whites, sugar, water and cream of tartar or corn syrup in top of double boiler, mixing thoroughly.
Place over rapidly boiling water and beat constantly with beater until mixture will hold a peak (7 minutes). Remove from boiling water.
Add vanilla and beat until cool and thick enough to spread.
Makes enough frosting for tops and sides of two 9-inch layers.

title: appetizer roll-ups
directions: Remove crust.
Mix cream cheese, chives and parsley together; spread on one side of bread.
Cut each slice in half; roll up and secure with thin strip of bacon and toothpick.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Put pie filling in an 8 x 10-inch pan and cover with dry cake mix. Cut butter into small squares and cover cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes (until slightly brown).
You can use other kinds of pie filling also; but cherry is Jamie's favorite.

title: stuffed pasta shells
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Stuff shells and place on oiled baking pan.
(Preferably olive oil.) Dot with spaghetti sauce.
Cover with foil.
Heat at 325° for about 10 minutes or until hot.

title: marilyn's marinated carrots
directions: Slice and cook carrots until tender.
Combine cooked carrots with sliced green peppers and onions in a bowl.

title: monte cristo au gratin
directions: Place meat between 2 slices of bread.
Dip sandwiches in egg mixture.
Heat oil and butter in a frying pan; fry both sides of sandwiches until golden brown.
Place in a baking dish.
Combine cheese, milk, mayo and nutmeg in a saucepan.
Heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts and mixture is smooth.
Pour over sandwiches and broil 6 inches form broiler for 3 to 5 minutes, until bubbly.
Makes 3 servings.

title: chicken cutlets
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray cookie sheet with no-stick cooking spray.
Place margarine in one bowl.
Place remaining ingredients in another bowl. Dip chicken in margarine and then coat with mixture.
Place on cookie sheet and bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake to box directions.
Take from oven and with a handle of a wooden spoon, poke holes in cake.
Pour condensed milk over cake, then pour caramel over top of milk.
Let cool.
Spread on whipped topping and then break up cold candy bars on top of whipped topping.
Keep refrigerated.

title: nine layer salad
directions: Break the lettuce into small pieces. Spread the lettuce in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then sprinkle the celery over the lettuce.
Add the green pepper, frozen peas, onion, eggs and bacon in layers.
Mix the sugar into the mayonnaise.
Spread mayonnaise over the top of the salad.
To with cheese.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap or foil and place into refrigerator for 8 to 12 hours before serving.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 7 minutes over medium heat.
Add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan, well-greased.

title: mexican cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables in water until tender. Add soup and bouillon cubes and finish cooking. Turn heat down to simmer and stir in cheese.

title: sunshine pickles
directions: Fill quart jars with cucumbers, still whole; pack lightly. Fill half full with vinegar.
Finish filling with water.
Seal and set in sun for 8 days.

title: martha's favorite kool-aid punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: baked lasagne
directions: Brown meat; add onion
and
garlic
in oil.
Add tomato paste and tomato sauce and
stir
well.
Add
sugar,
salt and pepper and simmer on low heat.
Add
3 cans water for each can of tomato paste and 2 cans water for each tomato sauce.
Bring to boil and cook until
it thickens.
Boil lasagne; drain when done.
Bake in 10 x
13-inch
pan.
Layer
meat
sauce, cooked lasagne
and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat
until
pan
is
full. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cherry cola soda blender style
directions: Blend the cola beverage and sugar into an electric blender container.
Cover and turn on motor.
Add cherries and then ice cream.
Blend until thick and smooth.
Divide mixture among 8 tall glasses.
Fill with cola beverage.
Give a quick stir.
Top each with a scoop of ice cream.

title: hot bean casserole
directions: Drain all beans except pork and beans.
Saute onions in bacon fat.
Add vinegar and brown sugar.
Cook slowly about 20 minutes. Add beans and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour uncovered, stirring occasionally.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 days.
Reheat until hot.

title: no egg or milk muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients to blend.
Add safflower oil (don't stir). Add 3/4 cup of total water.
Stir.
Add remaining water gradually and stir.
Bake in an oiled Teflon muffin pan at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Stir and blend well.
To serve use about 2 teaspoons per cup of boiling water.
Store in an airtight can or jar and this mix will keep for several weeks.
Makes about 1-1/2 pints.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers and add milk. Stir until wafers are moist.
Add cut up fruit; mix well. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pack in your favorite pan or mold.
Store in refrigerator. This cake freezes well.

title: chicken fingers with honey mustard
directions: Cut chicken into 1/2 x 2 inch strips. Mix flour, salt and pepper in a shallow bowl.
Dip chicken in milk and roll in flour mixture to coat well.
Place chicken on waxed paper.

title: fried corn
directions: Put frozen corn and remaining ingredients in covered thick pan and cook for 1 hour, stirring often.

title: stuff pears
directions: Beat honey and cream cheese together in a bowl.
Spoon into pears and place into a baking dish.
Top with graham crackers crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Mix as directed on box and bake 3 layers.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Heat vinegar, salt and sugar.
Bring to boil and pour over cabbage.
Let it cool.
Keeps for weeks.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Arrange 1 can green beans in a casserole dish lined with butter.
Layer on top soup, onion rings and water chestnuts; repeat with green beans.
Depending on how large you want your casserole as to how many cans of green beans you use.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup with sour cream.
Mix all together.
In a separate bowl melt 1/2 stick oleo; add and mix one tube Ritz crackers, crushed.
Sprinkle this mixture on top of casserole and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: chicken rice-a-roni casserole
directions: Mix together.
For topping, combine crushed Ritz crackers and 1/2 stick margarine.
Spread on top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cherries on a cloud
directions: Tear angel food cake into small pieces.
Layer bottom of small cake pan.
Mix together Dream Whip, powdered sugar, milk and cream cheese until thickened.
Pour over angel food cake; top with cherries and chill for 1 hour.

title: skillet corn
directions: Cut corn off cob.
Scrape ears to get the milk and all of the kernels.
Cook and stir all ingredients in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until margarine is melted.
Cover and cook over low heat until corn is tender 10 to 15 minutes.

title: salted pumpkin seeds
directions: Remove seeds from pumpkin and wash off all pulp (you will learn anew the meaning of slippery doing this).
Place seeds in shallow baking pans.
Half cover seeds with saltwater (1 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water).
Place in a 200° oven and bake until all water has evaporated and seeds are crisp.
Store in airtight container if they last that long.

title: stewed corn
directions: Cut top layer of corn from cob.
Scrape remainder of corn from cob.
Mix corn and other ingredients and pour into skillet. Simmer on low heat 40 to 45 minutes; stir frequently.

title: beau monde dip
directions: Mix together and serve with raw vegetables or Fritos chips.

title: cream eggnog
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and salt in 3-quart mixing bowl.
Mix in evaporated milk, cream, vanilla and rum.
Chill.
Pour into punch bowl.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add one egg at a time, mixing well.
Stir soda into sour cream.
Add flour and sour cream to butter mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour (do not open oven).
Continue baking at 325° for 15 minutes longer.

title: lasagna toss
directions: Form individual hamburger patties onto separate pieces of foil, as if you were making hamburger steaks.
Place foil on large cookie sheet or large pan; one large patty per member of family.
Slice potatoes thin onto top of meat.
Do the same with an onion.
Salt and pepper to taste, then sprinkle all over with Worcestershire sauce.
Cover each dinner with foil and bake for about 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Easy and work saving.
Serve with a salad and bread if desired.
A delicious change!

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, cook and stir bacon or ham and onion until bacon is crisp and onion is tender.
Drain drippings.
Stir in soup and milk; heat, stirring occasionally.
Drain clams (refill the can of clams with fresh water); add to mixture.
Stir in lemon juice, pepper and thyme.
Heat on low until desired thickness.
Serves 4.

title: carrot loaf
directions: Dissolve sugar in oil.
Add sifted dry ingredients; add carrots; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into loaf pan and bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Cool.
Remove from loaf pan.

title: fruit basket delight
directions: Blend flour and margarine together.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: orange cream milk punch
directions: Place the ice cream and sherbet in a punch bowl. Pour in the milk and lemon-lime soda. Stir gently and serve immediately.

title: shrimp gerlu
directions: Melt butter in baking pan.
Soften onion in pan in broiler for about 5 minutes.
Do not brown.
Place shrimp in single layer over onions.
Put one piece of bacon on each shrimp.
Put one teaspoon sweet and sour sauce on each shrimp and bacon.
Broil until bacon is crisp and shrimp is pink, only about 10 minutes.
Great appetizer or main course.

title: orange fluff
directions: Pour Jell-O and pineapple (do not drain) into medium saucepan. Bring to a boil while stirring.
Boil and stir for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and allow to cool (15 to 20 minutes).
Stir in buttermilk and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
(A wire whip works well for this.)
Pour into a pretty glass bowl or casserole and chill until firm.

title: crock-pot dinner
directions: Drain potatoes; rinse under cold water.
Drain.
Place in crock-pot.
Add beans and liquid.
Cut kielbasa in chunks to press down into mixture.
Leave on low all day.
Serves 3.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Pour off drippings.
Add green chili peppers, enchilada sauce, cream of chicken soup and cream of mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Cook until bubbly.
Spread Doritos in baking dish.
Spoon soup mixture over Doritos.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese melts.

title: southwestern vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef in large Dutch oven. Stir in 5 cups water and remainder of ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 2 hours.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Heat soups, milk and half of the butter in a pan.
Add the rice and heat until the mixture is warm.
Pour this mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Lay the chicken on the top and then add the remaining butter on top of the chicken.
Cook the casserole at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.
Do not cover or open the oven until casserole is done.

title: chicken asparagus rolls
directions: In small bowl, combine garlic powder, rosemary and salt. Sprinkle over flattened chicken.
Lay slice of cheese on each piece.
Top each with 4 asparagus spears.
Fold long edge of chicken over asparagus and roll up.
Secure with wooden toothpick. Sprinkle paprika.
Place seam side down on microwave pie plate. Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Turn each piece and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Cover with wax paper. Microwave 2 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serves 4.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix well the first 3 ingredients. Fold in the whipped topping. Spoon into the baked pie shell and chill for 4 to 6 hours. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In 1-quart casserole, blend soup and milk.
Stir in tuna and eggs. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; stir. Top with chips; bake 5 minutes more or until hot.
Makes 4 cups.

title: the best potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Place down in glass pan with melted butter.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: lela's rolls
directions: In a big bowl dissolve yeast in water and then the sugar. Add dash of salt and oleo (cut in pieces).
Mix in flour with hands until well blended.
Cover and let stand until doubled in size.
Grease cookie sheet pan or muffin pans with oil.
Shape into rolls and let rise until doubled in size.
Bake 20 minutes at 325° or until golden brown.
Makes 30 rolls.

title: fruity chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken.
Toss remaining ingredients with cut up chicken. Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: premium chocolate chip caramel pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/3 cup melted butter.
Mix well.
Press firmly onto bottom and sides of greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in a 350° oven for 5 minutes. Cool.

title: garden chicken pasta salad
directions: Toss all ingredients.
Refrigerate.
You may make this simple salad up to 2 days ahead.
Serve chilled or at room temperature. Makes about 10 cups.

title: shrimp sauce
directions: Mix all and refrigerate.
Serve cold with shrimp.
Makes 1 cup.

title: airways sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Sift flour and salt together and add alternately with water, to first mixture.
Add lemon extract and rind.
Whip egg whites until foamy, add baking powder and continue whipping until stiff peaks are formed.
Fold into egg yolk mixture.
Pour into an ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Invert to cool.
When cool, cut cake from tube and sides of pan.
Frost.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with mixer.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Blend the two mixtures and pour into a greased and floured oblong pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts over mixtures. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fiesta salad
directions: If mixing ahead of time, mix first four ingredients and store in Tupperware bowl; add the other ingredients 30 minutes to an hour before serving.
(That is to prevent Fritos from getting soggy.)

title: salt substitute
directions: Mix together.
Put in decorative salt shakers.
Give to your friends.

title: baked alaska meat loaf
directions: Combine gravy mix, beef, onion and pepper.
Shape into 2-inch high loaf.
Prepare mashed potatoes according to package directions and spread over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Place flour and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Make a nest in the flour and sugar.
Place in saucepan the margarine, Crisco, vanilla, water and chocolate.
Melt these ingredients in the saucepan.

title: basketballs
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter on low heat; mix.
Turn off heat.
Slowly add powdered sugar.
Add Rice Krispies, one cup at a time.
Make into bite-size balls.
Put chocolate chips, Hershey bar and wax in top of double boiler.
Melt together and dip balls into this, using a toothpick, and put on wax paper.
Makes about 100 balls.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and place in bottom of dish.
Slice eggs across and place over asparagus.
Place almonds over eggs.
Mix soup and milk and pour over other.
Crush crackers and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 400°
about 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato pies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: mom's bread pudding
directions: In a large bowl beat eggs.
Add milk, sugar, butter, raisins, cinnamon, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Add bread cubes; stir gently.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: easy no-cook divinity
directions: In small mixer bowl, combine frosting mix, corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water.
Beat on highest speed until stiff peaks form, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to large mixer bowl.
On low speed, blend in 1 pound confectioners sugar gradually.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
When outside of candies feel firm, turn over.
Allow to dry 12 hours or overnight.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen candies.

title: butterhorn cookies
directions: Measure by dipping method or by sifting.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt in by mixing in bowl.
Cut in butter.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir in egg yolks, sour cream and vanilla.
Blend into flour mixture.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: diet rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Separate eggs very carefully (no yolks in whites).
Spray Pam on a Teflon cookie sheet.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff, not dry.
Fold in yolks, cottage cheese and Sugar Twin.
Don't break down egg whites, no more than 1 minute.
Place 1 tablespoonful very carefully on cookie sheet. Place another tablespoon on top of mixture carefully.
Repeat with remaining mixture until you have 6 piles about 2 inches high.
Bake about 1 hour.
Rolls should resemble delecation rolls.
Better cold as hamburger buns.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked ham
directions: Score ham.
Put 1/4 cup water in roaster; pour 1/2 bottle Coca-Cola over ham.
When ham is half done, pour remainder of Coca-Cola.
Baste several times during baking.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes per pound.
Remove cover the last 10 minutes.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Lightly beat 1 egg white.
Add pecan halves; mix thoroughly with spoon until all pecans are coated.
Mix the sugar, cinnamon and salt together.
Sprinkle over pecan halves; mix thoroughly. Pour onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 30 minutes.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Blend together.
Freeze in ice cube trays (about seven trays). Place frozen cubes in punch bowl and pour 1 liter bottle of 7-Up to each 3 trays.

title: pasta fagoili(italian macaroni and bean soup)
directions: Put oil in 1-quart saucepan.
Add enough garlic powder to generously cover oil.
Heat on low until you can smell the garlic, watching not to burn garlic.
Take off heat and add tomato sauce, both cans filled with water, salt, basil, oregano and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add undrained beans and mix well.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Sauce may now be refrigerated.
When ready to eat, heat and mix with cooked macaroni.
Best if sauce is refrigerated at least one day.

title: spareribs
directions: Trim excess fat from ribs.
Place in crock-pot.
Mix soup, vinegar, brown sugar, celery seed, soy sauce and chili powder in bowl.
Pour over ribs.
Cook, covered, on low for 7 to 8 hours.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugars, eggs and pumpkin; add dry ingredients.
Blend in extracts and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry onion and bacon together.
Combine beans, sugar, vinegar and pepper and add cooked bacon and onion plus grease.
Put in oblong baking dish and cook until brown, approximately 3 hours at 350°.
Recipe may be tripled using a gallon of beans.

title: cheese shrimp casserole
directions: In Crisco, cook pepper until transparent.
Add shrimp and cook until light pink.
Stir in flour, salt and oregano.
Add milk gradually.
Cook until thickened.
Add cheese, cut in pieces, and pimentos.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Spread rice in a greased 2-quart casserole or 6 greased individual serving dishes.
Pour sauce over rice.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes, until bubbly. Serve garnished with parsley.

title: spicy meat dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and lightly brown.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add cream cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Serve with Doritos.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar.
Pour over other ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.

title: ozelma's cheesy vegetable chowder
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large pot.
Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in corn. Remove from heat.
Melt margarine in heavy saucepan over low heat. Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute.
Gradually add milk and cook until thick.
Stir in remaining ingredients until cheese melts.
Slowly add cheese mixture to vegetables.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Halve pineapple chunks and orange sections.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans before serving.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fry bacon.
Drain.
Fry onions in bacon fat.
Add sugar, vinegar, mustard and garlic salt.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and mushroom casserole
directions: Salt and pepper chicken lightly.
Lay in flat baking dish or pan.
Pour mushrooms over chicken.
Sprinkle parsley heavily over chicken.
Mix together soup, mushroom juice and sherry.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.
Should be kept moist.
Baste occasionally.
Good served over rice.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix pineapple and Jell-O in pan.
Over medium heat let come to a bubbling stage.
Take off stove.
Let cool good.
Mix buttermilk and Cool Whip good, until thickens some.
Add pineapple mixture and nuts to Cool Whip mixture.
Put in refrigerator to cool or congeal.
Makes a big bowl.
Can be cut in squares if you desired. Can use pineapple, unsweetened, if you like.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place in baking dish or pan.
Mix 1 box of Jiffy corn bread by directions and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until corn bread is done.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients real good with your hands and make into small balls.
Then mix chocolate chips and wax; melt in double boiler and dip the balls into the mixture with toothpicks. Let dry on wax paper.

title: sourdough bread and biscuits(makes 2 dozen biscuits)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Let stand 5 minutes. Combine flour and sugar in a medium size non-metal bowl; mix well. Gradually stir in yeast mixture. Cover loosely with plastic wrap or cheesecloth and let stand in a warm place (80° to 85°) for 10 to
12 hours. Yield: about 2 1/2 cups.

title: snack brownies
directions: Mix and pour in square greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, condensed milk,
red
food
coloring, milk, 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Mix
cup
sugar and peaches, then add this mixture to first ingredients.
Mix and freeze.
Makes one gallon.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cover bottom of Dutch oven with olive oil.
Saute first 4 ingredients until limp.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring often as not to burn.
Add water slowly with seasonings to taste.
Lower heat and simmer until you are ready to add chicken. Wash chicken pieces and season to taste.
Brown both sides of pieces.
When all pieces are brown, pour sauce on top and cook 30 minutes on medium heat.
To this mixture add boiled spaghetti.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble bread
and
bacon together.
Cut up onion, bell pepper and tomatoes very fine.
Add
to
corn bread and bacon, mix well. Add mayonnaise
and stir until moist.
Chill before serving.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain. Add melted butter, vanilla and eggs; beat well. Combine baking powder, sugar and flour, then blend together with wet ingredients until smooth using blender, food processor or beaters. Spoon into buttered casserole. Do not fill more than half full as it rises. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. If you double recipe, you will need to cook 1 hour or more. Better cooked in shallow dish.

title: crock pot corn
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: fruit cocktail bars
directions: Beat sugar and eggs well.
Add fruit cocktail and juice, flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Spread in a greased and floured 15 x 18-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Spread glaze on while bars are warm.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg; mix well.
Stir together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a greased 8 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dum dum salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
When cool, dip into powdered sugar.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in 2 cups hot water and let cool.
Mix remaining ingredients together with cool gelatin; mold and chill.

title: crispy chicken with honey sauce
directions: Combine mayonnaise, honey, mustard, sesame oil and ginger (optional); stir well.
Remove 1/2 cup mayonnaise mixture, reserving remaining mixture for dipping.

title: delicious crock-pot pork barbecue
directions: Place sliced onions and cloves in the crock-pot.
Salt and pepper pork roast to taste and place in cooker; add water.
Cook on high for 1 hour, then lower the heat and cook on low for 8 hours (or cook on high for 4 to 5 hours).
Remove meat from cooker when done, debone and tear apart into strands.
Discard the water, onion and cloves.
Place the shredded meat back into the cooker and add the bottle of barbecue sauce.
Cook for 45 minutes more, then serve.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: Put jello and sugar in bowl.
Pour 1 cup of boiling water into jello and stir until dissolved.
Put cream cheese in 1/2 cup boiling water and beat until smooth.
Pour into jello and add lemon juice, apple and pecans.
Mix and pour into small molds or square container.
Stir and put in refrigerator for several hours until firm.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: demon chow
directions: Grind onions, hot peppers and green bell peppers together. Add salad mustard and white vinegar.
Mix all together.
Place into jars.
(Does not need to be sealed.)

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Pour into unbaked
pie	shell and bake until done.
Top with meringue if desired;
use powdered sugar instead of sugar in meringue.

title: italian salad
directions: Mix all together.
Let set overnight.
You can use any kind of cheeses, vegetables, cold cuts in any amounts to suit your taste. But you must let the salad set overnight to let everything blend together.

title: fish fillets in wine sauce
directions: Skin fillets.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place fillets in a single layer in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Arrange tomatoes over top of fillets.
Blend flour into melted butter in small saucepan.
Add milk gradually and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in wine and basil.
Pour sauce over top of tomatoes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan or casserole dish.
Cook broccoli; put on bottom of pan.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and chicken broth. Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Cover with slices of Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: holiday pie
directions: Heat butter, brown sugar and nuts in saucepan until butter is melted. Spread in bottom of pie shell. Bake at 450° for 5 minutes. Cool.

title: broccoli and garlic pasta
directions: Prepare linguini according to package.
Over medium heat, cook broccoli and garlic in hot oil for 2 minutes.
Add broth and tomatoes, bring to a boil and cook 6 minutes.
Drain pasta, place in bowl with broccoli mixture, top with red pepper flakes and cheese.

title: seven layer magic bars(makes 24 to 36 bars)
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass). In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter in oven. Sprinkle crumbs over butter. Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs. Top with remaining ingredients in order listed; press down firmly. Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool. Chill, if desired. Cut into bars. Store, covered, at room temperature.

title: chuck beef steak
directions: Place steak in baking dish.
Brush with butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place onion slices on top.
Place lemon slices on top of onion slices.
Mix catsup, water and Worcestershire sauce together.
Pour mixture over steak.
Cook in covered dish at 350° for 2 hours.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve on crackers. Makes a large bowl full.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Slice angel food cake in 1/2-inch slices and lay in pan (9 x 13-inch) to make crust.
Pour cooled lemon pudding over the cake. Whip the cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Whip the Dream Whip according to directions.
Fold in the Dream Whip with the cream cheese mixture and put on top of lemon pudding.
Set in refrigerator for at least 6 hours.

title: lemon bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°, grease and flour 10 inch bundt pan. Blend all ingredients in a large bowl; beat 3 minutes at high speed. Scrape bowl often. Bake at 350° for 45 - 55 minutes, or until it springs back when touched lightly in center. Cool right side up for 25 minutes. Remove from pan. Serve with your favorite topping.

title: beef and noodle goulash
directions: Fry hamburg and onion in shortening until brown.
Drain off excess grease.
Add tomatoes and corn.
Cook noodles while hamburg is browning.
Drain noodles and add to hamburg mixture.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Stir and layer cheese over top of mixture.
Cover and allow cheese to melt.
Ready to serve.

title: potato soup
directions: Fry bacon; drain.
Add potatoes, celery and carrots to drippings.
Salt, pepper and water to cover.
Cook 15 minutes or until tender.
Combine flour and small amounts of milk until smooth.
Add to mixture and add rest of milk.
Cook until it begins to boil, over medium heat.

title: coconut lemon squares
directions: Line cookies on bottom and sides of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix the pudding according to package directions, then pour over the cookies in the pan.
Whip up the egg whites until stiff and fluffy.
Pour over the filling and bake 5 to 7 minutes until meringue is nice and golden.
Or you can use whipped cream when pudding cools.

title: beef nachos
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat and add picante sauce.
Let Velveeta melt in microwave, then add to beef and picante sauce. Serve over tortilla chips.

title: lemon angel bars
directions: Mix cake mix and pie filling together and pour into a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: norwegian pancakes(international dish)
directions: Whip the sour cream with the sugar. Add well beaten eggs and flour to make batter slightly thickened. Beat well. Bake in small cakes on griddle.

title: 7-layer mexican dip
directions: Using a large platter, layer the ingredients (in order or change up, if you like).
Serve with corn tortilla chips.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can fried onion rings.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer. Makes 6 servings.

title: puffs for chicken salad
directions: Melt butter in water.
Add flour and salt all at once and stir vigorously.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture forms ball that doesn't separate.

title: lane cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Dry ingredients should be mixed together and then added alternately to butter mixture with milk.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites and fold into batter.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake until cake springs back to touch.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Stew 4 whole chicken breasts in at least 4 cups lightly salted water until done.
Take breasts out, reserving broth.
Slice in serving pieces when cool.
Partially cook 2 packages frozen broccoli spears.
Drain and put into bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased casserole.
Layer chicken on top and cover with sauce.
Make the sauce the same as if you were making white sauce.

title: one bowl apple cake
directions: Stir sugar into the apples; let stand until sugar dissolves. Add the egg; beat into the mixture.
Mix the flour, cinnamon, soda and chopped nuts; mix well.
Pour into an 8-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
While cake is baking, make sauce.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except Kisses.
Preheat oven to 350°. Place on cookie sheet about 1 teaspoon at a time.
Cook about 8 minutes or until top of cookie begins to crack.
Remove from oven and place a Kiss on top.
Let cool.

title: granola bars
directions: Heat oven to 350. Coat a 9 by 13 inch pan with nonstick cooking spray and set it aside.

Melt the butter in a large pot over low heat. Remove the pot from the heat and whisk in the sugar, honey, flour, vanilla extract and cinnamon. Add the remaining ingredients and mix well. Transfer the mixture to the baking pan. Using the sheet of waxed paper and the palms of your hands, press he granola firmly into the pan, packing it to a flat and end even thickness. Bake for 20 minutes, until golden brown. Allow the granola to cool 1 hour in the pan, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely before cutting into bars. Makes 16-24 rectangular bars and a quick breakfast on the go!

title: peanut sauce
directions: 1. Mix ingredients in a double boiler or a low fire.
2. Simmer slowly, stirring until sauce is smooth, neither runny or sticky.

title: copper pennies - carrot salad
directions: Heat carrots, then drain.
Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients together.
After doing this, add carrots.
Stir, then refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls out on cookie sheet, pinching seams together.
Bake according to directions.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing.
Spread over cooled crust.
Spread vegetables over cream cheese layer.
Grate 1 or 2 carrots.
Spread some over top of vegetables to resemble cheese.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and
sugar;
add
eggs
one at a time. Add flour, baking powder and milk alternately.	Add flavoring. Bake at 325° for 70 minutes in tube pan.

title: zucchini spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until tender. Add zucchini and cook until transparent. Add remaining ingredients and simmer about 10 minutes. Serve over hot spaghetti.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Stir peanuts, sugar, syrup and water together in a heavy skillet.
Start cooking; start stirring continuously when peanuts begin to pop.
Cook approximately 18 minutes on high heat.
Remove from heat and stir in soda, butter and vanilla.
Pour immediately onto buttered cookie sheet and spread thin.
Break into pieces when hard.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Add cheese and soup to rice while hot; add onions, celery and broccoli.
Mix well. Place in casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: dill casserole bread
directions: Place cottage cheese in warm bowl; add yeast-water, egg and soft butter.
Combine all dry ingredients and gradually add; beat well.
Cover with clean cloth; let rise until doubled.
Punch down and put in 2 small, greased loaf pans.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
While warm, brush with butter and salt.

title: creamy chicken biscuit casserole
directions: Roll chicken in mixture of flour, salt, pepper and paprika. Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chicken, skin side down. Bake in a 400° oven for 40 minutes.
Turn chicken pieces.
Combine soup, milk and dill seed; pour over chicken.
Place biscuits on top of chicken.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until biscuits are golden brown.
Serve hot.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: asparagus casserole (great for easter)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter; blend in flour and gradually stir in milk.
Bring to boil, stirring until mixture thickens.
Fold in eggs, asparagus, salt and pepper.
Pour into buttered baking dish; sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake for 15 minutes.
Yields 4 side servings or 2 main dish servings.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, Accent, Worcestershire and onions together. Shape into ball.
Roll in grated ham and refrigerate.

title: cranberry ripple cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients and stir, mixing in a large bowl. Beat butter or margarine for 30 seconds, adding sugar and extract and beating until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour and sour cream alternately, beating until smooth.
Spread one-half of batter in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Spoon 1/2 of cranberry sauce (without touching the sides of the pan).
Add remainder of the batter; top with the remaining cranberry sauce. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: italian dressing
directions: Mix all together in medium bowl.
Chill and serve.
May be transferred to 1/2-pint clean jar.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix in order given and refrigerate.

title: garlic grits
directions: Break 2 eggs in 8-ounce cup.
Add milk until full.
Cook grits.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole and cover.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Uncover. Sprinkle with grated sharp Cheddar cheese and paprika.
Bake uncovered for 20 additional minutes.

title: highland stew
directions: Dredge meat in flour.
Cut sausages in half.

title: sausage dressing
directions: Make sausage into cakes and fry.
Remove from grease.
Chop onion and green pepper.
Saute in grease.
Add bread crumbs, chicken broth and water.
Stir well.
Break sausage into small pieces and add to mixture.
Make sure dressing is good and wet. Add more water if needed.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place mixture in refrigerator overnight.
Shape into cookies and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: daisy's egg pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and flour.
Beat until mixed thoroughly. Add milk, cream and nutmeg.
Bake in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell at 350° until done, about 1 hour.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour 1 cup of batter through funnel into hot oil, making a circular motion.
Turn when golden brown. Remove to paper towels.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: oriental spaghetti salad
directions: Heat vegetable oil, sesame oil and sesame seed on medium heat until seed turn brown.
Remove from heat.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Serve chilled.

title: mom's secret icing
directions: Mix flour and milk in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Let get cold.
In a deep bowl, put sugar, shortening and vanilla.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening and baking powder.
Beat egg, vinegar and water.

title: pea salad
directions: Marinate in layers for 4 to 5 hours.
Toss.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: raisin applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Mix in egg. Combine 1 1/2 cups flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in applesauce and lemon rind.
Dredge the raisins and pecans in 1/2 cup flour.
Stir to coat well.
Fold into batter.

title: carrot drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with carrots.
Add lemon and vanilla extracts.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Frost with Orange Frosting.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Pour into crust. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Mix small amount of sour cream with sugar and vanilla.
Pour over cheesecake.
Bake 5 additional minutes.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and pour melted margarine over.
Top with Velveeta.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well.
Serve with strawberries, bananas, apples or pineapple, etc.

title: coconut supreme cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in 8 x 12-inch pan. While hot, mix cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour on cake, then punch holes in the cake so mixture will run into cake. Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Top with liberal amount of Cool Whip and shredded coconut before serving.

title: lemon torte
directions: Mix all together and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake exactly 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool.

title: homemade granola
directions: In large bowl, stir together oats, sugar, wheat germ, bran, seeds, coconut and nuts.
Heat oil, honey and vanilla until it bubbles.
Throughly mix liquids with oat mixture until blended well.
Spread mixture onto large, rimmed baking sheet.
Bake at 325°, stirring every 10 minutes, until lightly browned.
Note:
30 minutes yields a slightly moist granola.
Bake longer for a crunchy granola.
Remove from oven and stir several times while cooling to avoid clumping.
Add raisins or dried fruit when completely cool. Store in airtight container after cooled.
Makes approximately 8 cups.

title: hamburger and corn casserole
directions: Cook noodles in a large amount of boiling, salted water for 10 to 12 minutes or just until tender; drain. Brown meat and onion until tender. Drain off fat. Stir in soup, corn, sour cream, milk, pimiento, salt and pepper. Mix well. Stir in cooked noodles. Place in a casserole dish. Toss bread crumbs with melted butter. Top and bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 50 minutes or until heated through.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil together for 2 1/2 minutes the sugar, milk and margarine. Remove from heat; add peanut butter and stir until smooth.
Then add oatmeal.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper and cool.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Put serving size pieces of chicken breast in oven-proof dish; season.
Add a few pats of butter or oleo.
Add part of a bottle Catalina dressing (as desired) and cranberry sauce.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.
Serve with stuffing, rice or potatoes.
Also good with cube steak.

title: chewies
directions: Melt butter; add rest of ingredients.
Mix and bake in greased jelly roll pan or broiler pan at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes (will not look done).
Cool completely before cutting.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and season to taste.
May want to add salt, pepper or Creole seasoning.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar together in large bowl and set aside.
Beat eggs in a bowl until thick with peaks.
Add and blend in milk and butter, then add dry ingredients and beat until smooth.
Makes 5 dozen at about 3 inches each.

title: easy chocolate icing
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa until smooth.
Add milk, butter and vanilla.
Cook on medium heat for 2 minutes after it boils.
Let cool and beat until creamy.
Will frost a 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Chop cherries, pineapple and pecans. Put marshmallows in double boiler and melt, then add condensed milk and mix well.
Remove from heat; add to chopped mixture.
Mix well.
Make into loaves and wrap in foil.
Put in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: creamy potato puff
directions: Combine softened cheese with potatoes; mix until well blended. Add remaining ingredients and place in 1 1/2-quart greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: coconut squares
directions: Put butter in large bowl of electric mixer; add 1/2 cup brown sugar and beat
until light and fluffy.
Add 1 cup flour and mix well.
Pat into
greased
13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake in 375° oven 12 minutes.

title: apricot wraps
directions: Fold each apricot around an almond.
Cut bacon strips into thirds.
Wrap a strip around each apricot and secure with toothpick.
Place on baking sheet and bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes or until bacon is crisp, turning once.
Meanwhile, combine jelly and soy sauce in pan and cook, stirring, until warmed and smooth.
Remove bacon wrapped apricots and drain with paper towels.
Serve with warm sauce for dipping.

title: mozzarella chicken
directions: Wash package of chicken breast fillets.
Dip in egg.
Roll in Italian seasoned breadcrumbs.
Fry in olive oil 10 to 15 minutes on each side.

title: my favorite banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add bananas.
Add sour milk and eggs. Add dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan or miniature pans.
If using 1 loaf pan, bake at 350° or until done. If using smaller pans, bake about 45 minutes and loaf pan about 1 hour.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook roast or stew meat; save broth. Cook onion and potatoes until tender. Cut roast in bite size pieces and put in broth. Add potatoes and onion. Add the 4 cans of vegetables and the tomatoes. Salt and pepper to taste.
Heat all together for about 10 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Dissolve soda in sour milk.
Combine flour, spices and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add chopped prunes and nuts. Beat until smooth.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egg casserole
directions: Place the crumbled sausage in a 9 x 13 pan.
Then add the cubed bread.
Beat the eggs and add the salt, dry mustard, and milk. Pour over the sausage and bread.
Top with cheese and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour uncovered at 325°.

title: quick pita nachos
directions: Spread the pita with the salsa.
Top with the cheese slices; sprinkle with the oregano and paprika.
Place on aluminum foil; bake at 400° until hot and cheese is melted.
Serves 2, cut into quarters.

title: toeffegi(sandwich spread)
directions: Blend together kidney beans, olives, lemon juice, salt, garlic powder and sesame seed.
In a separate bowl mix onion powder, tahini and tofu.
Mix these two together.

title: apple pan dowdy
directions: Mix brown sugar, 1/4 cup flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt, vinegar and water together; boil for 2 minutes.

title: bread and butter pudding
directions: Line bottom of a greased dish with raisins.
Cut bread in 3 strips, crosswise.
Dip in melted butter, in skillet or frypan brown lightly.
Then arrange on top of raisins in dish.
Beat the remaining ingredients, pour over bread and raisins.
Set dish in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.

title: kolacky
directions: Mix oleo, flour, sour cream and salt to make dough. Wrap in foil. Place in refrigerator for 1 hour. Roll out dough a little at a time and cut into small squares. Fill center with solo filling, fold over and pinch dough in center. Place on slightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375 degrees until browned.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat all ingredients together except the corn.
Add the corn. Bake in a 2-quart deep bowl at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fried rice and meat
directions: Place
rice,
ham, pork, cooked chicken or luncheon meat and 1/2 small onion in large frying pan over medium heat.
Cook until onion
is tender.
Add soy sauce.
Cook 10 minutes.
Beat egg well.
Add
to
cooked
rice mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings, about 3/4 cup each.

title: chicken delight
directions: Cook chicken, celery, onion, salt and pepper until done. Remove chicken from bone and save broth; strain and keep celery and onion.
Melt butter and pour over Pepperidge Farm dressing; mix well.

Put 1/2 dressing in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and add in layers chicken, onion, celery, celery soup and chicken broth. Pour broth slowly (you may need to make holes for it to soak in). Cover with rest of dressing and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until brown on top.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix well,
shape into balls and place on aluminum foil. Chill and serve on
crackers.

title: spareribs and sauerkraut
directions: Season ribs with salt and pepper.
Brown over medium heat in heavy skillet.
Add small amount of water; cover and cook slowly for 1 hour.
Empty sauerkraut into kettle.
Top with ribs, 3 tablespoons fat and 1/4 cup water.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.

title: sweet & sour dressing
directions: Blend first three ingredients in a blender.
Add next four ingredients and pour in oil slowly, blending all together. Refrigerate and pour over favorite salads.

title: chocolate dream dessert
directions: Melt oleo; add flour and nuts.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; let cool.

title: pa. pumpkin cookies
directions: Sift flour and measure 2 cups, sift again with salt and cinnamon and set aside.

title: green wonder salad
directions: Drain vegetables; discard liquid.
Slice chestnuts thin; chop celery and onions.
Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: microwave almond toffee
directions: Microwave butter and sugar in glass bowl on High for 1 minute. Beat until smooth.
Microwave 4 minutes, then stir in 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Microwave another 2 minutes or until thick.
Beat with wire whisk.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan lined with buttered foil.
Sprinkle chocolate chips.
Let stand covered for 4 minutes. Spread chips and sprinkle with 1/2 cup nuts.
Let sit until chocolate is firm.
Peel off foil and break into pieces.
Store in fridge.

title: divinity(never fail)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cook until syrup forms hair.
Beat egg whites.
Pour syrup over egg whites in small stream.
Pour syrup in 7 times, cooking syrup between pouring.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: apricot sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 1 to 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish with butter flavor Crisco.
Arrange potatoes in oven casserole dish.

title: chicken
directions: Around each half of chicken breast, wrap a piece of bacon. In the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch casserole, cut pieces of dried beef.
Place chicken on top.
Mix soup and sour cream together; put on top of chicken.
Cover the dish all of cooking time.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Reduce to 300° for 1 more hour.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all
ingredients
and spread on slices of bread for sandwiches or serve on lettuce.

title: dill vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; then refrigerate until ready to use.

title: watergate dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: autumn pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into small loaf pans and bake at 350° until knife comes out clean from center.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients, except broth and flour, in a large bowl.
Mix the broth (undiluted) and the flour until there are no lumps.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour the thick broth over meat and vegetables and mix thoroughly.
Place mixture in a heavy covered pan.
Bake at 250° for at least 8 hours.

title: hershey pie
directions: Melt candy bars in double boiler; remove from heat and let cool 3 to 4 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip and pour mixture into pie crust. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery in small amount of oil until tender (not brown).
Drain.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients. Bake in casserole 25 minutes at 350°.

title: mrs. black's brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together.
Cool.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar. Combine chocolate and egg mixture, then add vanilla and salt. Add flour and coconut. Mix thoroughly. Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar; then add eggs.
Mix well.
Sift flour, cinnamon, soda and baking powder.
Add to mixture.
Fold in carrots.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans for 30 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: hidden valley ranch pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese, green onions and Hidden Valley dressing mix until blended.
Spread 1/4 of mixture on each tortilla.
Drain vegetables by blotting on paper towel.
Sprinkle equal amounts of vegetables on cream cheese mixture.
Roll tortillas tightly. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Discard ends.

title: cranberry - cherry pie
directions: Combine all, but butter and milk; let stand 15 minutes.

title: apple casserole
directions: Cook butter, cornstarch, sugar and water until thick. Add vanilla and cinnamon. Pour over apples. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: rosettes
directions: Sift flour before measuring.
Mix all the other ingredients together and then stir in slowly the flour.
Beat until smooth. Heat oil to 350°.
Heat iron in oil and pat on paper towel.
Makes 36 tarts.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, oil and nuts (if used).
Beat at low speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake in preheated oven at 375°
for 6 to 7 minutes. Grease or spray cookie sheet with nonstick spray.
Cool on cookie sheet 1 minute.
Remove to cooling rack.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen. May dust with confectioners sugar if desired.

title: holubtsi(stuffed cabbage)
directions: Place cabbage in large pot of boiling, salted water.
Remove leaves, 1 at a time, as they come off and are still crisp. Let cool in drainer.
Cut away enough of thick vein to make easy to roll.
Yields about 20 leaves.

title: candied cherry snaps
directions: Cream butter, adding confectioners sugar gradually.
Blend in egg and vanilla; add flour.
Mix well; stir in pecans and cherries.
Chill dough for 1 hour; divide into thirds.
Shape into 12-inch long rolls; wrap in waxed paper.
Chill for at least 3 hours or place in freezer for 2 hours.
Cut into 1/8-inch thick slices; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 13 to 15 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
