title: piccalilli
directions: Wash tomatoes and peppers.
Peel onions:
cut cabbage in quarters.
Put vegetables through food chopper.
Sprinkle alternate layers of vegetables with salt.
Cover:
let stand overnight.

title: pauline's rice(from pauline youtsos)
directions: Melt butter in a pan.
Add the rice and stir over low heat until the rice is browned.
(Be careful not to burn the butter.) Add the chicken broth after it has been heated to the boiling point.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes.
Remove from heat and put a double layer of paper towels over the pan, under the lid.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: joyce's good coney sauce
directions: *It calls for 2 tablespoons but start with 1 and add to taste.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Stir first 8 ingredients until well mixed.
Add cheese.
Mix to separate particles of cheese.
Combine buttermilk, melted butter and egg and beat well.
Add to dry ingredients in just a few swift strokes, no more than 20 seconds.
Mix will be lumpy.
Fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full.
Cook about 20 to 30 minutes in preheated 350° oven or until brown on top.

title: zucchini cheese muffins
directions: Stir together all dry ingredients and the cheese.
In a separate bowl beat together eggs, butter and milk.
Stir in zucchini.
Add liquid ingredients to the dry flour mixture and stir just enough to moisten.
Spoon into well-greased muffin cups. Bake at 400° for 20 to 22 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: chocolate "pig-out"
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, butter and nuts.
Press 1/2 to 3/4 of the mixture into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Bake 6 minutes.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Place mushrooms in glass bowl; set aside.
Mix oil, water, garlic, salt and pepper in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over mushrooms.
Cover.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Add the parsley and pepper, stirring to blend.
Yield:
10 appetizer servings.
(Recipe may be doubled.)

title: apple dessert
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan or Pyrex dish.
Layer apples on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle apples with cinnamon.
Crumble cake mix over apples.
Spread pecans over top of cake mix.
Drizzle melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: fantastic fruit salad(winter or summer)
directions: Slice your fruits into bite size chunks.
Layer your fruits. Mix your fruit salad.
Lightly sprinkle sugar on your fruit salad. Mix again.
Cover your fruit salad with plastic wrap.
Chill in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Serve.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Cut shortening in the dry ingredients.
Pour the yeast into the buttermilk before pouring it into the flour mixture.
Mix with a stiff spoon.
Roll dough on a floured surface to desired thickness; cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake in conventional oven at 425°.
Keeps well in refrigerator for several days in covered container.

title: salmon hot dish
directions: Brown celery and onions in melted shortening.
Stir in flour and salt. Add soup and milk. Cook until it thickens.
Add salmon and lemon juice.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Make biscuits and place on salmon mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until brown.
(May use tuna instead of salmon.)

title: marinated carrots
directions: Bring carrots to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Drain; cool.
Add salt, pepper and mustard.
Beat in a little oil to blend with mustard.
Add remaining oil, sugar, vinegar and soup.
Beat again to blend.
Stir in the pepper and onion.
Cover tightly and chill overnight.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: mocha torte
directions: Melt marshmallows in coffee, over low heat.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Cut pound cake slices into thirds and use to line sides and bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Reserve scraps for middle of torte.
Spoon half the filling into the lined pan. Sprinkle with toasted almonds.
Add a layer of cake fingers.
Spoon in remaining filling and chill several hours or overnight.
If desired, trim with rosettes of additional whipped cream and drizzle with chocolate sauce and sprinkle with some more almonds.

title: sweet and sour potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until soft. Mix all ingredients and let sit for 1 hour. Leave potatoes warm and pour liquid over potatoes and refrigerate 24 hours before eating.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Mix and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Or 20 minutes in microwave.

title: strawberry-banana salad
directions: Combine the jello and boiling water in a medium mixing bowl until it is completely dissolved.
Mash the banana well in a small mixing bowl.
Add all the other ingredients and stir until blended.
Pour into a mold and refrigerate 1 hour or until firm.

title: **honey cookies
directions: Cream shortening, adding sugar gradually.
Add unbeaten egg, beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and extract.
Fill cookie press.
Form cookies on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen small cookies.

title: fruit ambrosia
directions: Mix yogurt and orange juice in a large bowl.
Add melon and grapes and toss gently to mix and coat.
Spoon into individual dessert dishes and serve or cover and chill for up to 2 hours.

title: cheddar raisin muffins
directions: Sift the flour with baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter until particles are small.
Stir in cheese.
Combine egg and milk. Add to dry mixture, stirring only until flour is moistened.
Fold in raisins.
Spoon into well-greased muffin tins.
Fill about 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Prick potatoes once.
Bake potatoes on High power for 5 to 6 minutes.
Turn over and bake 5 to 6 minutes more.
While still hot, slice potatoes lengthwise.
Scoop out insides, saving shells. Whip together potatoes, margarine, Cheddar cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Gradually blend in milk.
Spoon potato mixture back into shells.
Return to oven for 5 more minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar slowly.
Add baking powder and crumbled crackers.
Mix real well.
Fold in nuts.

title: "hardee" biscuits
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk.
Top with melted butter before baking.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.
Makes 9 "Hardees" large biscuits or 12 regular size.

title: mock champagne
directions: In a
punch
bowl,
put cubes of ice or molded block of ice made
with either water or frozen Sprite.
Add a pink rose when semi
frozen.
Mix	equal
amounts	of
Sprite
and apple juice. Pour
over ice and let stand for a few minutes.
Serve cold.

title: ice cream
directions: Fill 1 gallon size zip-type plastic bag half full of ice and add the salt.
In the 1 pint size zip-type bag put the sugar, milk and vanilla.
Seal the small bag and place it into the big bag and seal it.
Put the bags into a 2 or 3 pound coffee can and put the lid on.
Roll the can on the floor for 10 minutes.
Rinse off the top of the small bag, open carefully and enjoy!

title: brunswick stew
directions: Pour all the ingredients in a pot and let it simmer for about an hour.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Remove yolks; save egg whites.
Mash yolks until free of lumps.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until smooth.
Refill egg whites with egg yolk mixture.
Garnish tops, if desired, with bits of pimiento stuffed or black olives.
Yields 12 deviled egg halves; makes 6 servings.

title: cheese danish
directions: Cream cheese, egg yolk, and sugar.
Spread one package of rolls on a greased 9 x 13 pan.
Spread cream cheese mixture on top.
Add on the remaining rolls on top.
Beat egg white.
Spread on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: aunt nena's chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Stir together flour and baking soda.

title: chilled tomato soup
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients in a large pitcher, stirring well; chill 4 to 6 hours.

title: chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°; prepare stuffing mix according to package directions.
Add vegetables with seasoning packet. Combine soup, milk and parsley; set aside.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cocoa in medium saucepan.
Add 1/2 cup milk and mix well.
Add remaining 1 1/2 cups milk and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to thicken.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and margarine.
Serve with plain cake or hot buttered biscuits.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage. Add salt and green pepper.
Let stand for 1/2 hour.
Squeeze out cabbage.
Simmer the sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and vinegar for 15 minutes.
Let cool and put on cabbage.
Freeze.

title: grandma grapes
directions: Whip cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Fold in grapes.
Chill 1 hour.
Very good.

title: fruit soup (base)
directions: Cook the tapioca, sugar and water together as directed on the box.
Cool the tapioca base.
Fold in thawed orange juice and thawed frozen strawberries.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Fold in any fruit that is in season (grapes, melons, strawberries, pineapple or bananas).
This is great served with brunch.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix apples, 5 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon together and set aside.
Beat remaining ingredients together until smooth.
Put into a greased and floured tube pan, layering batter then apples and ending with apples on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours.
You can substitute fresh peaches for apples if desired.

title: sunday night sandwiches
directions: Brush insides of rolls with butter.
Mix mustard, poppy seed and onions	in
a
bowl.
Spread on rolls.	Place ham and cheese on rolls.
Place
rolls
in roll pan.
Bake, wrapped in foil at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: teamonade
directions: Bring 8 cups water to a boil; pour over tea bags.
Cover; let stand 20 minutes.
Discard tea bags.
Add sugar; stir well and set aside.
Combine lemonade concentrate and 6 1/2 cups water in a large pitcher; stir well.
Add tea, stirring well.
Chill.
Serve over ice.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: charlotte russe pie
directions: Put in double boiler milk, gelatine, 2 egg yolks, sugar and salt.
Cook until thick (not too thick).
Let stand until almost cold.
Next, whip the cream and mix with custard.
Then beat the 2 egg whites and fold this all together.
Roll graham crackers and put in square pan or pie tins.
Pour custard on top of graham cracker crumbs, then sprinkle top with graham cracker crumbs.
Cool in refrigerator until serving time.

title: baked fish
directions: Cut fish in portions.
Roll in flour.
Place fish in single layers in well-greased dish.

title: barbecue sauce for grilled hamburgers
directions: Combine all ingredients in
small saucepan.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Brush on hamburgers as they are grilled.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Add vinegar to milk. Combine at once with flour mixture.
Makes 3 singles or 2 large. If you only want one crust, freeze the remainder in a circular shape.

title: candy apple walnut pie
directions: In a large bowl, toss together apples, walnuts, cinnamon candies, 1/3 cup sugar and flour.
Pour into one frozen pie crust. Break or crumble second pie crust into very small pieces.
Toss with remaining 2 tablespoons sugar; sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° on a cookie sheet for 55 to 60 minutes or until candies melt and bubble up through the crumbled crust.
Cool completely before serving.

title: mini pizza
directions: Cover the top of the bread with pizza sauce.
Spread small pieces of cheese on top of sauce.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: frank-potato chowder
directions: Combine potatoes, vegetables, onions, parsley, bouillon cubes and salt in saucepan.
Add 1 cup water and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add hot dogs.
Blend flour, pepper and milk.
Stir into vegetable mixture and bring to a boil.
Cook for a few minutes.
Add butter and stir until it thickens.

title: turkey burger balls
directions: Chop green pepper and onion to taste.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Shape into balls and brown. Add one can of cream of chicken, celery or mushroom soup.
Cook until done, about 1 hour.

title: first down dip
directions: Combine process cheese spread and sour cream in pan; stir over low heat until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve warm with vegetable dippers, chips or bread sticks.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: cranberry holiday punch
directions: Make 1 quart of ginger ale into beverage cubes.
Chill remaining soft drinks.
When ready to serve, pour cranberry juice and carbonated beverages into punch bowl.
Float beverage cubes. Garnish with orange slices.
Yields 24 punch size cups.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator for 3 hours before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook noodles in boiling, salted water for 25 minutes or until tender, stirring frequently.
Drain. Arrange in shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Alternate layers of cooked noodles, meat, Ricotta, Mozzarella, spaghetti sauce and grated cheese.
Bake in preheated oven for approximately 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked bean medley
directions: Microwave butter in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole at High (100%), 30 seconds or until melted.
Stir in green pepper.
Cook, covered at High, 2 minutes or until pepper is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except bacon.
Cook, covered, at High for 4 minutes or until boiling.
Cook, uncovered, at Medium (50%) for 8 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.
Sprinkle bacon over top.

title: ants on a log
directions: Trim celery and cut into 4 inch long stalks.
Spread cream cheese on stalk.
Top each with raisins or dry fruit.

title: taco casserole
directions: Layer nachos, ground beef, green pepper, cottage cheese and sour cream.
Layer Velveeta cheese and taco sauce.
Layer Mozzarella cheese; sprinkle with nacho chips.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: stroganoff for shrimp
directions: Cook chicken breasts (halved) with 4 cups water, the tops from a full stalk of celery and 2 1/2 teaspoons salt for about 30 minutes or until tender.
Remove the chicken.
Cool, skin and cut into chunks.
Reserve broth.

title: seafood salad
directions: Boil macaroni; rinse well.
Add crushed pineapple with juice. Boil sugar, flour, eggs and lemon juice in double boiler.
Pour over macaroni and pineapple mixture.
When cool, add apples.
When ready to serve, add whipping cream and stir (can also use Cool Whip).

title: how to preserve a husband
directions: Be careful in your selection; do not pick too green and take only such as have been reared in good Christian atmosphere.
Some insist on keeping them in a pickle, while others keep them in hot water.
This only makes them sour, hard and sometime bitter.
Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well-sweetened with smiles and flavored with kisses taste.
Then wrap in a mantle of charity.
Keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion and serve with peaches and cream. When prepared this way, they will keep for years.

title: wu wu
directions: Mix in glass over ice.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into buttered baking dish. Place dish into a pan of hot water and bake slowly (250° to 300°) for approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until firm.
Test by inserting knife into center of pudding.
Pudding is done if knife comes out clean.
Serves 4.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Put margarine in skillet and saute onion and celery until soft and clear.
Add the flour and blend with the margarine, then blend in the milk.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add egg yolks, crabmeat, salt, pepper and grated cheese.
Transfer to buttered casserole and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chicken and mushroom pasta
directions: Season chicken with oregano, parsley, basil and garlic salt. Let set for 1/2 hour.
Saute chicken in olive oil.
At same time, cook pasta and, in separate pan, cream of mushroom soup and milk. Drain pasta and combine with chicken and soup in a large casserole dish.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
If desired, saute the sliced mushrooms and add to finished dish.

title: apple dumplins
directions: *These amounts may be increased or decreased according to taste.

title: one pan breakfast
directions: Fry bacon in large skillet.
Remove bacon but keep grease in pan.
Pat out hash browns to cover bottom of pan; sprinkle onion on top and cook until underside of potatoes are browned.
Blend eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with cheese and bacon.
Cover and cook until eggs set (about 10 to 15 minutes).

title: artichoke-cheese dip
directions: Blend all ingredients except French bread together in small baking dish and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve with the French bread for dipping.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in heavy large saucepan and simmer 3 to 4 hours.

title: lentil pea soup
directions: In large saucepan, saute onion and potatoes in oil over medium-high heat for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add the water, peas and lentils and cook over medium to low heat for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook another 20 minutes.
Heart healthy and low-fat.

title: reine de saba
directions: Melt chocolate at low temperature.
Soften butter at room temperature.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks with 1/2 of sugar. Cream butter and remaining sugar; add yolks, then chocolate, then extracts and almonds.
Fold in alternately into creamed mixture, whites and flour until blended, then turn batter into buttered and floured 10-inch spring-form pans.
(Makes 2.)
Bake until firm 1 1/2-inch around edges, center still soft.
Bake approximately 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool until firm.
Serve thin slice with whipped cream.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion and next 5 ingredients in oil in a large skillet 3 minutes or until tender. Stir in tomatoes and next 4 ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cook, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes. Add shrimp; cook 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink. Remove and discard bay leaves; serve over rice.

title: texas bread
directions: This makes 2 loaves.

title: pickled carrots and zucchini
directions: Advance preparation:
In saucepan, mix first 5 ingredients and 1/2 cup water.
Add carrots; cover and simmer until crisp-tender. Add zucchini; return to boiling.
Transfer to bowl.
Cover; chill at least 8 hours.
Makes 3 cups.

title: cathedral cookies(more like candy)
directions: Melt chocolate and oleo over double boiler and add egg.
Set aside.
Mix sugar, nuts and marshmallows in bowl thoroughly and add to chocolate mixture.
Cut 3 pieces of foil 14-inches long and sprinkle coconut on each.
Divide the chocolate-marshmallow mixture into three parts and roll into logs, rolling the coconut onto the surface.
Wrap the foil around the log and refrigerate overnight.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough 1/8 inch thick.
Spread over pizza.
Press with fingers to join slices.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes, until light brown.
Cool on rack.
Mix cheese, sugar and vanilla (beat until smooth) and spread over cool cookie dough.
Arrange fruit over topping.
Heat preserves and drizzle over fruit.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Put layer of graham crackers and pour 1/2 of pudding mix. Then add another layer of graham crackers; pour remaining pudding mix.
Put one more layer of crackers and pour fudge topping on top.
Put in refrigerator.

title: danish kringle
directions: Dissolve
yeast in water.
Mix flour, shortening, sugar and salt
as
pie
crust.
Beat
yolks and add warm milk.
Add yeast, egg
and
milk
to flour mixture and beat well.
Cover. Place
in refrigerator overnight.
In morning, divide dough in 3 parts. Roll
into
thin strips, about 10 inches wide and 20 inches long. Spread
with
beaten
egg whites, layer of brown sugar and fruit. Fold over, lengthwise, and seal edges.
Bake about 20
minutes
in medium
hot
oven about 375°.
Ice with powdered
sugar
frosting while hot.
Spread with chopped nuts or a bit of brown sugar.

title: cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a large mixing bowl. Heat butter, cocoa and Cola to boiling water.
Pour over flour mixture.

title: chicken perigord style
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, melt 6 Tbsp. margarine. Cook chicken breasts until brown, remove from pan and set aside. In drippings, add 2 Tbsp. margarine and cook mushrooms until golden - about 2 minutes.
With slotted spoon, remove mushrooms. Into drippings, add more margarine if needed.
Stir in flour and salt until well blended.
Gradually stir in broth and milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add chicken and mushrooms in pan - reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Goes well with side dish of fettucine alfredo.

title: baked potato topping(reduced fat)
directions: Process all ingredients in a blender on low to medium speed until smooth.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Beat together first 2 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll out with rolling pin.
Cut into desired shapes.
Batter may be colored, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, brown sugar, oil, vanilla, cinnamon and ginger.
Beat all until fluffy.
Stir in 2 cups coarsely shredded zucchini.
Add balance of ingredients. Pour into 2 greased (5 x 9) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: california rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
In large bowl, mix well hot rice, sour cream, cottage cheese, bay leaf and salt.
Spray 2-quart baking dish with cooking spray.
Layer half rice mix in bottom of baking dish, then half of chilies, half of cheese; repeat layer. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for approximately 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: west texas fried venison
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper and coat the venison pieces.
Heat bacon fat in skillet and brown venison on both sides.
Add celery and onions and continue browning.
Add Worcestershire sauce and tomatoes and cook, covered, 1 to 2 hours or until venison is tender.
Cook small bag of egg noodles; drain and place in serving dish.
Put venison mixture on top and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit cocktail, mandarin oranges, pineapple, marshmallows and nuts together. Fold in whipped topping. Top with red maraschino cherry halves.
Chill before serving.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: You begin by reserving 1 cup of cake mix for topping.
Next, you combine the rest of the cake mix, 1 egg and 1 stick of butter. Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Soften tortillas in oil.
For filling, mix sour cream, green chilies, olives and chicken soup.
Put 2 or 3 spoonfuls of filling and one or two teaspoons of cheese in each tortilla.
Roll and lay in buttered casserole.
Top with remaining filling mixture and cheese.
Bake in a 350 oven until cheese is melted and lightly browned.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Cook syrup, water, sugar and vinegar until a hard ball will form in cold water.
Beat egg whites with a pinch of cream of tartar.
Add syrup slowly; add vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Drop from spoon on waxed paper.

title: the hulk protein shake
directions: Add all ingredients to blender; blend and pour into cup.

title: angel food cake
directions: Sift sugar 3 times.
Divide in half.
Place half with flour. Sift 5 times.
Mix salt and cream of tartar together well and set aside.
Beat egg whites until bubbly and sprinkle salt mixture on top.
Beat again until shiny and starting to peak.
Add vanilla and 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Beat again.
Add sugar, beating until sugar is gone.
Fold in flour mixture 1/4 cup at a time. Alternate, mixing until well mixed.
Using rubber spoon, place mixture in ungreased angel pan.
Smooth surface; take care not to force air out.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 40 minutes.
Invert cake on wire rack 1 hour.
Remove with sharp knife around edge and frost.

title: cran-strawberry cooler
directions: In a blender, combine the cranberry juice, white grape juice, fresh strawberries, ice and sugar substitute. Cover and process until smooth. Pour into chilled glasses.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together. Mix together, then fold in carrots and nuts.
Flour and grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done when tested with toothpick.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: fettucine alla zucchini
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Wash and chop all vegetables.
Saute	onion
in
margarine
until barely tender. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over pasta; sprinkle liberally with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: oatmeal cinnamon drops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix first 5 ingredients, then add flour, cinnamon and soda; mix and add the oats, then mix in raisins (optional), nuts (optional) and chocolate chips. You can also add 1/2 cup butterscotch chips or 1/2 cup M&M's, if you like. Bake about 12 minutes or until golden brown. Enjoy! Makes about 6 dozen.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. No icing needed.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons bacon fat.
In remaining fat, cook onion and green pepper until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese. Pour mixture into baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° until rice is done, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Crumble bacon; sprinkle each dish with half the bacon, then cheese.
Return to oven to
melt cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: caunterbury's coconut bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Mix the next 5 ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Toast 1 cup of coconut on
cookie
sheet.
Be careful, it burns easily.
Add dry ingredients and coconut to batter.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp and green noodles
directions: Saute shrimp in butter.
Cook noodles according to package directions and drain.
Mix first 8 ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: swedish cabbage pudding
directions: Cut off the bottom part of stem of white cabbage.
Cut the cabbage into shreds or pieces.
Brown them in butter in a frying pan.
Boil rice, water and 1/2 teaspoon salt for approximately 20 minutes.
Let the rice cool.
Mix ground beef with 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and white or black pepper.
Add the rice and milk.
Lay the cabbage and the meat in alternate layers in a buttered ovenproof dish.
The top and bottom layers should be cabbage.
Bake in a 350° oven for 3/4 to 1 hour.
Serve with boiled potatoes and lingonberries.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mound bar
directions: Combine sugar, graham cracker crumbs and oleo; press into bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Combine milk and coconut; spread over crumb mixture and bake 15 minutes.
While still hot, sprinkle with semi-chocolate chips; spread over top of bar.

title: quiche lorraine hors d'oeuvre(diet recipe)
directions: Break up crisp bacon and sprinkle half of it into bottom of a 9-inch pie plate.
Make following custard:
Put into a bowl and mix well the 2 whole eggs plus 2 yolks, Dijon mustard, dry mustard, cayenne pepper, bacon fat and 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese.
Scald the cream by heating just to the boiling point (do not boil).
Pour scalded cream into the custard mixture.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Remove.
When set, sprinkle with remaining cheese, bacon and parsley.
Serve warm.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time mixing well after each addition.
Add flour and milk, then vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: margaret eichhorn's date bars
directions: Beat egg yolks until light and add sugar.
Sift flour once, measure, add baking powder and sift again.
Add dates and nuts (finely chopped) to the flour, rubbing well through flour so as to separate them.
Add to the egg and sugar mixture.
Fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour to 1-inch thickness in shallow baking pans and bake in slow oven (325°) until a toothpick inserted will come out clean.
When cool, cut in 1 x 3-inch bars and sift powdered sugar over them.
Then eat!

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat eggs well. Add sugar and beat.
Sift cocoa and cornstarch. Add to eggs and sugar. Add evaporated milk and whole milk. Add vanilla. Pour in 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour. Add meringue.
Bake until brown.
This makes 2 pies.

title: coffee cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar,
baking
powder
and
salt. Blend shortening in this mixture.
Remove 1/2 cup for topping. Blend buttermilk and soda and add to flour-shortening mixture. Fill greased and floured pans 1/2
full.
Melt butter and pour over batter in pans.

title: chicken dip
directions: Mix everything together except for cheese. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with Fritos Scoops.

title: scallops and shrimp with linguini
directions: Cut scallops in half and combine with shrimp.
Cut pea pods in half; thaw if frozen.
In skillet, cook onion and garlic in oil and margarine over medium-high heat for 30 seconds.
Add half of the scallops and shrimp mix, parsley, basil and red pepper.
Cook and stir for 3 to 4 minutes or until scallops are opaque and shrimp turn pink.
Repeat with remaining shrimp and scallops. Return all mixture to skillet.
Add pea pods and tomatoes.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
In large bowl, toss scallop mixture with linguine.
To serve, transfer to a platter and sprinkle with cheese, if desired.

title: velvet almond fudge cake
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup almonds on bottom of 10-inch Bundt pan. Measure all remaining ingredients (except chips and almonds) into mixing bowl.
Blend, then beat for 4 minutes at medium speed. Stir in almonds and chips.
Pour into pan and cook in microwave on High for about 16 minutes.
Check with toothpick.
Do not overcook; there should be wet spots on the top of the cake. Invert on a plate.

title: spinach and cheese cannelloni
directions: Cook lasagne; drain.
Cut each strip crosswise in half.
Cook spinach in small amount of water 5 minutes; drain well.
Cool.
Mix spinach, butter, cottage cheese, nutmeg, basil, Parmesan cheese, eggs, salt and pepper.
Place 1 tablespoon spinach mixture in center of each lasagna half.
Roll up, beginning at narrow end. Place rolls, seam side down, in greased casserole.
Cover with white sauce and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Bread crumbs and dots of butter may be used on casserole before baking.

title: combination sandwiches
directions: Mix all the ingredients together with the mayonnaise and spread between two slices of bread or on crackers.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: pepperoni calzone
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Lightly grease 12-inch pizza pan. Unroll 1 can of dough and place in greased pan. Starting at center, press out dough with hands to edge of pan. Spread a single layer of pepperoni over dough and then sprinkle shredded cheese over pepperoni. Unroll remaining can of dough and press out dough on work surface to form 12-inch round. Fold dough in half and place over cheese. Unfold. Press outside edges to seal. Cut several slits in top crust. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until crust is deep golden brown. Cut pizza calzone into wedges and serve with a side of warm pizza sauce for dipping.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer until just tender.
After the potatoes have cooled, peel and slice into 1/2 to 3/4-inch slices.
Place sweet potatoes in a lightly greased dish.
Mix apple, mandarin oranges, lemon juice, brown sugar, pineapple juice and cinnamon.
Pour this mixture over sweet potatoes.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: okra, corn and peppers
directions: Place butter in a 2-quart casserole.
Microwave at High for 55 seconds or until melted.
Add sweet red peppers and green onions; cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Microwave at High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add okra, corn, water, salt and pepper.
Cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Microwave at High for 3 minutes; stir well.
Cover; microwave at High for 7 to 9 minutes, or until corn is tender. Yields 6 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream the sugar and cooking oil.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift flour, baking powder and cinnamon together; add creamed mixture.
Fold in carrots and nuts.

title: holiday balls
directions: Add peanut butter to butter and stir well. Add graham crackers, coconut and nuts; mix well.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla; mix. If mixture is too soft to form into balls, add more crumbs until
of right consistency.
Form into balls on cookie sheet lined with waxed paper.
Chill well. Melt chocolate bark in microwave dish and dip balls. Drain and put on cookie sheet.

title: "the best" chicken and rice
directions: In a deep skillet brown rice and chicken.
Add 2 cups water; simmer until water dissipates.
In a separate pan, combine butter, sour cream and milk.
Dice onion and brown; add this to mixture along with mushrooms and seasoning packet.
Combine rice, chicken and mixture.
Serves 4.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and vanilla until golden brown, then put in butter, vanilla, peanuts and soda.
Spray cookie sheet and spread candy on sheet until cool, then break up.

title: potato tacos
directions: Fill a large pot with water and heat to boiling.
Add potatoes and cook for about 30 minutes.
In a frying pan, heat 1/2 tablespoon lard or oil.
Mash the potatoes and spoon them into tortillas.
Close filled tortillas and put in frying pan.
Cook until tortillas are done, then add lettuce and tomatoes on top of potatoes to make tacos.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In a greased 9 x 13 casserole, start 1st layer of bread slices (about 8).
Then the 2nd layer of ham, then a 3rd layer of cheese. Repeat all layers again; top with leftover bread pieces.

title: grandma's gingersnaps
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add molasses, vinegar, soda and sifted dry ingredients.
Form small balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: slo-cook beef barbecue
directions: Cut meat across grain into slices 1/4-inch wide and 1/2-inch long.
In large skillet heat oil and brown meat on all sides. Transfer meat to slow cooker.
In blender or food processor place remaining ingredients and blend until onion is finely chopped. Pour sauce over meat.
Cover and cook on low 5 to 6 hours.
If slow cooker is less than 1/3 full, place a circle of foil over surface of meat.
If possible, stir meat once midway through cooking time.
Serve on dinner buns.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Make a paste of cocoa and red food coloring.
Add to mixture.
Next add flour, buttermilk and vanilla, beat until smooth.
Fold in vinegar and bake in 3 layers in 350° oven.

title: garden rice
directions: Saute onion, celery and garlic in butter in a Dutch oven; add broth, brown rice, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat 40 minutes.
Stir in chopped carrot and cook an additional 10 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugar gradually.
Add egg; blend thoroughly into creamed ingredients. Add flour.
Shape into small balls; place on cookie sheet.
With a fork, press across cookie in both directions.
If desired, press nuts on top.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown the pork chops in a frying pan.
When both sides are browned, drain off any fat.
Add slices of raw potatoes over the pork chops.
Pour a large can of tomato sauce over the potaotes and pork chops.
Cover and simmer over low heat for an hour or until chops are tender and the potatoes are done.

title: cavatelli
directions: Cook macaroni by directions on the box. Brown onion and pepper. Add sausage and hamburger. Cook until all pink is gone. Combine macaroni and hamburger mixture; add pizza sauce. Top with cheese. Bake at 325° until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: fried mexican ice cream
directions: Scoop out 4 to 5 balls of ice cream. Return to freezer.
Mix the cornflakes, cinnamon and sugar.
Roll frozen ice cream in half of the crumb mixture and freeze again.
Beat egg and dip coated balls in egg, then roll in remaining crumbs.
Freeze until ready to use; heat oil to 350°.
Place 1 frozen ice cream ball on slotted spoon and cook for 1 minute.
Immediately remove and place on serving dish.
Drizzle with honey and top with whipped cream. Balls will be crunchy on the outside.

title: doctor bird cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt, sugar, soda and cinnamon.
Add bananas to flour mixture then add oil, eggs, vanilla, pineapple and juice.
Blend but do not beat.
Pour into greased 9-inch tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Does not require frosting.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick melted margarine and cracker crumbs.
Stir and press in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan evenly to make crust.
In mixing bowl, place cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1 1/2 sticks margarine.
Beat until creamy and spread over crust.
Place sliced bananas over filling.
Pour drained pineapple over bananas. Cover with Cool Whip, sealing to the edges.
Arrange cherries on top and sprinkle with nuts.
Drizzle chocolate syrup on top.
Cut in squares to serve.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk for 3 minutes.
Add peanut butter and saltines.
Mix together.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Cook beef seasoned with salt and pepper, onion and celery until done.
Add green lima beans (cooked until tender).
Add okra, tomatoes, corn and diced chicken, then season to taste.
Let simmer until vegetables are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Serve on white rice while hot.

title: corn pudding(simplified)
directions: In a blender, blend the milk, eggs, flour and oleo.
Stir in the corn.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: summer relish
directions: Combine chopped vegetables with vinegar and sugar.
Chill thoroughly before using.
Serves 8.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Cool to lukewarm.
Mix in brown sugar, oleo or oil, white sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Beat together.
Mix together cinnamon, soda, flour and salt and add to first mixture.
Bake in greased 8 x 12-inch pan 35 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Add salmon and bread crumbs.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells (18) and drain.
While shells are cooking, combine the Ricotta cheese with the parsley.
In a saucepan, cook the zucchini, tomato sauce, tomatoes, onion, mushrooms, garlic powder and bay leaf.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan and fill shells with Ricotta mixture.
Pour sauce over shells and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with foil and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
Each provides: 2 protein, 1 bread.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in shallow baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream well.
Pour over chicken pieces.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 275° for 4 hours, uncovered.
Good served with cooked rice.
Suitable for freezing.

title: vinegar and oil dressing
directions: Combine equal amounts of oil, sugar, vinegar and water into cruet, bowl or bottle.
Mix well.
Pour over greens combination or any kind of vegetable salad.

title: fruit ambrosia
directions: In large bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk, yogurt and lime juice; mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill 3 hours or longer to blend flavors.

title: chipped beef bake
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, onion flakes and garlic powder.
Stir in chipped beef and top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly around the edge and the pecans have begun to brown.
Serve hot with rye bread rounds or crackers.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In a saucepan, cook celery and onion in butter until tender. Add chicken broth, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Slowly stir in mushroom soup, milk and cheese. Mix thoroughly.
Remove from heat.
Add cooked spaghetti.
Let stand for 1 hour.

title: biscuits
directions: Just follow directions on the box.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Turn out on floured board and roll to about 1/4 inch.
Cut with cookie cutter into desired shapes. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar. Bake at 350° about 8 minutes.

title: sausage cheese muffins
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Add cheese soup, Worcestershire sauce and water.
Add biscuit mix and stir until just moistened. Pour batter into greased muffin tins.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mock chicken casserole
directions: Drain mushrooms.
Saute onion in margarine.
Boil water; cook frozen vegetables about one minute and drain.
Combine mushrooms, onion, soyameat and vegetables.
Add slivered almonds.
Turn into buttered 7 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Top with cheese and bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package.
Drain (should have about 3 1/4 cups spaghetti).
Stir butter into hot spaghetti.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form mixture into a crust in a buttered 10-inch pie plate.
In skillet, cook ground beef, sausage, onion and green pepper until tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, paste, sugar and garlic salt.
Heat well until mixture cooks down to a thick consistency.
Spread cottage cheese over bottom of spaghetti crust.
Fill pie plate with meat mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese and bake for 5 minutes.
Cool and slice like a pie.

title: cornstarch paste
directions: Mix 3/4 cup water, Karo syrup and white vinegar together in a saucepan and bring mixture to boil.
Stir constantly to avoid lumps.
If a few drops of oil of wintergreen are added, this paste will be good for about 2 months.
Let mixture stand overnight before use.

title: crunchy crescent rolls
directions: Separate rolls.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Roll up; dip in butter and liquid smoke mixture.
Roll in dry mixture with remaining ingredients.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: raisin pie
directions: Put sugar, raisins and water on stove to boil.
Then mix cream, cornstarch and beaten egg yolks.
Add to boiling mixture; cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Add meringue and brown.

title: cioppino
directions: Saute onion, green pepper, celery, carrot and garlic in olive oil until soft.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, basil, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Discard bay leaf.
Cut fish into serving size pieces.
Scrub clams well.
Stir wine into tomato sauce.
Add fish, shrimp and scallops; simmer for 10 minutes.
Place clams in layer on top of fish.
Cover and steam 5 to 10 minutes, until clams fully open and fish flakes easily.
Sprinkle on parsley before serving.

title: brown rice
directions: Brown onion in butter on top of stove.
In casserole dish, put rice, beef broth, consomme and onion; stir.
Place in oven at 350° until dried, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: In 5 to 8-quart Dutch oven over medium heat, in butter, cook onions until tender.
Add water, potatoes, salt and seasoned pepper.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Do not drain.

title: finnish spoon cookies
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a skillet over medium to medium-high heat until it is golden brown.
Set aside to cool.
Add sugar and vanilla to the cooled butter.
Mix flour and soda; add to the butter mixture.
Shape with a teaspoon and place upside-down on a cookie sheet.
Slide out with a fingertip.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until light brown.
Do not overbake.
Cool.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat and bone from meat.
Cut into 4 to 6 servings. Grease pan lightly with fat from meat.
Brown meat; sprinkle with salt both sides.
Push meat aside.
Add onions, cook and stir. Add bouillon, soy sauce and garlic, cover and simmer 10 minutes or until meat is tender.
Add green pepper; cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with water; pour into mixture in skillet, cook, stir constantly, until thickens and boils.
Boil and stir one minute, add tomatoes, heat thoroughly.
Serve immediately with hot rice.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream the butter or margarine and sugar in a large bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend well.
Combine the dry ingredients.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts, if desired.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Do not overbake.
(Cookies will be soft.
They puff during baking, will flatten when cool.)
Cool on cookie sheet about 1 minute.
Put on wire rack to cool completely.
Makes about 5 to 6 dozen cookies. Store in airtight tin lined with wax paper to retain softness.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend first 4 items until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze.
(Do not take out of freezer until ready to use.)
Cuts easily; return unused pie to freezer until ready to use again.

title: buttery corn bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Combine the eggs and milk.
Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with egg mixture.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 22 to 27 minutes or until tests done.
Cut into squares.
Serve warm.

title: roast (block style)
directions: Place roast in pan.
Use foil
to line pan and wrap the roast. Sprinkle garlic powder,
salt
and
pepper over roast. Mix together cream of mushroom soup and Lipton onion soup mix. Pour over meat; wrap foil
around
roast
and
seal tightly to hold in juices.
Bake 4 to 4 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: freezer cucumber chips
directions: Combine the first 4 items.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain and squeeze veggies to extract moisture.
Add chili pepper, sugar and vinegar.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Spoon into freezer containers; cover tightly and freeze at least overnight.
Thaw 4 hours before serving, then store in refrigerator.
Makes 3 pints.

title: macaroni
directions: Prepare Creamettes according to general directions on package; drain. Melt butter. Add flour and cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes. Do not brown. Stir in milk, salt and pepper. Cook until smooth and thickened. Combine macaroni with white sauce. Pour into 11 x 7-inch casserole. Top with cheeses. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Stir in between cooking time for buttery creaminess.

title: almond snack mix
directions: Melt bark in double boiler.
Pour over mix.
Mix well so all ingredients are coated.
Lay on waxed paper to dry.
When cool, break apart and store in covered container.

title: low-fat cole slaw
directions: Mix together and chill several hours.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix all together well and drop by teaspoons onto a prepared cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown meat and drain.
In large pan add all ingredients and simmer together for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve and enjoy.

title: no fat muffins
directions: Spray muffin pans with nonstick spray.
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: jaeson's chili
directions: Brown meat well; drain on paper towels.
Saute onions and garlic until soft.
Place all ingredients (except beans and corn meal) in a large pot.
Cook over low heat for 2 hours.
Add beans and cook another hour.
Degrease chili.
Stir in corn meal and return to heat.
Bring to a boil; stir constantly.

title: applesauce
directions: Heat apples and water to boiling over medium heat; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, to break up apples, until tender (5 to 10 minutes).
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; boil and stir one minute.
Makes about 4 cups.
Can be easily doubled or quadrupled for canning, just pour into hot jars.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat egg and sugar well in a small mixing bowl; sift flour with baking powder and cinnamon.
Mix in.
Stir in vanilla, apples and nuts.
Spoon batter into a well-greased and floured 8 x 8 x2-inch pan; bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crusty brown on top.
Let pudding cool about 1/2 hour before serving.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Mix corn, margarine, soup and rice.
Put in casserole dish.
Layer cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook ground beef on medium heat until brown; drain grease. Stir in taco seasoning mix and tomato sauce.
Simmer on low heat until thickened.
Crush tortilla chips; mix all ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together and pour in pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes in preheated oven at 425°, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: zesty sausage appetizer
directions: Cut sausage links diagonally into bite-size pieces.
Combine preserves and mustard in saucepan and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Add sausage and simmer 15 minutes longer.
Serve hot from chafing dish, electric skillet, etc.
Spear with picks. Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: cherry dessert jello mold
directions: Add all above ingredients and chill.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, salt, milk, egg and oil.
Insert a skewer in one end of each hot dog; coat with flour.
Dip into cornmeal mixture.
Deep fry in hot oil (375°) until golden brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
In mixing bowl, combine sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla and zucchini.
Mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in nuts.
Bake one hour at 325°.

title: holiday cran-apple drink
directions: Mix juices and sugar in a big pan.
Take orange and put cloves in it (approximately 48).
Add cinnamon sticks.
Heat to boiling, then simmer for 2 hours before serving.
Serve hot.
May add rum or other liquor, if you wish.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a well-greased pan.

title: wonderful brownies
directions: Mix together and bake as directed.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: Drain carrots, measuring liquid.
Add water to make 3/4 cup liquid.
Blend cornstarch and liquid in a saucepan.
Add instant breakfast drink, butter, salt and nutmeg.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat, cook and stir until thickened. Add carrots and heat.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer ingredients in order listed as evenly as you can.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cocoa drop cookies
directions: Combine brown sugar and butter; add egg and vanilla.
Blend. Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cocoa.
Mix into first mixture alternately with milk.
Fold in nuts, if desired. Drop spoonfuls onto slightly greased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: spanish-style pork chops
directions: In a bowl, rub pork with Worcestershire sauce.
In a frying pan over medium high heat, brown chops in oil, without crowding. Discard oil.
Return meat to pan.
Add water.
simmer, covered; for 10 minutes.
Turn chops.
Add capers and garbanzos.
Simmer, covered until meat is no longer pink at bone, about 5 minutes. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 6.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Beat all together.
Put into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients and place into greased loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all together. Sprinkle on top of casserole. Melt 2 1/2 tablespoons butter. Pour over topping. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Put small marshmallows on top last 5 minutes of baking. Brown lightly. Enjoy.

title: homestyle chicken and biscuit dumplings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in a large cooking bag. Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Add gravy mix, garlic powder and water. Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
Place carrots in bag in even layer. Sprinkle chicken with seasonings, then place on top of carrots. Arrange biscuits around chicken. Close bag with tie. Cut 6 (1/2-inch) slits in top of bag.
Bake until chicken is tender, 50 to 55 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients thoroughly. Stir in milk. Blend dry ingredients; stir into mixture. Fold in blueberries. Spread in a 9 x 9 greased pan.

title: eric's spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute
sausage	after
breaking into very small pieces. Saute onions and garlic.	Add remainder of ingredients except cheese and linguini.
Simmer for 60 minutes.
Add cheese when you put the linguini in the pan to boil.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Slice and crumble all ingredients.
Pour in broth and mix with hands.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour or until liquid is cooked off.
To test doneness, insert knife in middle.
If knife comes out clean, dressing is done.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, parsley, pickle relish, and white pepper in a large bowl.
Stir well.
Add macaroni and remaining ingredients.
Toss well to coat.
Cover and chill. (Serves 8.)

title: rosebud rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in the water; stir in sugar.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Grease muffin tins; spoon each 1/2 full.
Circle with spoon to make smooth.

title: spinach dip in a flash
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl; transfer to a greased pie plate and bake at 305° for 20 minutes.	Serve hot with fresh bread.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix the rice, soup and water in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Put the chicken breasts on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a pan, saute onions in butter. Add water and bouillon cubes. Bring to a boil and add noodles. Cook until tender. Add broccoli and garlic. Cook 8 minutes. Add warm milk and cheese. Heat until cheese is melted.

title: grilled shrimp
directions: Wash, shrimp and drain on paper towels.
Mix salad oil, lemon juice, salad dressing mix, salt and pepper.
Place shrimp in bowl and pour over marinade.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Lift shrimp from marinade with slotted spoon and place on grill.
Grill for about 10 minutes, turning once and brushing with marinade.
Pour remaining marinade into saucepan and stir in brown sugar, soy sauce and onion.
Heat to boiling.
Serve as a dip for shrimp.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer first four items in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt butter or margarine and drizzle over top.
Add crushed pecans to the top. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix flour and baking soda; set aside.
In large bowl cream butter until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Gradually beat in flour mixture just until blended and smooth.
Beat in sour cream and vanilla until blended.
Beat in chocolate until well blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool on rack in pan 10 minutes.
Carefully remove from pan.
Cool completely on rack.

title: fondant nut candy
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and water and stir until sugar is dissolved; cook to soft ball stage.
Beat until too stiff to beat; pour immediately over nuts and work nuts into candy.
When cool, form into roll.
Slice.

title: irish soda bread
directions: First soak raisins in boiling water.
Mix flour, salt, sugar and baking powder together in large bowl.
Crumble soft stick of oleo into dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add caraway seed, if desired.
Drain water from raisins.

title: matthew schmidts apple crunch
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of a 10-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling.
Sprinkle nuts on top and pour melted margarine over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place potatoes in a greased 13 x 9 inch pan. Season with 1 tsp. salt and 1 tsp. pepper. Melt butter. In a bowl, add onions, sour cream, cream of chicken soup and melted butter. Mix well. Pour soup mixture over potatoes. Sprinkle with cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until all is completely warm and cheese begins to melt.

title: church salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and chill.

title: lemonade pie
directions: In a large bowl beat together condensed milk, lemonade and Cool Whip until well blended.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: ed's peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water until the syrup threads.
Add peanuts and margarine to syrup and cook long enough for the peanuts to be slightly roasted.
The candy will be darker than the syrup.
Remove from fire and immediately add soda; beat well and pour into a buttered cooking sheet.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: rosettes(these require a rosette iron for frying in deep fat.)
directions: Beat eggs and cream together; add sugar and flour and stir until smooth.
Cover and let stand for 2 hours.

Put the Rosette iron in the deep fat while both are still cold; heat to 375°. Remove iron while it is still very hot; dip it into the batter. Hold the batter-coated iron above the batter for just a moment before returning it to the hot fat; this will prevent the Rosette from slipping off the iron as it cooks.
Fry to a golden brown; remove from the fat and slip off the Rosette from the iron.
Drain on paper towel.
Heat the iron again before dipping it into the batter.
After they are slightly cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: low-fat zucchini muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into muffin tins with cupcake papers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
May be frozen in airtight bags!

title: mama's brownies
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and cocoa; set aside.
In saucepan, mix water, margarine and oil.
Combine mixture with ingredients in saucepan and add buttermilk, eggs, vanilla, salt and soda.
Mix together and pour into a greased and floured large sheet cake pan. Bake.

title: mochiko cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add milk directly to melted margarine and eggs.
Add liquid to dry mixture and mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with flaked coconut.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Cut in pieces and cool.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Press broccoli between paper towels to remove excess water. Combine corn bread mix, eggs, chopped onion, cheese, butter and seasonings.
Stir well.
Stir in broccoli.	Pour mixture in greased 8-inch square pan.	Bake at 375° for 25-30 minutes or 'til brown.
Serves 9.

title: quick corn and mushroom squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough into 4 long rectangles. Place in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Press firmly over bottom and 3/4-inch up sides to form crust.
Seal perforations.
Sprinkle ham, cheese, corn and mushrooms evenly over crust.

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add oil and salt.
Mix with flour and pepper.
Knead for 10 minutes.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Flatten on greased pans.
Spread with sauce and partially bake at 425°.
Top with cheese and your choice of toppings.
Return to oven until cheese is melted and crust is browned.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Sprinkle the salt over the cucumbers and after 10 minutes, drain. Add the remaining ingredients. Mix all together well; chill and serve.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except margarine and bread cubes.
Put margarine in bowl.
Soak bread in melted margarine.
Put potato mixture in casserole dish.
Place bread cubes on top.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom

title: party pizza
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage and onion; drain.
Add cheese and catsup to meat mixture and stir until cheese melts.
Mixture will be soupy.
Put slices of party rye bread on cookie sheet.
Put a teaspoon of mixture on bread and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: stuffed grilled burritos
directions: Pour Ro-Tel in raw beef.

title: shrimp and crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken chowder
directions: Simmer chicken in water in covered kettle with carrot, onion, bay leaf and basil.
When tender cool (without cover).
Skim off fat.
Take meat from bones and cut in bite size pieces.
Put fat into large pan with flour and blend well. Add chicken broth and milk; cook, stirring until thickened.
I mash carrot and onion and return to pot.
Add all other vegetables and cook until tender. Add chicken and heat through.
Just before serving, add egg yolk mixed in the wine.
Stir just to blend and serve.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: curried shrimp and rice
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter. Blend in flour, sugar, curry, ginger, salt and pepper. Slowly pour in half and half. Add cinnamon. Simmer, then add lime juice and cooked shrimp. Simmer 5 minutes. Add rice and water chestnuts.
Bake in a moderate oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: microwave bread pudding
directions: Mix milk, eggs, sugar, cinnamon and salt in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Beat with rotary beater.
Stir in bread cubes and raisins.
Dot with butter.
Microwave 26 to 28 minutes on Medium or until almost set in center.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruity yogurt dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; cover and blend on high speed about 15 seconds or until smooth.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Mix the cream cheese (softened at room temperature) with vanilla and eggs.
Slowly add sugar until it is creamy.
Set aside until ready to use.

title: meatball or "lil" wiener sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in a large slow cooker.
Bring to a mild boil; stir to mix well.
Add 3 pounds of prepared meatballs or little cocktail frankfurters, or little smoked sausage links.
Even good if you mix together.
Simmer for 1 to 2 hours on low.

title: cheese grits
directions: Boil water with salt substitute.
Add grits, cheese substitute and margarine and cook until thick.
Cool for a few minutes before adding beaten eggs and Tabasco sauce.
Pour in glass baking dish (well-greased with margarine or sprayed with original Pam).
Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger, eggs, rice, onion, salt, pepper and milk.
Make into balls.
Makes about 25 balls.
Roll in flour, brown in skillet and pour off grease.
Pour the cream of mushroom soup and water over the meat balls and simmer for 1 hour.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese. Put into a 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt together; then set aside.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Lightly oil a skillet and heat.
Drop batter by spoonfuls onto the hot skillet. Fry until brown on one side.
Flip and brown on the other side.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and warm water in mixing bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix with spoon until smooth.
Add enough remaining flour to handle easily; mix with hand.

Turn onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic; about 5 minutes. Round up dough and place in greased bowl, cover with damp cloth and let rise in warm place (85°) until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours. Punch down and let rise again until almost doubled, about 30 minutes.
Roll 1/2 of dough into oblong 15 x 9-inch, spread with softened butter and cinnamon and sugar.
Roll up tightly, beginning with wide side, pinch edges to seal.
Cut roll into 1-inch slices. Melt 1 stick of butter in 13 x 9-inch pan and sprinkle with about 1 cup brown sugar.
Place slices a little apart in pan.
Cover and let rise until doubled in bulk, 35 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.
While slightly warm, frost with powdered sugar frosting.
Makes 3 dozen rolls.

title: meat - cheese roll
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine beef, egg, bread crumbs, onion, 1/3 cup tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix well and shape into a flat rectangle, about 10 x 12 inches, on a piece of wax paper. Sprinkle cheese evenly over meat mixture.
Starting with the shortest end, roll up jelly roll fashion and press ends of roll to seal.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients in bowl; set aside.
Heat oil in nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
Sprinkle chicken with pepper.
Cook for 4 to 5 minutes per side.
Transfer to platter; keep warm.
Add green onions, ginger and garlic to skillet.
Cook 1 minute.
Add soy mixture and cook one minute more.
Pour over chicken.
Makes 4 servings.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Cook, debone and tear chicken into small pieces. Combine soup, chicken, sour cream and poppy seed. Place in 8 x 10 baking dish. Crush crackers on top of mixture. Add oleo (cut up) on top of crackers. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mash peaches and drain all fruit thoroughly.
Add coconut to fruit mix.
Mix Eagle Brand milk with lemon juice until thick. Pour over fruit mixture.
Pour in Cool Whip and mix thoroughly. Pour mixture into two pie shells and refrigerate for at least 3 hours before serving.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Spoon three pints of sherbet into punch bowl.
Let stand about 5 minutes.
Pour in chilled 7-Up slowly, stirring to combine with sherbet.
Float scoopfuls of remaining sherbet on top of punch. Serves 36.

title: tapioca delight
directions: To 5 cups boiling water, add tapioca and salt. Boil 15 minutes. Remove from heat and add sugar and Jell-O. Refrigerate overnight. Then add the pineapple, bananas and Cool Whip. Mix well. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: tuna-swiss baked patties
directions: Place tuna in a colander; rinse under cold tap water 1 minute. Set colander aside to let tuna drain 1 minute.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream butter, vegetable shortening and sugar.
Add together the other ingredients and bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 325°.

title: apple cake(a 10 year old can make this cake)
directions: Mix apples, sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Stir, add dry ingredients.
Mix by hand.
Nuts and raisins may be added.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Be sure to grease and flour pans.

title: sausage soup
directions: Brown sausage in olive oil.
Cook spinach; drain.
Put in large pot.
Add broth, bouillon and water.
Heat to boiling. Lower to simmer.
Cut up sausage and add to soup.
Add orzo when close to serving.
Serve.

title: double chocolate mousse cake
directions: Best if prepared early in the day or a day ahead.

title: texas cake
directions: Bring butter, water and chocolate to a boil.
Add at once remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into jelly roll pan. Bake at 350 for 20-25 minutes.
Pour icing on as soon as you remove cake from oven.

title: broccoli and egg casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of water until tender; drain. Saute onion in butter until tender; stir in soup, mustard and salt.
Heat until bubbly.
Arrange broccoli in casserole dish. Top with chopped egg, cheese and mushroom sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle onions on top and bake 5 minutes more.

title: pineapple meringue pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in water and pineapple juice.
Add egg yolks.
Blend in butter, lemon juice and rind.
Add crushed pineapple.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir until smooth.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue.

title: oriental chews
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place noodles and coconut on cookie sheet in single layers.
Bake 10 minutes or until crisp.

title: cheese snappy wafers(for kid munchies)
directions: Cut butter into flour until mixture resembles coarse meal. Mix in cheese, pepper and salt.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Pinch off small pieces and place on ungreased cookie sheet and pat flat. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Cut up chicken.
Wash and season with salt and both peppers. Fry until golden brown in cooking oil over hot fire.
Lower heat and add all chopped seasonings, except garlic.
Cook until all seasoning is clear or onions, bell pepper and celery are tender. Here's where you add the hot sausage.
I think this makes a better jambalaya.

title: pineapple cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Whip cream cheese with sugar; add Cool Whip, then add well-drained crushed pineapple. Fold together.
Spoon into graham cracker crust, 9-inch.

title: eggless applesauce cake
directions: Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes.
Good luck!
Would pass as a fruit cake for Christmas.

title: helen c. morlock's lebkuchen
directions: In separate bowl, combine the molasses and baking soda. Cream sugars and shortening
in
large
bowl.
Add
eggs, sour cream and molasses mixture.
Add
flour 1 cup at a time adding the spices and anise oil after
some of the flour is mixed in. If you are using nuts, mix
those in also before all the flour is in. Continue adding
the
flour until dough does not stick to your fingers.
Chill
overnight.
Roll
out
on	a
floured surface, about 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet 10 minutes at 375°. X	In separage bowl, combine the molasses and baking soda.
Cream sugars and sho Xg in large bowl.
Add
chopped
nuts	before all the flour. Chill overnight.

title: deluxe sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter, confectioners sugar, egg, vanilla and almond extract.
Blend in flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Cover; chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each half to three-sixteenths inch thick on floured board.
Cut into desired shapes; sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes, or until light brown on edges.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: 7-layer casserole
directions: Layer all the ingredients in casserole dish in layers.
Bake for 1 hour, uncovered, at 350°.

title: pad thai
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions; drain.
Combine tomato juice, soy sauce, vinegar, sugar and cornstarch; set aside. Heat 1 tablespoon of oil or butter in hot wok or large skillet. Add chicken and stir-fry 1 minute; remove.
(I cook my chicken until it is completely done which takes quite a bit longer than 1 minute.)
Add garlic, bean sprouts and green onions and stir-fry for 1 minute.
Stir in linguine and cook 2 more minutes or until heated through.
Return chicken with shrimp, curry, pepper and tomato mixture.
Cook, stirring until sauce boils and thickens. Makes 4 servings.

title: barbecue butter beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake 2 hours.
Perfect for picnics, doubled.
Can cook in crock-pot, also.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake following directions on box.
While cake is still hot, prick holes all over.
Pour Carnation milk over cake while still hot.
Cool.
Cover with Cool Whip and coconut.

title: dump cake
directions: In 9 x 13 pan, put pineapple and pie filling with dry cake mix over the top. Add pecans and cut butter pieces over the top. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: corn flake drops
directions: Boil sugar and corn syrup for 45 seconds in 3-quart pan. Remove from heat and add crushed corn flakes and peanut butter; mix.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook broccoli according to package; drain.
Cook onion in margarine until tender.
Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tomato salad
directions: In a saucepan, heat tomatoes; add jello and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Pour into a sprayed salad mold or square glass dish. Refrigerate.

title: peas in sour cream sauce
directions: Cut cucumber into 1/4-inch slices.
Soak tarragon leaves in 2 tablespoons warm water for 10 minutes.
Place peas, cucumber, salt and tarragon in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes; drain well.
Combine sour cream, mayo and lemon juice. Place in saucepan over low heat; stir constantly, until thoroughly heated.
Combine sauce and vegetables to serve.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Grind apples and peppers.
Combine all ingredients except Sure-Jell.
Cook just until it comes to boil.
Remove from heat; let set 5 minutes.
Add Sure-Jell.
Cook to rolling boil per instructions on Sure-Jell package.

title: party ham sandwiches
directions: Freeze the package of rolls. Melt butter. Add mustard, onion, poppy seed and Worcestershire sauce. Mix well and refrigerate until mixture is spreadable. Slice package of frozen rolls with electric knife to make 2 pieces - like 1 big sandwich. Spread the top slice and the bottom slice with the butter mixture. Cover bottom half with slices of ham and cheese. Place top half on the ham and cheese slices. Return to freezer. Bake at 350° approximately 40 minutes. Cover loosely with aluminum foil to prevent getting too brown. Slice into small rolls. Serve warm.

title: barley chicken soup]
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large soup kettle.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 2 1/2 hours.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: georgia's jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add soda to buttermilk and beat until it foams. Add to butter/sugar mixture.
Add jam, nuts and raisins; beat well. Sift flour and spices; add gradually, beating as you go.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: applesauce-rhubarb muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir just until moist (batter will be lumpy).
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Sprinkle tops with cinnamon-sugar.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: In a big bowl, whip your eggs, then add all but 1/4 cup of the cheese.
Pour into the Pie Crusts.
Bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour. Top with remaining Cheese and bake another 15-20 min.
Let it cool for 1/2 hour.
Makes 12 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix well.
Put into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in a casserole dish.
Place cheese slices over chicken.
Mix soup and water.
Pour mixture on cheese slices. Sprinkle stuffing mix on mixture.
Pour melted butter over stuffing crumbs.
Bake at 350° until well heated and cheese melts.

title: upside-down pear cake
directions: Melt butter in bottom of 10 x 15-inch glass baking pan. Sprinkle this with brown sugar.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crumble cookies in food processor or blender and set aside. Mix all remaining ingredients except Cool Whip.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer in large (clean) flowerpot or container with cookies on top and refrigerate.

title: slow cooked pepper steak
directions: Saute steak in a little oil and put into a slow cooker.
Mix together soy sauce, minced garlic, sugar, salt, pepper and ground ginger and pour over meat in slow cooker.
Add onion, tomatoes and green pepper to slow cooker.
Cook on low for one hour.
Stir in water mixed with cornstarch.
Cook on high until thickened.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: chess cake
directions: Melt butter. Add sugar. Blend. Add egg yolks; beat well. Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture. Fold in nuts. Add vanilla. Beat egg whites stiff. Fold into mixture. Spread into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. It will rise, then fall.

title: sausage stuffing
directions: Saute celery and onion with meat and diet margarine.
Add bread and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Stuff turkey.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Blend gelatin and water.
In a saucepan, mix brown sugar, salt, spices, pumpkin, beaten egg yolks and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring until it boils.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Cool.
When partially set, beat until smooth.
Carefully fold into meringue (egg whites, cream of tartar and sugar).
Pour into a baked 9-inch pie shell and chill until set (about 2 hours). Garnish with whipped topping.

title: bar cheese spread
directions: Microwave cheese and margarine until melted.
Stop and stir often.

title: eggplant
directions: Peel eggplants; cut in round slices 1/2-inch thick.
Place under broiler until brown on both sides.
Brown meat; season, then put a layer of eggplant, meat, tomato sauce (mix this with 2 cans of water first) and sprinkle with pine nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pudding mix and pineapple mix in Cool Whip.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup melted margarine, salt, pepper, soup, cheese, onion and sour cream. Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Mix cornflakes with 1/4 cup melted margarine and spread over top. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Layer chops in bottom of 9 x 13 casserole dish. Top with potatoes and onion. Thin mushroom soup with 1/2 can of water. Pour over chops, potatoes and onion. Cover casserole with foil. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until bubbly.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Remove lemon.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: mulled cider
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil, except brandy.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add brandy and strain mixture.
Serve warm.
May use tea or more apple cider in place of brandy.

title: braised sirloin tips
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter until lightly browned.
Spoon into 3-quart casserole.
Add meat to skillet and brown.
Spoon over mushrooms.
Combine 3/4 cup water, wine, soy sauce, garlic and onion; add to skillet, scraping bottom to salvage particles.
Blend cornstarch with 1/3 cup water, stir into wine mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Spoon over meat.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Add salt to taste.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: pigs in blankets
directions: Prepare pastry.
Roll pastry to 12 x 12 1/2-inch rectangle. Spread lightly with mustard.
Cut pastry into 40 (3 x 1 1/4-inch) strips.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Wrap each frankfurter with pastry strip, pinching ends together.
Place seam side down on baking sheet.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
