Add soup, cheese, onion and corned beef.
Put in greased baking dish.
Pour milk over all and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: molasses brown bread
directions: Sift flour with all baking powder, baking soda and salt. Combine with all dry ingredients.
Beat in molasses and milk.
Fold in nuts and raisins; mix.
Spoon batter into 10 or 12 greased soup cans.
Fill to 3/4 and cover cans with small pieces of greased aluminum foil.
Place cans on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Unfold.
Freeze if you want to.
Cut in thin slices and put cream cheese on them for snacks.

title: quick and easy lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix together spaghetti sauce, water, oregano, basil and meat.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: marshmallow cream fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk; bring to a boil and stir constantly.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate chips, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly. Add walnuts, if desired.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet. and spread evenly.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: lasagna gustoso
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
In skillet, on medium heat, cook and stir ground beef until red is partly out; add onions and continue cooking until red color is out of meat.
Stir in one can of pizza sauce, tomato paste, garlic salt and oregano.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: burrito snacks(kids can make!)
directions: Kids can make this snack.

title: jim's chili(makes 5 gallons)
directions: Bring to a boil and simmer for 4 hours.

title: mimi's ranch chicken
directions: Salt both sides on chicken breast.
Rub on Ranch dressing and roll in corn flake crumbs.
Place in greased baking dish.
Add water to dish, to cover half of chicken.
Cover with foil or lid. Bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: huguenot torte
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Beat eggs with mixer until lemon colored.
Without stopping the mixer, add sugar to the eggs.
Add baking powder, salt and flour; continue beating until well mixed.
Add vanilla; fold in apples and nuts. Spoon into greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, or until crusty and brown.
Crust will fall as Torte cools.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Heat peanut oil in a heavy skillet.
Add diced onion and saute until transparent, about 5 minutes.
Allow to cool in skillet. Grind or chop together chicken livers, egg and entire contents of skillet.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Chill until ready to serve. Makes about 1 1/2 cups spread.

title: strawberry sauce
directions: Thaw strawberries according to package directions.
Crush strawberries.
In a medium saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch; stir in strawberries and jelly.
Bring to boiling.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Strain; cool.
Serve over ice cream. Cover; chill any remaining sauce.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix sugar and
Crisco.	Add
eggs, beaten.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Mix alternately
with flour.
Bake in tube pan at 275° or 2 hours or longer.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding mix with cottage cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add pineapple and "optionals."
Let set and serve.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onion in hot oil. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, water, salt, sugar, pepper and oregano.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions. Drain.

title: quiche
directions: Brown meat and onions. Blend mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch. Stir in meat, onions and cheese. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. You can freeze before baking if you wish. Add 30 minutes to baking time.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix everything except sugar and mayonnaise.
Mix sugar and mayonnaise together and stir into salad.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Serve cold.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese at bottom.
Then spread chili on top of that.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: aunt jewel's chicken salad
directions: Toast the seeds and nuts in a skillet; use the same skillet for dressing.
Toss all ingredients and season to taste.

title: stuffed tomatoes mid-east style *(serves 8)
directions: Cut a 1/2-inch piece off stem end of tomatoes; reserve tops. Scoop out as much of the pulp as possible.
Sprinkle the insides of the tomatoes with 1/2 the salt and pepper; chop pulp.
Heat 1/2 cup oil in saucepan; brown onion in it.
Stir in the bulgur until coated.
Mix in the tomato pulp, mint, currants and remaining salt and pepper.
Add the water; cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Mix in parsley and nuts; taste for seasoning.
Stuff the tomatoes loosely; replace the tops.
Arrange upright in oiled baking dish.
Brush with remaining oil; sprinkle with breadcrumbs. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
These can be served as a first course or as a vegetable side dish and are equally good hot or at room temperature.

title: magic peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 15-inch pan.
Mix 1 cup of sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour this over butter.
Don't mix or stir. Place peaches on top of this.
Add remaining sugar over peaches. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or longer.

title: scotch crunchies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch bits.
Stir in noodles, raisins and peanuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer accordingly.
Microwave 10 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: pull-aparts
directions: Separate biscuits and cut in half.
Mix cinnamon and sugar in a large plastic bag.
Put biscuit pieces in bag and shake to coat (do half at a time).
Place in a well-greased Bundt pan.
Melt together brown sugar and oleo; pour over biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix together; add enough flour until no more sticky. Roll out real thin and slice. Let dry on baking sheets. Make ahead of time and they freeze well. Also should double the recipe, depending on how many noodles you want.

title: london broil
directions: Mix well.
Cover meat.
Refrigerate and let stand for at least 4 hours or overnight, turning meat several times in marinade. Baste meat while broiling or baking.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Boil sugar, syrup, water and salt until it forms hard ball stage (270°).
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly pour hot syrup over the egg whites, taking care not to pour too much syrup at a time.
Beat until mixture becomes stiff.
Add vanilla and nuts. Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: pistachio nut swirl cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, eggs, sour cream, oil and almond extract in large mixer bowl; blend.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Pour 1/3 of batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Sprinkle with half of the sugar mixture.
Repeat layers and top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; beat until light and fluffy. Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Beat into egg mixture, along with vanilla.
Add nuts, coconut and chopped apples.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Melt butter; add sugar.
Add a little milk to egg yolks and beat well.
Add remaining milk and combine ingredients.
Cook on medium flame until thick, about 15 minutes, stirring constantly. Add vanilla.
When thickened, add coconut and nuts.
Let sit until cool.

title: rocky road cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: crazy crust apple pie
directions: In bowl mix flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, egg, shortening and water; blend well.
Pour batter into 9-inch pan.
Mix pie filling, lemon juice and cinnamon; pour into center of batter, do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil your chicken until tender, then pull chicken off bones. Melt the margarine in baking dish in oven. Sprinkle 2/3 box stuffing mix over the margarine.
Put chicken over stuffing mix. Heat together the broth, soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken. Add the other 1/3 box of stuffing mix on top of broth mixture. Pour 1/2 cup broth over top. Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: steak and wine
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown steak cubes well in margarine.
Add pepper and garlic salt while browning.
Add wine, mushrooms with juice and water to cover meat.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add cream cheese and melt.
Do not boil cream cheese. Serve over rice.

title: linguini and clam sauce
directions: In frying pan, cover bottom with olive oil or butter.
Heat and saute garlic.
Add clams and parsley.
Heat thoroughly; spoon over cooked linguini.

title: old world supper
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove.
Slice and saute the remaining ingredients in the bacon drippings until tender.
Top with Polska kielbasa or smoked sausage.
Heat for 12 minutes, covered. Garnish with crumbled bacon.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: hot creamed corn
directions: Melt cream cheese with butter and milk until smooth. Fold in other ingredients.
In a 2-quart pan, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: long john silver's batter dipped fish
directions: Heat the oil in a deep pan to about 400°.
Cut the fish into approximately 7 x 2-inch wedges.
With a mixer, blend the flour, water, egg, sugar and salt. Dip each fillet into the batter, coating generously. Quickly drop into the oil.
Fry each fillet until dark golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Remove from the oil and place on paper towel or metal rack to drain.
Makes 4 to 6 fillets.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Lightly stir in oil, sugar, zucchini, vanilla, sifted flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon together. Add to egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts and pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until center springs back when lightly touched.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool.

title: orange ambrosia
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in sherbet until melted.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Mix in oranges and pineapple.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: pork chops with mushroom gravy
directions: In 10-inch skillet, cook bacon and onions over high-medium heat, stirring occasionally, until browned.
Add pork chops, arranging bacon and onions on top of chops.
Cover; continue cooking for 10 minutes or until brown.
Turn pork chops.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cover; cook pork chops until tender (10 to 15 minutes).
Place pork chops on platter; keep warm while preparing gravy.
In same skillet with drippings, brown particles, bacon and onions.
Add remaining ingredients except half and half and mushrooms.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until smooth and bubbly.
Stir in half and half and mushrooms.
Cook until mixture is thickened.
Serve over rice and chops.

title: vanilla wafer cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and milk.
Cook to soft ball stage. Remove from heat and add vanilla cookie crumbs, coconut and nuts. Drop at once on cookie sheet.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: best buttermilk biscuits
directions: In mixing bowl, sift dry ingredients together.
Cut shortening into flour mixture; gradually add buttermilk.
Turn onto floured surface and knead a few times.
Roll dough to 1/2 to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter. Place with sides touching on cookie sheet and bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 12 biscuits.

title: coconut cake supreme
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan according to package directions. While cake is hot, make holes in cake with toothpick.
Pour on Eagle Brand milk a little at a time.
Allow to soak in.
Repeat with coconut cream.
This is a slow process.
Cook cake completely.
Mix desired amount of coconut with Cool Whip.
Spread on cake.
Sprinkle additional coconut on top.
Store in refrigerator.

title: puffy oven pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add flour and milk to eggs, beating with mixer until combined.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in each of 2 (9-inch) glass pie pans.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Pancakes will form a well in the center and edges will puff up.
Spoon fruit into center of pancakes.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and top with sour cream.

title: surrilitos de maiz
directions: *May use
1 bouillon cube or 1/2 cups chicken stock in place of water.

title: easy pork chop bake
directions: In a 2 to 3-quart casserole dish, slice and evenly space 1 stick of margarine or butter.
Peel, then thinly slice potatoes and layer over the bottom of dish.
Spread carrot coins over potatoes. Place browned pork chops over carrots.
Prepare onion soup packet with water as directed, then pour over pork chops.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover with foil; bake at 375° for 1 hour, or until liquid is absorbed.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Spread each slice of ham with a little mustard.
Place a slice of cheese on each slice of ham.
Cut roll-ups in quarters after rolling them up.
Secure loose ends with toothpicks.
Heat until cheese is beginning to melt and ham is hot in 375° oven.
Can also be heated in microwave oven.

title: the roundman's fabulous baked zita
directions: Cook the pasta to al dente (slightly undercooked).
In a separate bowl, mix together the Ricotta cheese, about three quarters of the grated Mozzarella cheese, the beaten eggs and the spinach.
Don't overmix, just slightly blend the ingredients. Empty the zita into a colander and drain.
Do not flush with cold water, as you will be using the hot pasta immediately.

title: pumpkin nut bread(portuguese)
directions: Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans or three 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
In a large bowl, cream the shortening and sugar until fluffy. Stir in eggs, pumpkin and water. Blend in flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 70 minutes.
Serve plain or with cream cheese or butter.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain fat.
In a casserole dish, spray bottom with nonstick spray.
Cover the bottom with 1 cup of green chile mixture.
Layer with corn tortillas, then sprinkle hamburger or chicken, onions and cheese, then cover with more green chile. Repeat layers of corn tortillas, hamburger, cheese and chile two times.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Alternate tomatoes and toast cubes in greased 1-quart casserole, having toast for top layer.
Season with grated onion, salt and pepper.
Pour butter over all.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) until heated through, about 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Heat 1 inch salted water to boiling.
Add broccoli.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Cook until stems are almost tender, 10 to 12 minutes; drain.
Place broccoli in an ungreased 1 1/2-quart round casserole.
Beat soup and milk, with whisk until smooth; pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix baking mix with oleo until crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of cheese. Bake until crumbs are light brown, about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour and salt together.
Add milk and beaten egg yolks.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shells.
Top with meringue.
Brown in oven at moderate heat.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: In a large skillet or wok, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add mushrooms, onion and ginger; stir-fry for 1 minute.
Push vegetables aside.
Pour egg into skillet and scramble.
Stir in rice and gently, separate grains.
Add shrimp and soy sauce; stir until thoroughly heated.
This kitchen tested recipe makes 4 servings.
Contains 189 calories.

title: shake a pickle
directions: Stir all ingredients until dissolved.
Slice 1 gallon unpeeled cukes and pack solid in a gallon glass jar.
Pour brine over cukes.
Set out at room temperature and shake 3 to 4 times a day for 3 days.
After 3 days, place in refrigerator.
Will keep for weeks.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place one pie crust in pie pan. Combine brown sugar, white sugar, flour and lemon rind; toss lightly with the fruit.
Fill one pie shell.
Cover with top crust.
Bake for 50 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: canadian pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and oleo and bake on cookie sheet 7 minutes at 350°. Cool and crunch up.

title: creamy carrot casserole
directions: Mix together and put in greased casserole dish.
Top with seasoned croutons tossed in melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lipton coq au vin
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until crisp; remove and reserve.
In drippings (if using nonstick pan, drippings aren't necessary), brown chicken.
Add bacon, onions, soup mix blended with wine, water, salt, thyme and garlic.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve with rice or noodles and buttered broccoli.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; add this to rest of ingredients that have been placed in large pan. Combine all together (you can divide the cookie mixture evenly and add chocolate chips or peanut butter chips, raisins, etc.). Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Place on racks and cool. Since this makes such a large recipe, this can be divided.

title: baked hamburger in tomato sauce
directions: Moisten bread with a little milk, then add to hamburger.
Make patties.
Brown and drain.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Thoroughly chill can of milk in crushed ice or in refrigerator overnight.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add salt, honey, lemon juice and lemon rind.
When it has congealed slightly, beat milk until it is stiff and whip gelatin mixture into it.
Spread half of the crumbs on large pan (10 x 13 1/2-inch).
Pour lemon mix over it and top with remaining crumbs.
Set in refrigerator to chill (approximately 3 hours).

title: rigatoni ala vodka with shrimp
directions: Melt butter over medium heat, do not let it brown.
Over medium to low heat, cook onion, garlic and basil until onion pieces are soft, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Add vodka.
Raise heat to boil, sirring the mixture frequently.
Lower heat to simmer and cook sauce for 8 minutes or until about 1/4 of the mixture has evaporated and the aroma of the vodka has subsided.
Add tomatoes, continue cooking about 5 minutes longer.
(Tomatoes should be soft.)
Add heavy cream and cook 5 minutes longer.
Add shrimp, cover pan and cook additional 5 to 8 minutes or until the shrimp are cooked through.
Cook rigatoni according to package directions. Drain and transfer rigatoni in a large bowl.
Add vodka sauce and toss well with pasta.
Garnish with basil leaves, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: spicy cheese dip
directions: Cook onion in margarine until clear.
Add tomatoes, cheese and garlic.
Stir constantly until cheese is melted.
Add Tabasco to taste.
Serve hot with corn chips.

title: hawaiian pineapple upside-down cake deluxe
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a 9-inch or upside-down cake pan, 2-inches deep, melt butter.
Mix in brown sugar.
Arrange pineapple slices close together in mixture in a single layer.
Cut remaining slices in half and stand around sides of pan.
Place a cherry and walnut half in center of each slice.
Keep warm while mixing cake. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, mixing well.
Stir in flavorings and peels.
Fold in coconut.
Spread over pineapple in prepared pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Remove from oven and let cake stand in pan for 10 to 15 minutes.
Loosen edges carefully and invert onto serving plate.
Allow pan to rest over cake one minute so syrup will drain.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: apple casserole
directions: Mix butter, sugar, flour and cheese.
Microwave on Low until melted.
Spread over apples.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.

title: poppy seed fruit dip
directions: Combine dressing, sugar and vanilla.
Gently fold in whipped cream.

title: beef ribs(tangy hot)
directions: Sprinkle ribs with salt and pepper.
Arrange on a rack in a foil lined roasting pan (12 x 9 x 1-inch).
Roast, uncovered, in preheated hot oven until browned for about 30 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350°.

title: okra skillet
directions: Fry onion in oleo until tender. Add okra; cook over medium heat for 3 minutes. Stir constantly. Stir in tomatoes and corn. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and quarter.
Cook noodles.
Combine cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Mix all ingredients.
Crumble Lay's regular chips to cover top.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Use exact measurements.
Mix well together; chill.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Mix together first five ingredients.
Layer noodles, cheese mixture and spaghetti sauce in casserole.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Pour 1 cup of water around edges.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour. Remove cover.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, until brown and bubbly.

title: tiger butter
directions: Melt white chocolate in a 2-quart microwave dish for 5 to 8 minutes on Medium heat, stirring every two minutes.
Stir in peanut butter and spread mixture on wax paper on a cookie sheet. Immediately melt chocolate chips on Medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes. Drizzle over peanut butter layer.
With knife or spatula, swirl mixture.
Refrigerate until firm, then break or cut into small pieces.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan and bake 30 minutes at 300°. Remove from oven and add 1 1/2 cups brown sugar.
Mix all ingredients well.
Remove 1/2 of mixture for topping.
Press remaining half for crust.
Spoon onto crust 1/2 gallon ice cream. Add topping and put into freezer.

title: original cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
This will make 4 balls. Can be rolled in finely chopped pecans or finely shredded dried beef.

title: ham and cheese "pizzazz" rolls
directions: Slice package of rolls horizontally.
Mix butter, poppy seed, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread on bottom section of rolls.
Add layer of ham, layer of cheese, then another layer of ham.
Put tops of rolls on.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: nutmeg pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan. Combine flour, soda, nutmeg, salt and baking powder.
With an electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter and sugar until fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add vanilla.
On low speed, gradually beat in flour mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Spread in pan.
Bake until toothpick comes out clean, about 45 minutes.
Put powdered sugar in a sieve and sprinkle over cooled cake.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin. Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices.
Toss raisins with flour mixture.
Mix dry into wet ingredients.
Fold in nuts. Fill 12 cups 2/3 full and bake 18 to 20 minutes in a 400° oven. Serve warm with butter or honey butter.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a heavy pan.
Bring to a full boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in marshmallow, nuts and vanilla.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet or deep dish.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix
Jell-O
and cake mix.
Add oil; blend.
Add apricot nectar
and
lemon
juice.
Add
eggs 1 at a time, beating well after
each
addition.
Grease well and flour 10-inch tube pan. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and beat for half a minute or put in a blender and beat for half a minute.
Pour into a quart jar.

title: fruit dessert or salad
directions: Mix all together; garnish with mandarin oranges and maraschino cherries.
Can be made ahead and keeps well.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time beating well after each.
Mix flour and baking powder. Add alternately with milk beginning with milk and ending with flour.
Mix well.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Bake in a greased Bundt or tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: skillet hopping john
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter until onion is tender.
Stir in black-eyed peas, chicken bouillon, rice, salt and 1/2 teaspoon red pepper.
Bring mixture to a boil; cover and simmer 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Serve with additional crushed pepper if desired.
Serves 6.

title: pan browned potatoes with onions
directions: Melt the
butter in a frying pan.
Add the potatoes and onions; brown over high heat, letting them get as brown as you like. Turn
when
brown
and cook until done 15 to 20 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: five minute crab dip
directions: Drain can of crab thoroughly and place to the side.
Spread cream cheese from the center out on a 12-inch plate, leaving 1 to 1 1/2-inch edge.
Cover cream cheese with cocktail sauce. Sprinkle drained crab over cocktail sauce.
Place Triscuits around edge of plate and serve.

title: southern baked pork chops
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper. Brown in oil.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops. Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until chops are tender.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream
together eggs, oil and sugar.
Sift together and stir in cinnamon, flour, soda and baking powder.
Add zucchini, vanilla,
raisins and nuts.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
This freezes well.

title: baked rice-tomato dish
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add meat and cook until brown and crumbly.
Add rice, tomato juice, olives.
(easy on the salt.) Bake in a slow oven, (325 degrees) for 1 1/2 hours.
Add liquid if necessary.
This dish can be prepared ahead of time and then baked.

title: batter for chicken nuggets
directions: Make kettle 1/2 full of berries.
Fill it up with water and heat slowly until berries turn light.
Put through strainer and add sugar, 3 pounds to a gallon.
Stir until sugar is dissolved, then put in jars.
Let it work for a few weeks.

title: tomato and cracker salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl and chill.

title: grilled vegetable sandwich
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Oil 2 baking sheets.
Mince garlic and combine with oil.
Cut eggplants into 1/4-inch rounds and brush with garlic oil.
Put on baking sheets and sprinkle with salt. Bake 10 minutes.
Slice peppers.
Combine peppers, 1 tablespoon garlic oil and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Turn eggplant and push slices close together.
Add red peppers and sprinkle vegetables with thyme.
Bake until very soft, 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove vegetables and heat broiler.
Grate cheese.
Cut bread into 4 pieces and split.
Brush with remaining garlic oil.
Broil until golden. Top bread with vegetables and cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, granulated sugar, vanilla, melted margarine and the egg and place in a buttered casserole dish.
Mix brown sugar, flour, nuts and soft margarine to crumb consistency. Sprinkle on top of dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: raspberry fudge balls
directions: Combine cream cheese and chocolate.
Beat at medium speed until blended.
Stir in vanilla wafer crumbs and jam; cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in nuts. Cover and chill until firm.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cracker salad
directions: Crush crackers in a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Dredge slices thickly with flour.
Fry quickly in 2 tablespoons hot drippings or butter, browning well on both sides. Remove to serving platter.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and brown sugar. Keep warm.
Add 1 tablespoon of butter to the pan and blend in a tablespoon flour.
Add the milk and cook, stirring constantly.
Should be about the consistency of thick cream.
Pour over tomatoes and serve.

title: salsa chili and cheese potato topper
directions: Microwave potatoes on High 8 to 10 minutes or until tender, rotating after 4 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Brown hamburger, bell pepper and onion; drain.
Stir in picante sauce, heat through, stirring occasionally.
Cut potatoes lengthwise in half. Break up and fluff with fork.
Season with salt.
Spoon equal amounts of beef mixture over each potato half.
Top with cheese and onions.

title: fruit soup
directions: In a 6-quart Dutch oven, soak apricots, prunes and raisins in water for 3 hours.
Add cinnamon sticks and sugar.
Over high heat, bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 1 hour.
Stir in apple and tapioca.
Cover.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 10 to 15 minutes or more, until tapioca is clear. Remove from heat.
Stir in undrained cherries and grape, orange or lemon juices until well blended.
Remove cinnamon sticks.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes about 16 (1 cup) servings.

title: popcorn balls(made easy)
directions: Put popcorn in a large bowl.
Place sugar, syrup and jello in pot.
Bring to boil under low heat.
Pour over popcorn.
Shape as desired.

title: corn cheese pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl (if too liquidy, add more corn meal).
Mix well.
Put into 2 well-greased 9-inch pie pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until top is golden and semi-hard.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Cook raisins in two cups water until soft.
Blend together first five ingredients.
Separately, blend together the remaining ingredients.
Add the raisins to the flour mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 small loaf.

title: instant homemade ice cream
directions: Mix with electric mixer.
Put in freezer can.
Add enough milk to fill can 2 inches from top.
Freeze.

title: sweet banana mash
directions: Peel and dice sweet potatoes.
Cook in pot, covered in water, until tender.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place bananas (unpeeled) on cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes.
Drain potatoes.
Placed in large mixing bowl.
Remove peel from baked bananas.
Add to bowl, along with sugar, butter and heavy cream.
Blend until smooth.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: mushroom-broccoli chowder
directions: In saucepan, bring broth and broccoli to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Set aside.
Cook mushrooms and onions in oleo.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk; cook and stir until thickened.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Add broccoli with broth, corn and pimiento; heat through.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add milk; heat on medium until thickens, then turn on low and add 1 tablespoon margarine.

title: yogurt bran muffins
directions: Combine yogurt and cereal.
Mix lightly.
Add raisins, carrots, sugar, oil and egg whites; mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to cereal mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
Spoon into paper-lined muffin pan, filling each almost full.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: lancashire hot pot(or lamb stew)
directions: Fry the chopped onion with the lamb pieces until lightly browned. Stir in the flour, mixing well. Add the stock gradually and bring to the boil, stirring well. Add the sliced carrots and leeks, most of the parsley and season to taste.

Pour the stew into a deep casserole dish and top with the sliced potatoes. Sprinkle them with salt, dot with butter and put the "Hot Pot" into a medium oven at 375° for about 2 hours. Turn the heat up for the last 1/2 hour to brown the potatoes. Enjoy!

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1/2 cup evaporated milk and butter.
Put 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk; pour over cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over caramel.
Add pecans on top of chips.
Add 1/4 cup evaporated milk to the rest of cake mix batter.
Spread batter over caramel mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Brown meat and drain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring over low heat until cheese melts.
Serve warm.
This dip will freeze well.
Serves 36.

title: fettuccini alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccini according to package directions.
Drain well and place in a warm serving dish large enough for tossing.
Add margarine, cream and Parmesan and parsley and toss until fettuccini is well coated.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 6.

title: bar x lima bean casserole
directions: Place into 2 or
quart
casserole; bake in 300° oven for 50 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Set oven at 325°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Mix flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder; set aside.
Beat sugar, butter and vanilla until fluffy.
Add eggs, beating one at a time. Add buttermilk; add to dry ingredients.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
(Add raisins, if desired.)

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and lightly grease baking sheets.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Cream the margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla until light and fluffy. Stir in flour mixture just until blended.
Drop by level tablespoon onto baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Cool on wire racks.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Crumble corn bread.
Layer corn bread, bacon, green peppers, onions, tomatoes and pickles in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine mayonnaise, pickle juice and sugar in small bowl; blend well.
Spoon over salad; toss lightly just before serving.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: hershey's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine, brown sugar, granulated sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in a separate bowl; then add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Saute
peppers, celery, onions and meats in hot butter. Add salt.
Reduce
heat;
cook	5
minutes.
Stir
in olives, mushrooms with liquid, soups and sauces.
Cook 5 minutes. Cook noodles
following box directions. Drain.
Pour noodles into a 14 x
x 2 1/4-inch roasting pan. Add sausage; gently stir until well
mixed. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake 35 minutes at 350°. Serves 12.

title: cajun tortilla chips
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. To prepare Cajun seasoning, combine first 8 ingredients in a small bowl. To prepare chips, arrange the tortilla wedges on 2 baking sheets coated with cooking spray. Coat wedges in cooking spray. Sprinkle 2 teaspoons Cajun seasoning over wedges. Bake chips at 375° for 6 minutes or until crisp. Yield: 80 chips (serving size: 4 chips).

title: apple wassail
directions: Boil all of the ingredients for 5 minutes, then add 1 tablespoon of brown sugar and boil for 15 minutes. Garnish with lemon or orange slices.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Combine tuna, soup, lightly beaten egg yolks, bread crumbs, onion, parsley, lemon juice and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in gently into tuna mixture.
Put in well greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mama filyaw's jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and mix well.
Combine buttermilk and jam.
Add alternately with sifted dry ingredients. Add nuts, raisins and spices; stir well.
Bake in tube pan for approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: seven layer rainbow salad(serves 16)
directions: Soften Knox gelatine in cold water.
Bring milk to boil.
Add sugar and dissolve.
Add softened gelatine and cool slightly.
Add sour cream and vanilla and beat on low speed.
Set aside to cool. Be sure to keep cream mixture at room temperature.
In four separate containers, dissolve each package jello in 1 cup hot water, then add 1/2 cup cold water.
Oil a 9 x 13-inch clear glass baking dish.
Pour in lime jello; refrigerate until firm.
Add 1 1/2 cups cream mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.
Continue with remaining jello and cream mixture, ending with cherry jello on top.
Make sure layers are set before adding each addition. Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours before cutting.

title: banana split delight
directions: Press margarine and graham crackers into bottom of 13 x 12-inch pan.
Beat eggs, 2 sticks margarine and powdered sugar together for 15 minutes, then spread on top of crackers.
Mix remaining ingredients together and spread over the powdered sugar mixture.

title: chocolate banana cream pie
directions: Prepare both chocolate and banana puddings in separate bowls. Pour banana pudding into pie crust. Let firm slightly, then pour chocolate pudding on the top. Refrigerate for 1 hour. Then before serving, remove from refrigerator and add the banana slices on top, then top with chocolate sprinkles. Serves 8.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill before serving.

title: beef tortilla pizza
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until meat is no longer pink; drain.
Stir in oregano and salt.
Lightly brush tortillas with oil.
Bake tortillas on 2 baking sheets in preheated 400° oven for 3 minutes. Spoon meat mixture evenly over top of each tortilla; top with an equal amount of tomato.
Sprinkle with basil and cheeses.
Return to oven; bake 12 to 14 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coleslaw dressing(tart)
directions: To one well beaten egg, add vinegar and sugar.
Mix together and cook over low heat until thick.
Stir constantly as it burns easily.
Add a little salt and pepper and a dash of butter.
Dry mustard may be added.
Thin with cream, if needed.

title: party ham rolls
directions: Mix margarine, mustard, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce and onion in a small bowl. Slice through middle of dinner rolls and open. Spread mixture on both sides; top with ham and cheese and close. Heat in 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil, then add peanut butter and heat, while stirring, until peanut butter is well-mixed.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and roll in balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: play dough
directions: Add one cup of Cascade and one cup of Clorox II to a bucket of the hottest water to come out of your faucet.
Soak several articles overnight and wash as usual.
I have also filled water in my washer, soak and wash the next morning.
I have found this removes about 90% of the stains that do not wash out with normal laundering.

title: nut rolls
directions: Crumble yeast into small bowl.
Add water and sugar.
Let stand until you mix butter and flour as for pie crust.
Make a well and add egg yolks, salt and yeast mixture.
Mix until smooth and dough leaves bowl.
Divide into 4 parts and roll thin.
Spread with filling; place on greased pan and brush with egg white.
Let stand in warm place for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until brown. Remove from oven and cover with damp cloth for 10 minutes.

title: carrot spread
directions: Combine all ingredients, blending well. Serve as a spread on snack bread or crackers.

title: easy grape juice
directions: Put grapes in quart jar; add sugar and fill jar with boiling water.
Process in boiling water bath canner, boiling 10 minutes. Let stand at least 4 to 6 weeks before serving by straining through sieve.

title: egg casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay 5 pieces of bread (cut into strips) on bottom of pan.
Whip eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread.
Shred 2/3 cup butter over eggs, 1 1/4 cups shredded Colby cheese.
Brown bacon; crumble over cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: collard greens, turnip greens, mustard greens, etc.
directions: Place meat in pot with water and boil for about 1 1/2 hours or until almost tender.
If very salty, pour off water after 1/2 hour of boiling and add fresh water.

title: creamy cherry delite
directions: Combine cherry pie filling, crushed pineapple and diced apple. Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, add bananas, Cool Whip, pecans and marshmallows.
Mix well and chill before serving.

title: zucchini squash
directions: Put butter in squash while hot.
Mix all ingredients in a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Beat for 3 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: sausage spaghetti spirals
directions: Cook sausage & green pepper over medium heat until meat is no longer pink. Drain. Stir in pasta & spaghetti sauce. Mix well. Transfer to a greased 13 X 9 X 2 baking dish. Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes. Uncover, sprinkle with cheese. Bake 5-10 minutes longer until cheese is melted. Serves 10.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and let set overnight.
It keeps well.

title: trifle (dessert)
directions: Make custard; set aside to cool.
In large serving dish, alternate layers of sliced angel food cake, fruit cocktail and sliced banana.
Moisten with orange juice/sherry.
Pour custard on top; set aside in refrigerator 1/2 hour.
Swirl Cool Whip on top. Decorate with almonds and cherries.

title: chocolate eclair pie
directions: Mix pudding per directions.
Add whipping cream.
Refrigerate pudding and whipping cream mixture.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Use a food processor for best results.
Drop small ingredients into processor bowl (garlic, coriander, green onions, etc.).
They will be finely chopped in a few seconds.
Scrape down bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, except for water, salt and pepper.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Let salsa ripen at room temperature for an hour.
At serving time, stir in ice water. (Water is optional.
If you use water, salsa may be soupy.)

title: rotel rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onion and bell pepper. Then add Ro-Tel and all other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 10 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cover cabbage leaves with boiling water and let stand until limp.
Drain.
Combine beef, salt, pepper, rice, onion, egg and seasonings.
Place a portion of meat mixture in a cabbage leaf, roll and secure with toothpicks.
Brown in Crisco oil.
Combine sugar, water, lemon juice and tomato sauce; pour over rolls. Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Baste now and then.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add milk, sugar and salt.
Combine corn with other ingredients.
Add to milk mixture.
Mix well.
Turn into buttered casserole and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook macaroni.
Mix together the hamburger, macaroni, mushrooms, pizza sauce, tomato sauce, Parmesan cheese, onion and 4 ounces of pepperoni in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and oregano.
Place remaining 1 ounce of pepperoni slices on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower in salted water until tender 10 to 15 minutes.
Strain and chop coarsely.
Saute onions in butter until tender.
Blend in flour.
Add broth, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until thick, stirring occasionally.
Add cauliflower and heat.
Do not boil.
Add lemon juice just before serving. Garnish with cheese, chives, chopped parsley or paprika.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken bake
directions: Place raw rice in baking dish.
Combine 1/2 of soup with water and pour over rice.
Sprinkle 1/2 of onion soup over this.
Place chicken over top.
Add remaining soup on top of chicken topping with remaining onion soup.
Wrap entire pan with foil.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and chill 24 hours.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage. Add vegetables and cook until tender. Add chicken broth and rice. Put into 2-quart greased casserole dish. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir yeast mix and buttermilk into flour mix.
Turn out onto floured surface and roll into 1/4-inch rectangle. Spread with butter.
Fold dough in half. Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: favorite corn muffins
directions: *Hodgson Mill or similar "stone ground" corn meal.

title: copper carrot salad
directions: Place in bowl in alternating layers, sliced carrots, pepper (coarsely chopped) and thinly sliced onion.
Make marinade of the undiluted tomato soup, oil, vinegar, sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over carrots, peppers and onions.
Let stand in refrigerator at least a day.
Keeps well for a week.

title: spiced zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts. Set aside.
Beat eggs lightly in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients and stir until moistened.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Combine ingredients; pour into buttered casserole dish and bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: holiday potatoes(10 to 12 servings)
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix together the potatoes, 1 cup of the Cheddar cheese, the soups, onion, sour cream and melted butter.
Pour mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in large Pyrex dish and bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Put in casserole dish and shred cheese on top.
Saute onion in oil, add hamburger and brown.
Add kernel corn; salt and pepper to taste.
Put in casserole dish on top of macaroni and slice olives on top.
Mix tomato soup and water.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 450°.

title: ranch-style turkey 'n pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Cream together cream cheese with 1 cup powdered sugar.
Whip Dream Whip according to package directions.
Fold Dream Whip into cream cheese mixture.
Spread in cooled pie crust and refrigerate for 2 to 4 hours.
Spread can of blueberry pie filling over cheese mixture.
Whip another package of Dream Whip according to directions and spread over blueberries.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Grate hot pepper cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Spread refried beans into small baking dish.
Mix the sour cream and Hidden Valley Ranch mix and spread over beans.
Layer the chili peppers, tomatoes, cheeses and olives.
Chill for 1 hour and serve with tortilla chips.

title: tex-mex tomato recipe
directions: Cook ground beef; add package of Sloppy Joe mix with water. Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook macaroni until done according to package; drain.
Add to ground beef.
Add corn and most of the cheese, leaving some for topping.
Add corn and mix well.
Top with leftover cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes, until cheese is melted and it is heated.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all
ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth. Serve immediately.
It's a quick refresher!

title: buffet stroganoff
directions: Saute beef in butter until brown.
Add mushrooms, green peppers and onions.
Mix flour with sour cream, stirring well to thicken.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over hot buttered noodles.

title: mile high strawberry pie
directions: Mash enough strawberries to make 3 cups. Add sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook on medium heat.
Stir until thick (boil 2 minutes).
Cool about 2 hours.

title: misoyaki butterfish
directions: Soak overnight.
Wrap each fish in foil individually, adding sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: dorothy's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on the box.
Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Thaw broccoli in 1/2 cup of water.
Combine rice, broccoli and water, onion and celery.
Add Cheez Whiz and soup. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick chicken casserole(microwave)
directions: *Tuna may be used.

title: crunchy cole slaw
directions: In a small saucepan, heat oil, stir in contents of noodle seasoning packet and garlic salt.
Cook for 3-4 minutes or until blended.
Meanwhile, crush the noodles and place in a bowl.
Add coleslaw mix and almonds.
Drizzle with oil mixture and toss to coat.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6 - 8.

title: almond-cream strawberries
directions: About 40 minutes before serving or early in the day, cut stem ends off strawberries.
Cut a deep "X" in top of each strawberry. Gently spread strawberry apart to make "petals."
Set aside.

title: chicken lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne until tender; drain and rinse.
Arrange half in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix soup, milk and seasonings. Set aside.
Beat cheeses together; stir in onion.
Spread half over noodles.
Put half the chicken over cheese layer.
Pour half the soup mixture over chicken.
Repeat layers and top with crumbs. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mistletoe salad
directions: Drain all vegetables well. Mix with onion, green pepper and celery.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together well, using a slotted spoon or spatula.
Place in canister with airtight lid and store until ready to use.

title: special sauce
directions: Combine Miracle Whip, French dressing, relish, sugar, pepper and onion.
Use fork to stir well.
Keep refrigerated, tightly covered, to use in 2 weeks.
Makes 2 cups.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar and soft oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add chocolate syrup and flour.
Make sure to mix well.
Add nuts if desired.
Pour onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
It should be soft.

title: pizza oo-la-la
directions: Brown beef and drain. Mix all ingredients together except Mozzarella and pepperoni. After mixing, don't let stand too long before baking (liable to jump out of pan). Pour into lightly greased casserole dish. Top with Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until noodles are tender.

title: calico bean hot pot "mom's"
directions: Cook bacon crisp; drain.
Brown onion and beef.
Combine with remaining ingredients in 3-quart casserole.
Stir.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours.

title: favorite buns
directions: Scald milk to lukewarm; add the rest of ingredients with 2 cups flour.
Beat well and let stand.
Add remaining flour.
Put in greased bowl to raise.
Punch down, raise again and make into dinner rolls.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: party fruit salad
directions: Mix together; put into 13 x 9-inch pan or mold and freeze. Cut into squares.
Serve on lettuce leaves or in a bowl.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Mix cake mix and bake as directed in 9 x 13 pan. Cool (best if done the day before). In a saucepan, combine 1/2 can of milk (6 ounces) and 1 1/2 cups sugar. Bring to a boil quickly. Remove from heat and add marshmallows; stir until melted. Stir in coconut. Pour mixture over cooled cake. Refrigerate until cool enough to add next layer. In a saucepan, combine 1 cup sugar and rest of milk; bring to boil. Remove from heat and add butter and chocolate chips. Stir until melted. Add almonds. Pour over coconut layer. Cool at least 2 hours. Top with more coconut and almonds.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Sift or stir dry ingredients in mixing bowl to blend thoroughly.
Slowly add sufficient water to form a stiff dough. Cover bowl with towel; let stand 30 minutes.
Pinch off balls of dough with floured hands and work out into 5-inch circles.
Drop into oil heated to 360° and fry until golden brown.
Yields 7 or 8 fry breads.

title: luncheon casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pat into a 9
x 13-inch greased pan.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Mix soup, milk and Worcestershire and pour over Tater Tots.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone the chicken breasts. Cut chicken meat into large pieces and arrange in shallow baking dish.
Place the Swiss cheese on top.
Mix the soup with 1/2 can of broth from chicken and pour over the top. Add the bread crumbs from the stuffing mix (as is, do not cook) and sprinkle the package of seasoning over the top.
Melt the margarine and dribble over the stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cook at 250° for 15 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients.
Brush on chicken or ribs when barbecuing.
Makes 3 cups.

title: college caesar chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in dressing for 10 minutes.
Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes on medium-low heat using entire contents of dressing. Check to make sure chicken is fully cooked.
Serve chicken on bed of rice.
Pour hot dressing over chicken and rice.
Serves 4.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, seasoned with a little salt and pepper.
Add grated carrot, onion, soup and sour cream.
Melt margarine and pour over stuffing.
Stir to coat stuffing.
Add half of stuffing to squash mixture.
Put in casserole dish and cover with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 370° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: kool-aid play doh
directions: Mix Kool-Aid with boiling water, then mix all ingredients together.
Smells great and less expensive than store bought! Store in Ziploc bags.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, beat.
Add melted chocolate and nuts.
Add sifted flour, soda and milk alternately. Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cover with chocolate powdered sugar icing.

title: marion's knots
directions: Cream sugar, egg yolks, vanilla and cream cheese.
Add flour, baking powder and rinds.
Blend well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add to batter.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook bacon and set to 1 side.
Add potatoes, onion, celery and
carrots to bacon drippings.
Cook about 20 minutes,
stirring
occasionally, until tender.
Stir in milk, salt and pepper.
Bring
to a boil.
Stir sour cream, flour and paprika together.
Add	1
cup of hot potato mixture to sour cream and mix, then pour sour cream mixture into soup. Cook until soup bubbles.
Pour
into
bowls and top with crumbled bacon. Yummy and fast.

title: ginger bread
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients and add soda dissolved in hot water.
Add flour.
When
mixed well, add 1 cup boiling water and mix. This mixture will be very thin.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Let cool.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix together.
Put in refrigerator and chill.
Put in muffin tins.
Pinch off about the size of large walnuts.
Cook at 400° for 20 minutes.
Will keep for days in refrigerator.
Cook as needed.

title: smoky spareribs
directions: Bake ribs in shallow pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over ribs. Continue baking 45 minutes or until tender.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
Cream butter, sugar and berries together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and extract.
Roll berries in extra cup of flour.
Mix in also.
Grease and flour cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours or until done.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over fresh fruit.

title: bolognese tomato sauce
directions: Put the oil, onion, garlic and parsley into a 2-quart saucepan.
Saute slowly.
Add ground beef, salt and pepper to taste, oregano and basil.
Saute slowly, stirring often, until meat is brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and 1 cup water. Simmer slowly, uncovered, for approximately 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: cucumber dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients
in a small bowl with a tight lid. Stir or shake well.
Refrigerate.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: garden vegetables casserole
directions: In a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange vegetables in layers (layer of squash, layer of onions, etc.).
In between layers, make 2 layers of rice.
Be sure not to have rice on top or bottom of casserole, preferably have tomato layer on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place butter slices on top.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt butter and save half for corn flakes.
Mix all ingredients and place in ungreased pan (13 x 9 pan). Mix corn flakes with leftover butter and place on top.

title: three beans and a punt salad
directions: Mix beans, onion and pepper in a bowl.
Mix other ingredients in a cruet and shake well.
Pour over salad and chill overnight or at least 4 hours.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: garden vegetable soup(serves 6)
directions: Spray large saucepan with Pam; saut carrots, onion and garlic over low heat until softened, about 5 minutes.

title: best cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended and add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Roll as thin as possible on generously floured bread board or on waxed paper.
Cut out and bake on greased cookie sheets in a 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: do ahead brunch eggs
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until boils and thickens.
Remove from heat. Add cheese; stir until melted.
Cover and set aside.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into balls. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
(May use a little sweet milk to make mixture stick together better.)

title: garden casserole
directions: Saute onion, red pepper and garlic in butter.
Add flour; cook 1 minute.
Spoon 1/2 into greased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Layer 1/2 potato, 1/2 beans and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat onion, potato and beans. Combine half and half, rosemary, salt and pepper and pour over. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with cheese and red pepper.
Bake 5 minutes.

title: champagne punch
directions: Put sherbet in punch bowl, then add the following: frozen orange juice, frozen lemonade, unsweetened lemonade, 7-Up and champagne.
Stir, then add ice and serve.

title: chicken continental
directions: Put shredded
dried beef in the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Wrap each chicken breast with 2 slices of bacon; place on top of shredded dried beef.
Mix sour cream and cream of
mushroom soup
together.
Pour
sauce
over chicken.
Put sliced mushrooms on
top
of sauce.
Sprinkle with dill weed. Cover.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours or 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Shake the biscuit pieces in a mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bring to a boil the remaining sugar, cinnamon and margarine.
Dump 1/2 the coated biscuits into a greased Bundt pan.
Add 1/2 of the boiled mixture.
Add remainder of biscuits and pour remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Let cool before dumping out.

title: milky way bar cookies
directions: Stir 1 bar with milk in a saucepan over low heat until melted and smooth.
Cool.
Beat together butter and brown sugar until creamy.
Beat in egg, vanilla and Milky Way mixture.
Stir in flour blended with baking soda and salt.
Gently stir in remaining candy bars and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until cookies are just firm to touch.
Cool.

title: biscuit anise cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients on bread board.
Make hole in center. Add melted butter, eggs, flavorings and nuts.
Knead together until silky consistency.
Fit to 2 (12 x 4-inch) well-greased oblong pans.
Cook in preheated 375° oven until golden brown. Slice while hot into slices 1/2-inch wide and 4-inches long. Serve cool.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Fry bacon.
When almost done crunchy, add onion, ham or sausage and mango pepper and fry a little.
Add cabbage and fry all together; do not overcook.
Add salt, pepper and garlic at the end.
If bacon is too greasy, pour some grease out.

title: egg salad
directions: In a medium-size bowl, whisk the mayo, sour cream, salt and pepper. Chop eggs coarsely. Serve over lettuce leaves or make a quick sandwich.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Grind eggs, green pepper and pimentos.
Add other ingredients. Mix and store in refrigerator.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles until tender (about 20 minutes).
Drain and salt to taste.
Beat the eggs and add the sugar to the eggs and beat together.
Quarter the cherries.
Drain the pineapple.
Soften the cream cheese and melt the margarine.
Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for at least 1 hour and until top is brown.

title: duchess sauteed beef liver
directions: Beat egg yolk (I used whole eggs) in mashed potatoes; spoon into pastry bag fitted with a star tip. Pipe potatoes in a border around edge of a 10-inch round platter or ovenproof board.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla.
Combine rest. Put on ungreased pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: fresh berry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Pour the berries into a 2-quart casserole dish or pan of equal size. Add water. Combine sugar and flour and stir to mix. Sprinkle over top of berries. Dot with butter.

title: orange pork chops
directions: 1. In large skillet, brown chops in oil on both sides.
Add water, paprika, pepper, and 1 tsp. salt.
Bring to boil. 2. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer about 35 minutes turning once. Meanwhile grate peel from the stem end of orange.
Then cut 6 slices from the other end.
Set aside 3. In saucepan over medium-high heat combine 1 Tbsp. peel, sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon, cloves, and remaining salt 4. Stir in juice.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add orange slices, cover and remove from heat.

title: spoon bread
directions: Bring to
a
boil
corn meal, water and salt.
Take off stove; add
eggs
well beaten.
Add milk, melted margarine and mix well. Pour into greased baking dish.
Cook at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until brown on top.

title: delicious vegetable casserole
directions: Mix soup, yogurt (or sour cream) and vegetables together. Spread in deep 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with croutons.
Pour melted margarine over croutons.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Cover the first 1/2 hour, uncover last 1/2 hour.

title: pineapple cheddar ball
directions: Drain pineapple well, reserving 1 tablespoon juice.
Beat together cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and pineapple juice.
Add pineapple, bacon, onion, soy sauce and salt; mix well.
Chill several hours or until firm.
Shape to form 1 large ball or 2 small balls.*
Chill.
Just before serving, roll cheese ball in cereal, coating well.
Serve with unsalted crackers, apple slices or raw vegetables, as desired.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: pineapple melba
directions: Place peaches in food processor or blender.
Cover and process or blend until smooth.
Divide pineapple among 4 dessert dishes. Sprinkle with brandy.
Top with puree and raspberries.

title: sweet and tarty salad
directions: Melt cranberry sauce with package of Jell-O.
Add other ingredients.
Pour in mold or bowl and chill until set.
Goes great with meat, especially at Thanksgiving or Christmas.

title: congo squares
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together onto wax paper. Cream the shortening and brown sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients, then add nuts and chips.
Pour into greased large cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: grammy's potato salad
directions: Boil and peel potatoes.
Beat eggs with sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook in double boiler until thick; then, thin with light cream when ready to use.
Add potatoes and garnish.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook beef until brown; spoon off fat.
Add soup, water, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Cook 10 minutes and spread on buns.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Grease 9 x 12-inch or 8 x 12-inch ovenproof casserole dish. Put in croutons on the bottom.
Next, add the cheese and then the beaten eggs in milk.
Let stand overnight or for one hour in the refrigerator.

title: shrimp or chicken marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients for marinade.
Pour over shrimp and marinate 2 to 4 hours.
Broil or grill shrimp.

title: rich coconut cream pie
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan and cook until thick, about 10 minutes.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue. Sprinkle coconut onto meringue and bake until brown.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat shortening, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes until edges are golden brown.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: oysters au gratin
directions: Melt the butter.
Add the crumbs.
Line a pie plate with 1/3 of the crumbs.
Add the oysters.
Season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Cover with rest of crumbs.
Bake for 20 minutes in oven at 400°.

title: instant tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in 1-pint jars (to use for gifts).
Use 2 tablespoons tea mix to 1 cup boiling water.
Adjust amount of tea used to suit your taste.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and cinnamon together.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add milk and flour mix alternately.
Last, add fruit and nuts.
Drop from spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° about 20-25 minutes.
Makes about 120 cookies (150 small cookies).

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream soft oleo and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in vanilla; fold in flour.
Fold in chips.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt
margarine; add sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil without stirring 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in soda and vanilla; beat well.
Gradually pour over popped corn. Mixing well.
Turn
into 2 large greased roasting pans.
Bake at
250° for 1 hour.
Stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven;	cool completely.
Break	apart
and
store
in tightly covered container.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water. Add sugar and dash of salt. Mix until dissolved. Add celery, nuts, apples, trail mix and cold water. Stir well and refrigerate to set.

title: beer rolls
directions: Mix just enough to combine ingredients.
Fill greased muffin pan 3/4 full.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.
Yield:
18 small or 12 large muffins.

title: spoonbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve ice cold.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add milk and chicken broth. Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Cook and stir 1 minute.
Add parsley, lemon juice, onion, salt and dash each of paprika, nutmeg and pepper.
Cool.
Add 1 1/2 cups finely diced chicken; salt to taste.
Chill thoroughly.

title: moussaka lolo casserole *
directions: Cook beef and onion slowly in a skillet until the meat loses its red color.
Add tomato sauce, teaspoon of salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, mint, cinnamon, parsley and garlic powder.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes.

title: smoked turkey
directions: Rub turkey cavity and skin with garlic salt, salt and pepper. Brush turkey inside and out with 1/4 cup liquid smoke. Refrigerate overnight.
Place turkey in a shallow roasting pan. Bake in a 500° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 400°.
Combine 1 cup boiling water, butter and remaining liquid smoke; pour into baking pan.
Bake turkey for 2 hours longer or until tender.
Baste with pan liquid.
Serve cold.

title: family size chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender; debone.
Cook egg noodles in broth. Drain broth from noodles and save.
Mix first 6 ingredients together with 1 cup broth.
Pour into a 9 x 11 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle crumbled bread on top; dot with the margarine. Bake at 400° until brown on top, about 30 minutes.
tags: cream of onion soup or cream of chicken soup

title: easy no-bake chocolate drop cookies
directions: Slowly melt chocolate and butterscotch chips over medium heat. When all melted, add Chinese noodles.
Stir until noodles are coated with chips.
Drop mixture by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Put in refrigerator until solid.

title: pasta casserole
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions; drain.
Heat soup, milk, mushroom pieces and cheeses together.
Stir until cheeses are melted.
Combine pasta, cheese sauce, vegetables, tuna and 1 cup French fried onions and seasonings.
Pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or heated.
Top with onions and bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer or until onions are golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cream of green pepper soup(a cold soup)
directions: Saute peppers and onion in butter over moderate heat 15 minutes.
Add broth and cumin, bring to boil and simmer 15 minutes.
Puree (in batches) in food processor or blender, strain through fine sieve into bowl and stir in cream, lemon juice, white pepper and salt to taste.
Chill at least 4 hours or overnight. Serve with dollops of yogurt.
Yield: 4 1/2 to 5 cups.

title: avocado appetizer
directions: Peel and remove seed from avocado.
Slice avocado very thinly (or cube) and arrange in a 9 or 10-inch glass pie pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and salt.
Spread sour cream over slices and sprinkle with garlic powder.
Pour taco sauce over entire mixture and cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or more. Just before serving, sprinkle with scallions and grated cheese. Serve with large corn chips or tostadas.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Mix in peanut butter and cornflakes.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips and Crisco in microwave.
When melted, spread over mixture in pan.
Let cool and cut into desired size bars.
Butter pan.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Mix everything except cashews together in large casserole dish.
Put cashews on just before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and margarine thoroughly.
Add all other ingredients and mix well. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.

title: sertoma chicken barbecue
directions: Place chicken skin side up on grate set 3 to 6 inches from heat.
Cook, turning occasionally and basting frequently with sauce.
Allow 45 minutes to 1 1/4 hours total cooking time.

title: zesty zucchini and tomato bake
directions: In greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan, place zucchini, then onion and then tomatoes in layers.
Mix crumbs with butter and sprinkle over vegetables with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: Place the cubed bread in a bowl; pour scalded milk over the bread and allow the cubes to become well soaked and slightly cool. Beat the eggs only until mixed.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla to eggs; stir into bread mixture.
Add melted butter and stir. Grease a 2-quart baking dish and pour in pudding; add apples, raisins and walnuts; stir together.
Set the dish in a pan containing 1-inch of hot water and bake in a 350° oven for 60 to 75 minutes, or when knife inserted in center comes out not too wet.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: french dressing with tomato soup
directions: Beat all ingredients thoroughly with eggbeater.
Add sugar last to measure taste.
Put into covered jar and refrigerate. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal and boiling water.
Set aside until cool.
Add eggs, milk, oil and fruit.
Mix all of the dry ingredients and blend into the bran mixture.
Grease 2 1/2-inch diameter muffin tins.
Fill 2/3 to 3/4 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: barbie doll's fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: hot fudge sundae
directions: Cook in heavy saucepan until thick.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Cool; pour over ice cream.

title: e-z lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brown hamburger; drain fat.
Add jar of Ragu to hamburger.
Meanwhile, boil lasagna noodles until tender. Layers:
Use 1/3 of hamburger mixture on bottom of pan.
Lay 3 noodles across top.
Use 1/3 of cottage cheese.
Spoon a heap on each noodle.
Blend throughout the pan.
Sprinkle 1/3 of Cheddar and 1/3 of Mozzarella on top.
Repeat 2 more times (3 layers). Cover pan with foil; bake 20 to 30 minutes (until cheese melts).

title: good dressed eggs
directions: Mash egg yolks; add other ingredients.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients in sauce pan.
Stir in milk.
Simmer over low heat, stirring until thick.

title: flank steak with wild rice
directions: Pound steak until thin.
Mash garlic and salt together.
Rub on steak.
Place carrots and onions on steak, leaving a border about 1/2-inch.
Roll steak jelly-roll fashion; tie to secure.
Place steak in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place rice around steak.
Mix season package with water and bring to a boil.
Pour over steak and rice; stir the rice.
Cover with foil.
Bake until water is absorbed or until meat and rice are tender.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Remove string and slice.

title: our favorite salsa
directions: Mix all together; let sit for approximately 30 minutes to blend.
Enjoy with chips.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large bag add all ingredients. Close bag and shake until all coated.
Place in a shallow baking pan.
Bake 40 minutes until tender and brown.

title: robert redford pie
directions: Crust: Mix
margarine,
flour and chopped nuts; press into 2 pie pans or one 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramelized onions
directions: Cut onions into thick slices.
In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, cook onion until tender.
Stir in vinegar and brown sugar.
Cook until golden.
Makes 4 servings.

title: black bottom cups
directions: Combine the cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, egg and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips. Set aside. Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl. Add water, cooking oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Fill cupcake papers 1/3 full with chocolate batter.
Place a heaping teaspoonful of cheese mixture in center. Sprinkle tops with sugar and nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 24.
These freeze well.

title: german apple cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, add eggs and oil.
Mix well.
Beat until foamy.
Sift flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add flour mixture in small amounts; beat well after each addition.
Now, mix by hand apples and nuts; mix well.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grilled burgers
directions: Mix beef, salt and pepper.
Form into four 4-inch patties. Grill over medium-hot coals for 5 to 6 minutes; turn and grill 4 to 5 minutes more.
Serve on buns, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: chili skillet
directions: Cook macaroni; saute onion in a little shortening and remove. Add salt and pepper to ground beef.
Shape into large patty in pan.
Brown 5 minutes on each side, then break into large chunks. Add chili powder and saute a few minutes more.
Add onion, beans, tomato soup and macaroni.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.

title: peach and raspberry crisp
directions: Stir together the flour, brown sugar, oats, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg, then add butter and stir until mix looks like coarse meal (can be done in food processor), then stir in pecans.
Toss fruit with the cornstarch, lemon juice and sugar.
Spread fruit mix into a 7 x 11-inch pan or glass casserole dish.
Sprinkle nut mix evenly over it and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat butter and margarine together.
Slowly add sugar (a little at a time).
Add plain flour.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Cook in a 250° oven for 1 hour.

title: microwave banana pudding
directions: Mix well the flour and water. Add egg yolks, sugar and milk. Microwave approximately 9 minutes (or until thick) on High. Remove and add butter and vanilla. Layer bottom of dish with vanilla wafers, layer of sliced bananas, 1/2 pudding, another layer of bananas and remainder of pudding. Top with vanilla wafers.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and oleo and pat in 7 1/2 x 11-inch pan and bake 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar; spread over crust, then sprinkle chopped nuts.
Spread on Cool Whip, then spread on pie filling and swirl through Cool Whip. Chill.

title: crabmeat salad
directions: Combine crabmeat and celery.
Mix remaining ingredients together; pour
over
crabmeat.
Mix
gently to avoid breaking lumps of crab.
Serve on lettuce.

title: sesame green beans
directions: In saucepan, bring beans and water to a boil; reduce heat to medium.
Cover and cook for 10-15 minutes or until the beans are crisp-tender; drain.
Add butter, soy sauce and sesame seeds.
Toss to coat.

title: frosted cocktail
directions: Cook sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Chill.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour half the mixture into blender.
Blend until light and frothy (7 to 8 seconds).
Repeat with other half of mixture.
Serve at once in chilled cocktail glasses with short straws.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Pack shrimp, onions and pepper in glass jar or other covered container. Mix other ingredients and pour over. Cover tightly. Be sure shrimp are all covered in ingredients. Store in refrigerator for at least 24 hours, but not more than a week. Shake often.

title: mixed mushroom and prosciutto sauce
directions: Heat the oil in large skillet.
Add mushrooms in batches. Saute on high heat until they begin to color.
Add the garlic, anchovies and Prosciutto; stir.
Then add the wine.
Cook until the wine is almost reduced.
Place the gnocchi in the skillet. Mix well and serve with a sprinkle of parsley.

title: pecan pies
directions: Beat with a large spoon sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add Karo and stir until blended.
Add pecan meats, butter and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (that has not been pricked) and bake for 1 hour in preheated oven at 300°.
Bake until center is firm.

title: cherry-cheese coffee cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla until smooth. Arrange rolls in circle forming pizza-like crust.
Press edges together.
