Reserve two triangles.
Spread cream cheese mixture evenly over dough.
Top with pie filling.
Press "perf" on reserved dough and cut into 4 strips.
Twist each strip and place on dough like wheel spokes attaching at edges.
Brush with egg white.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: imitation pecan pie or amish pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, butter, Karo, salt, flour, vanilla and water.
Beat all together.

title: garden pasta bake
directions: Cook pasta as package directs.
Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes, beans, 1/2 of cheese and soup.
Add pasta, salt, pepper and oregano.
Pour into 11 x 8 baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix well and form into small balls around well-drained olives. Freeze overnight on cookie sheet.
Bake frozen at 425° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: fruit freeze
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip; thoroughly whip.
Add frozen strawberries (partly thawed), pineapple and juice and bananas.
Freeze in large size Pyrex (13 x 9-inch).

title: biscotti(italian anise cookies)
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except flour.
Add flour, one cup at a time, until dough is thicker than cake batter.
Spread in pan.
Tap pan to remove air bubbles.
Bake 25 minutes; cool 5 minutes.
Invert to remove loaf.
Cut loaf into 1-inch slices.

title: savory green beans
directions: Place beans in a steamer basket. Place in a saucepan over 1-inch of water. Bring to a boil; cover and steam for 7 to 9 minutes or until crisp-tender.

title: butterscotch fudge
directions: Spread half of the nuts in the bottom of an 8-inch square foil-lined pan.
In a large saucepan, combine Fluff, sugar, milk, margarine and salt.
Bring to a full, rolling boil, over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add morsels, extract and rind; stir.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Remove chicken from oil and make gravy with remaining ingredients.
Return chicken to gravy and simmer until done. Serve with rice.

title: shrimp appetizer
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Press in large pie pan or dish.
Cover with shrimp cocktail sauce.
Place partially thawed salad shrimp over sauce.
Serve on crackers.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, about 4 hours. Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan; set aside.
In 4-quart saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and cereal and stir until well mixed.
With buttered spatula or fingers, press mixture evenly into greased pan.
Cool completely.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: donnie's mock turtle stew
directions: Cook meat in water, salt and pepper.
When tender, add margarine, milk, canned cream and mustard.
Bring back up to hot but do not boil.
Put in 2 tablespoons flour and cook until thick. Add egg yolks and serve.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Put in blender; blend well.
Keep chilled.
Makes a little over 3 cups.

title: szechuan chicken with cashews
directions: Cut chicken into 3/4-inch pieces.
Mix egg white, 1 teaspoon cornstarch, 1 teaspoon soy sauce and the white pepper in a medium bowl; stir in chicken.
Cover and refrigerate 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, juice, salt, flour and soda.
Beat after each ingredient.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Add a piece of pineapple to top.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together the sausage (do not fry), cheese and Bisquick. Make into small balls.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: fluffy dumplings
directions: Stir all ingredients well. Drop by spoonful on top of boiling liquid; cover and do not open for 15 minutes.

title: no-egg chocolate cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients and put in 8 x 8-inch ungreased pan. Make 3 indentations in mixture and put vanilla in one hole, vinegar in one and melted oleo in third.
Pour cold water over all and mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve iced or plain.

title: sunshine chip cookies
directions: In a small bowl, beat cream cheese with sugar, juice and orange peel until creamy.
Stir in mini chips.
Spread one cookie with about 1 tablespoon filling.
Top with second cookie. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Repeat.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: ethiopian snack
directions: Soak wheat overnight in hot water to cover.
Drain.
Place in heavy pan and add salt and cayenne pepper.
Roast, stirring constantly, over medium-high heat in a large, heavy pan until golden brown (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Add peanuts and roast about 5 more minutes.
Let cool; store in airtight container.

title: orange slice candy cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well after each.
Reserve 1/2 cup of flour.
Add soda and salt to the other 2 1/2 cups.
Add vanilla to buttermilk.
Alternately add flour mixture and candy with reserved 1/2 cup flour (coat candy with this 1/2 cup flour).
Add candy, nuts, raisins and coconut to batter; mix well.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan at 300° for 45 minutes.
After cake is baked, leave in pan.
Punch holes in top of cake.

title: meat balls and spaghetti
directions: Slightly beat eggs.
Add ground meat, then add bread crumbs, grated cheese, salt and pepper to taste and parsley.
Mix and form meat balls.
Brown in pan.

title: grilled peaches with raspberries
directions: Combine sugar and lime juice in bowl; stir well.
Add 1 cup raspberries and mash.
Add peaches, turning to coat.
Marinate at room temperature, cut side down, about 1 hour.
Remove peaches, reserving marinade.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil 6 cups water and dissolve 3 to 4 cups sugar in it and cool.
Add the juices and bananas to sugar water.
Mix well and freeze.
Remove from freezer about 2 hours before serving.
Pour Sprite or 7-Up into punch immediately before serving.
Very, very good.

title: pinto beans and ribs
directions: Wash and soak beans overnight.
Add enough water to cover; about 1 gallon.
Bring to a rolling boil for 30 minutes; reduce heat and let simmer for 1 to 2 hours.
Add pork ribs after beans have been cooking for 30 minutes.
Add chili powder and oil. Season to taste.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box and bake in 2 (9 x 13 x 2-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° until done.
Boil 1 cup Milnot and 1 cup of sugar.
Add marshmallows.
Melt.
Add coconut.
Spread on one cake layer.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cover with other layer.

title: macaroni vegetables salad
directions: In large bowl combine macaroni, vegetables, celery, radishes, salt and pepper.
Chill.
Add dressing and toss gently before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: veal or chicken sicilian
directions: Dredge meat in flour, salt and pepper mixture.
Brown lightly in hot oil.
Set aside.
In same skillet, saute artichokes and shallots about 5 minutes.
Add wine, peas and chicken broth, simmer 5 minutes.
Push vegetables to one side and return meat to skillet.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar and beat until light and lemon colored; beat in oil and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini, then add flour mixture, nuts and raisins.
Stir only until flour is moistened. Bake in 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain juices of blueberries and pineapple.
Should be 1 cup; if not, add water.
Bring to boil and add jello; stir until dissolved.
Add 2 cups cold water.
Let congeal.

title: cole slaw
directions: Wash and cut cabbage, blend in food processor along with carrots and onions.
Add pickle relish, salad dressing, salt, pepper, and sugar to taste.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken tenders in olive oil and Good Seasons Italian dressing mix.
Remove from pan.
Saute onion in the olive oil. When onion is cooked, add soy sauce (amount will vary according to taste).
Return chicken to pan with onion; simmer together 5 minutes.
Pour over 1 pound cooked spaghetti.
Enjoy!

title: oriental asparagus salad
directions: Cook asparagus until tender-crisp; mix sauce ingredients in a small bowl with a small whisk and pour over asparagus after draining.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix sugar and butter; add eggs and other ingredients.
Pour into well-greased and floured pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°. Cut in squares.

title: brown 'n serve rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in milk, sugar, salt, shortening and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in remaining flour to form soft dough.
Turn dough on lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and turn greased side up.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Bake in greased muffin pans or cake pans in preheated 400° oven for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
In a mixer bowl, cream butter and sugar for 15 minutes.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
With each yolk addition, also add 2 tablespoons poppy seed.
Stir in nuts and rind.
In a clean bowl with a clean beater, whip egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Sift flour and baking powder; beat into creamed mixture. Fold whites into creamed mixture.
Bake about 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: easy pickles
directions: To do this, you must figure the number of jars you are making. The mixture includes 1/2 the amount in water and 1/2 the amount in vinegar for each jar.
One cup sugar is added for each cup of the mixture.
Heat this mixture to a boil.

title: garlic shrimp
directions: To melted butter or margarine, add chopped garlic (best if placed in the microwave to cook garlic in butter) or cook on stove the butter and garlic until tender.
Then add all except lemon, coconut and shrimp.
Cook for a few minutes.
Add shrimp.
Cook until done.
Do not overcook.
Add lemon juice and coconut.
Stir for a few seconds with salt to taste.
Serve.

title: black-eyed pea hummus
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add first 4 ingredients.
Process 20 seconds, stopping once to scrape down sides.
Add black-eyed peas and next 4 ingredients; process the mixture until smooth.
Pour olive oil gradually through food chute with processor running.
Process until combined.
Cover and chill, if desired.

title: crock pot barbecue
directions: Put roast in crock-pot.
Do not add any liquids.
Cook for 8 hours (1 hour on high and 7 hours on medium or low).
Drain off all liquid that cooked out of roast; save 1 cup.
Put roast back in crock-pot.
Add barbecue sauce.
Begin cooking again. (Optional:
If you like, add 1/2 cup of the drained broth back to the pot and hold onto the rest for later if needed.)

The longer (6 to 8 hours) you cook with the barbecue sauce in the second phase, the tastier it becomes, however you will have to watch and stir frequently because the sauce will stick and burn on the sides of the pot.

title: artichoke nibbles(very good!)
directions: Drain marinade from 1 jar artichokes into saucepan.
Drain other jar and discard juice.
Chop artichokes and set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in marinade until tender.
In bowl beat eggs.
Add all the ingredients to eggs and turn into baking dish (7 x 11-inches), sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: southern cannonballs
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Roll into walnut size balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Drain and serve.
Yield: about 4 dozen servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw
the
frozen
spinach
and
squeeze all water from spinach
with your hand.
Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.
Serve
in
round loaf of bread, using cut out pieces of bread for dipping.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add dates or nuts, if desired. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and milk, stirring constantly.	Cook to soft ball
stage.
Put
Marshmallow Fluff, chocolate chips and vanilla in large
bowl
and
set
aside
while
cooking
sugar mixture. When it reaches soft ball stage, pour over marshmallow
mixture and beat until thoroughly mixed and begins to get stiff.
Pour into a buttered glass dish or cake pan (11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch pan).
Refrigerate until set.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Clean door knob peppers, making hole only large enough to take out seed.
Grate cabbage.
Stuff peppers as tightly as you can with cabbage.
Rinse cabbage off outside of peppers without getting inside wet.
(This just keeps so much cabbage from being in liquid in jars.)
Pack stuffed peppers in jars.
Add 2 pods of hot pepper to each quart jar.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Pour the half and half, vanilla and sugar in a bowl.
Whisk together and add a pinch of salt.
Quickly stir in snow until the mixture reaches ice cream consistency.
Top with chocolate syrup.

title: halloween bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° for 9 x 13-inch pan and 325° for glass pan.
Melt margarine or butter in pan (9 x 13-inch).
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over melted shortening.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over crumbs.
Place chips down next; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes; cut into bars.

title: aunt rita's california marinade
directions: Mix all of above.
Great for beef kabobs.
(Beef, red pepper, mushroom, squash, zucchini, onion, potato).
Marinade covers 2 1/2 pounds of meat.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms only of two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
In large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients except chocolate chips and walnuts.
Blend well on medium speed.
Stir in chips and walnuts.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until wooden pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: country skillet dinner
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic.
Reduce heat and spread on top of uncooked noodles.
Combine tomato sauce, mushrooms and oregano. Pour over noodles.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes.
Remove cover and sprinkle cheese on top and warm until cheese melts.

title: aunt eaqu's icebox rolls(easy)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Use a medium bowl.
Pour boiling water over sugar, salt and Crisco.
Stir until Crisco is almost dissolved.
Add 1 cup flour and mix well.
Add egg and second cup of flour; mix well.
Add third cup of flour, then yeast mixture. Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Take rice and spread on bottom of pan (9 x 13-inch).
Empty packets of onion soup out on top of rice and spread evenly.
Empty cans of soup out on top and mix all together.
Cut chicken in strips and layer on top of mix.
Then sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: pound cake deluxe
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
(Total beating time: 10 minutes.)
Add cake flour alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Pour batter into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Flour pan also. Don't cut oven on until you put cake in oven.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.

title: chocolate amaretto cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle chocolate wafer crumbs in bottom of a 7-inch baking pan.
Set aside.
Add cream cheese and next 7 ingredients; beat until smooth.
Add egg and continue mixing until all is well blended.
Fold in chocolate morsels.
Slowly pour mixture over crumbs in pan.
Bake at 300° for 65 to 70 minutes or until cheesecake is set.
Let cool in pan on wire rack.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours.
Garnish with chocolate curls, if desired.
Each serving contains about 200 calories.

title: rice consomme
directions: In skillet, melt butter.
Add onion, bell pepper and rice. Mix together until all are moist.
Remove from skillet and pour in casserole dish.
Add consomme.
Put in 350° oven for 1 hour.
The first 45 minutes, cook uncovered; add mushrooms.

title: heavenly chocolate caramel bars
directions: Mix cake mix with softened butter and egg until crumbly; reserve 1 1/2 cups.
Press remaining crumbly mixture in ungreased rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or glass dish.
Bake until crust seems dry, 10 to 12 minutes; cool 10 minutes.

title: baked sweet onions
directions: Saute onions in melted oleo.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine soup, half and half, salt and pepper.
Pour over onions.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture in pan.
Place bread slices on top and brush with 2 tablespoons melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: honey caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, honey and butter.
Bring to a boil.
Add cream of tartar and soda.
Pour over popped popcorn.
May be baked in slow oven for an hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Make a thin paste of food coloring and Nestle Quik.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add whole eggs and color paste.
Mix together. Sift together cake flour and salt.
Sift 3 times.
Add alternately the buttermilk and dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Beat with mixer for 3 minutes.
Remove from mixer; add vinegar and soda. Mix into batter by hand.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 8-inch round pans at 350° for 35 minutes or in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 250°.
When finished, roll in confectioners sugar.
Good to use for showers.

title: chicken combo
directions: Cook chicken until well done.
Fix 1 cup Minute rice well done.
While this is cooking, cut up cabbage.
Slice onion real thin.
Slice pepper.
Fry 1 package bacon until well done.
Put cabbage, pepper and onion in a kettle.
Put in a little cooking oil.
After chicken, rice, bacon is done, crumble up in a bowl. Fry cabbage, pepper and onion well done.
Mix after fried and cooked with chicken and rice mixture.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break in half and boil spaghetti (no salt); drain off water and let cool.
Cut tomatoes, peppers and cucumbers (don't peel). Put on top of spaghetti.
Pour all salad seasoning and Italian dressing.
Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: calico macaroni for 60
directions: Precook macaroni.
Set aside in large roaster oven.
Cook ground meat.
Add to macaroni.
Mix well.
Add corn (liquor and all).
Mix well.
Add 1 can spaghetti sauce.
Mix, adding part of second can if necessary.
Will be a bit "soupy".
Add 1/2 of the grated cheese.
Mix well.
Warm on low heat, stirring often.
Add more spaghetti sauce if needed.
Serve with a bit of the remainder of grated cheese on top.
Serves 60.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar, butter and nutmeg well.
Surround each marshmallow with a heaping tablespoonful of potato.
Roll in coconut and bake at 350° just until marshmallows melt.
Makes 16 potato balls.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut
biscuits into fourths.
Put 1 cup sugar and cinnamon into a bowl and place 8 biscuit pieces at a time into it. Shake
until well coated; repeat until all are coated with the mixture.
Place pieces
into
a
buttered
Bundt pan or large skillet,
layering them until all are used.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks butter
and
cup sugar together and pour over top of biscuits.
Bake
at
for 30
minutes.
Remove immediately. Cool.
Top with confectioners icing, if desired.

title: sweet and spicy barbecue steaks
directions: In small bowl, combine sauce ingredients; mix well.
Reserve 1/2 cup to serve as sauce.
Place beef steaks on grid over ash covered medium coals.
Grill for 12 to 16 minutes for medium-rare to medium doneness, turning once.
Brush both sides of steaks with remaining sauce during the last 3 to 4 minutes of grilling.
Carve steaks into slices.
Serve with reserved sauce.
Makes 4.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
In mixing bowl, mix the rice, margarine, soup and corn.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish; bake at 350° until warm.
Add Cheez Whiz on top; return until cheese melts.
(You may melt Cheez Whiz in microwave and pour over top.)

title: vegetable chowder
directions: Combine water and bouillon cubes in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Add vegetables; cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apple, celery and raisins in a medium bowl.
Combine mayonnaise substitute and lemon juice, stirring well to blend. Add to fruit mixture and toss lightly to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Serving amount is 1 cup with 98 calories.
Diabetic Exchange:
1 fruit and 1 fat.

title: creamed turkey soup
directions: In large Dutch oven over medium-high heat in hot butter or margarine, cook onion until tender.
Add chicken broth and potatoes and cook for 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: In a small bowl, cream together until light the sugar and butter.
Beat in egg and mashed bananas.
Stir creamed mixture alternately with sour milk into flour.
Add nuts.
Place in a greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: slaw
directions: Heat all ingredients, except cabbage, to boiling.
Pour over cabbage.
Store in refrigerator.
Keeps 2 weeks.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together raw, roll in size of marbles.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until brown.
May be frozen.
Makes 200.

title: raspberry bread pudding(with white chocolate sauce)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Generously butter a 9x13x2 inch baking pan. Combine the can of raspberries with enough milk to make 4 cups. Pour this over the bread chunks. Stir and set aside. In another bowl, combine the eggs, sugar and vanilla extract. Beat until mixed. Combine the egg mixture with the bread mixture and pour it into the prepared pan. Bake for about an hour or until set. Serve with White Chocolate Sauce.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Cream sugars, butter and peanut butter together. Beat eggs, milk and vanilla. Sift flour, soda and salt. Stir in with the batter. Chill thoroughly. Shape into balls the size of a walnut, then roll in additional sugar. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350°. Press chocolate Hershey's Kisses in the center while hot.

title: flaxseed meal bread
directions: Dissolve the yeast in 2 Tbsp. warm water and set aside until bubbly, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Add honey, oil, and salt to the remaining 1 1/4 c. warm water.
When the yeast water is ready, add to the honey mixture.
Add flaxseed meal, whole wheat flour, and 1 c. bread flour to water and mix well.
Add enough of the remaining bread flour to make a soft, kneadable dough.
Place the dough on a lightly floured surface and knead for 10 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Shape the dough in a loaf and place in the pan.
Let the dough rise in a warm place for 1 hour.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 to 50 minutes or until the loaf sounds hollow when tapped.

title: sponge candy or fairy food
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and vinegar in a large saucepan.
Cover tightly and bring to a boil.
Uncover and place a candy thermometer in the pan.
Without stirring, cook over medium heat to 300°. Gradually lower heat as mixture thickens, to prevent scorching. Remove from heat and quickly stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Turn into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not spread.
Candy will spread itself.
Cool.
Break into pieces.
May eat candy as is or you may dip pieces in chocolate dip.

title: rice creole
directions: In frying pan simmer cut onion, diced green pepper and cubed ham in the butter.
Season.
Add rice and tomatoes.
Bake in casserole 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in shortening; remove.
Blend flour into shortening from which meat was removed. Add catsup, water, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, garlic and chopped onion. Bring to a boil.
Lower heat to simmer for 20 minutes. Drop meat into sauce and cook only until tender.
(This much can be done 2 or 3 days before serving and stored in refrigerator.).
Ten minutes before serving, add fresh vegetables. Cook until crisply tender, about 10 minutes. Serve on hot fluffy rice. Serves 6.

title: sweet potatoes with nuts
directions: Beat eggs; mix well with all other ingredients.
Put in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Top with Nut Topping.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Put popped corn in a large container.
In a 2-quart saucepan, combine molasses, sugar and salt.
Cook over medium heat to hard ball stage, 250°.

title: easy rice pudding
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Mix egg, sugar and vanilla with rice.
Add evaporated milk and water and bring to a boil.
Simmer until thick.
Put into serving dishes and cool.

title: bruschetta
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the tomatoes, minced garlic, basil, parsley, lemon juice, red pepper flakes and salt and pepper to taste.
Toss very well; set aside for at least 3 hours.

title: wild west chow
directions: Brown meat; add onions, beans, tomatoes and enough water to cover.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.
Break vermicelli into 1 inch pieces and add to pot.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes more.
Fritos or grated cheese may be sprinkled on top prior to serving.
Makes 20 to 25 servings.

title: wild western chili soup
directions: In large, heavy pan, brown beef and cook onion with garlic until tender (use shortening, if necessary).
Stir to separate meat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Makes about 12 cups.

title: fruit slush
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Blend on high until the thickness of a milk shake.
Drink.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine sugar and butter; cream.
Add, alternating, milk and dry ingredients.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour in muffin pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in salted water a few minutes to soften; drain. Mix 2 tablespoons soup with the rest of the ingredients.
Divide the mixture among the cabbage leaves.
Fold in sides and roll up; secure with toothpicks.
In skillet, place rolls, seal side down. Pour on soup.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Stir now and then. Spoon sauce over rolls.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk and stir with a fork only until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Stir in cheese, dry mustard and red pepper.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured board or pastry cloth and knead just until smooth.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness and cut with floured 2-inch cutter.
Place biscuits, lightly touching on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Place diced (cooked) chicken in bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Place cooked broccoli on top.
In bowl, mix together soup, lemon juice, curry powder and mayonnaise.
Pour on top of broccoli.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: quick energy bars
directions: Toast oats in shallow pan at 350° for 15 minutes.
Grease 9-inch pan with oleo. Melt marshmallows, peanut butter, honey and oleo.
Pour into pan and chill until firm. Cut into bars.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Cook in a large pot on low for several hours.
Serve over a hot bed of rice.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add ground beef and brown.
Add onion and cook until it is transparent.
Stir in remaining ingredients except flour and milk.
Cover and cook over low heat until vegetables are tender.
Combine flour and 1 cup of milk.
Stir into soup and bring to a boil.
Add remaining 3 cups of milk and serve.

title: anisette boscotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and set a rack in the middle level.
Line a jelly roll pan or a cookie sheet with parchment or foil.
Combine eggs, anise extract, anisette and sugar and whip by mixing on medium speed about 6 or 7 minutes.
Stir together flour, cornstarch and baking powder.
Sift over and fold by hand into egg mixture in 3 additions.
If you don't want to pipe batter into pan, use a large spoon to form the logs.
Bake the logs about 20 minutes until well risen and firm.
Cool on pan.
Slice the logs diagonally at 1/2-inch.
Return the cut Biscotti, cut side down, and bake an additional 15 minutes, until lightly colored and dry.
Cool on pan. Store in tin.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Sift flour, soda, nutmeg and cinnamon together.
Add alternately the buttermilk to first mixture.
Add prunes, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pan, well-buttered.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove meat from bones.
Reserve 1/2 can noodles.
Mix ingredients together in large Pyrex pan.
Put reserved noodles on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder. Add to mixture. Blend in oats and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: kings caramel corn
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Have popped corn in 2 large bowls or pans. In saucepan, heat sugar, oleo, syrup, soda and salt, stirring occasionally, until bubbly around the edges. Cook slowly for about 5 minutes.
Pour over popped corn and stir well.
Place in 2 ungreased large pans.
Bake in oven 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes, until well coated. When cool, store in airtight containers to retain freshness.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix together and put in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Chill.
Also good in a graham cracker crust.

title: russian cream
directions: In a small saucepan, mix sugar and gelatin.
Add water and put mixture aside for 5 minutes, allowing it to set.
Next, place saucepan on medium to medium-high heat.
Stir constantly and bring to a full, rolling boil.
Remove pan from heat and add cream.
Mix sour cream and vanilla together and gradually beat it into the gelatin mixture.
Pour into 6 (1/2 cup) molds or dessert cups. Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.

title: tomato mozzarella salad
directions: On a large serving platter, alternate tomatoes and mozzarella slices.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients.
Cream together butter, lemon juice, vanilla and almond extract.
Gradually add 1 cup plus 2 tablespoons sugar.
Add in thirds, beating well eggs.
Blend in dry ingredients in fourths.
Turn batter into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes until done.
Delicious.

title: rice and corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: texas caviar
directions: Place peas in pan or bowl.
Add oil, vinegar, garlic, onion and salt; mix thoroughly.
Store in jar in refrigerator, and remove garlic after one day.
Store at least two days or as long as two weeks before eating.
Serve with crackers or tortilla chips.

title: shrimp and sausage jambalaya
directions: Saute seasonings in olive oil.
Add shrimp and cook until shrimp are cooked.
Boil sausage to remove fat and drain.
Add to shrimp mixture.
Mix tomato sauce and consomme; add enough water to equal 4 cups.
Add this to mixture and add seasoning.
You want to over-season because rice will absorb seasoning.
Add rice and boil until liquid is absorbed.
Cover and cook on low until rice is done.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients. Spoon onto hot grill. For lighter pancakes, fluff egg whites.

title: finger paints
directions: Whip together water and soap flakes until smooth.
Divide into several portions and add food coloring.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
Combine mix, milk, parsley and cheese until dough forms.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased or non-stick cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes until brown. Melt butter and garlic powder.
Brush over hot biscuits.
I bake in mini muffin pan for a bite size appetizer.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Combine water and salt in medium saucepan; bring to a boil. Add grits, cover and reduce heat.
Cook 10 minutes or until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add next 5 ingredients; stir until cheese melts.
Pour mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: frozen salad
directions: Boil pineapple, sugar and jello for 3 1/2 to 5 minutes, cool. Beat chilled milk and softened cream cheese in a chilled bowl. Add cooled jello mixture.
Freeze in small cake pan.
Garnish with nuts and cherries.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Beat together the cream cheese, sour cream, oregano, garlic powder and red pepper in a small mixing bowl.
Spread in a 9 or 10-inch quiche dish or pie plate.
Spread pizza sauce over top. Sprinkle with pepperoni, onions and green peppers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.
Serve with sweet peppers, broccoli, crackers, etc.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Use rolling pin and break pretzels into small pieces.
Mix with sugar and margarine and press into pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: speedy guacamole
directions: Combine
cheese
and avocados;	mix well until blended. Mix in	salsa to taste.
Serve with nacho chips and vegetable dippers.

title: stuffed pepper soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat. Add peppers to beef and saute for 3 to 5 minutes. Stir in all other ingredients and reduce heat to low or medium. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Last, stir in rice and heat through.

title: homemade pancake mix(makes 2 pounds)
directions: Fry on ungreased hot griddle.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: ritz cracker chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of oiled casserole dish.
Mix sour cream with soup and pour over chicken.
Crumble Ritz crackers over top.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and pour over all.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Good!

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter and stir in sugar, juice and orange rind.
Heat, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Stir in oats and pecans.
Chill mixture for 1 hour.
Shape into balls.
Roll in coconut flakes. Makes about 30 cookies.

title: strawberry daiquiri
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender, then fill to the top with ice cubes.
Blend.
Pour into prepared glasses.
Serve.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Use medium size pan.

title: fresh coconut cake frosting
directions: Originally the country cook's solution for using up stale bread as well as cream and eggs, bread pudding is now considered an elegant dessert.
This rich version is accented with pecans and accompanied with bourbon sauce.

title: chesapeake bay crab imperial
directions: Remove any shell or cartilage from crab meat.
Combine mayonnaise, pimiento, salt, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco and Old Bay seasoning.
Pour over crab meat and mix lightly.

title: blond brownies
directions: Mix together all ingredients in a microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on High for a total of 7 minutes.
Check after 4 minutes and rotate bowl 1/2 turn.
Continue cooking for 3 minutes. Brownies are done when toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Combine all ingredients. Shape into patties or drop by large tablespoon into 1/4-inch hot oil. Cook on both sides until golden.

title: tacos
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain fat. Stir in dried ingredients, then add the water. Simmer, stirring, until thickened.

title: no bake pineapple pie
directions: Add pineapple juice to instant pudding.
Stir with wire whip just until dissolved.
Add sour cream and sugar; blend, then stir in crushed pineapple.
Pour into shell.
Chill 2 hours; top with Cool Whip.

title: pasta with scallops
directions: Poach scallops in lemon water, about 3 minutes.
Set aside.

title: raw broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill and serve.

title: homemade "cracker jacks"
directions: Mix corn and peanuts together in large bowl or roasting pan. Keep warm in 250° oven.
Melt butter in heavy 2-quart saucepan. Stir in the brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Then boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in soda and vanilla.
Quickly pour over warm popcorn and nuts while tossing until well coated.
Spread out on shallow baking pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Make sure every piece of popcorn has been moved around on the bottom.
Remove and turn out on foil to cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: corn casserole
directions: Place ingredients in well-greased casserole dish and top with Cheddar cheese the last 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
